uddha: A Philosopher’s Quest for the Meaning of Emptiness\u003c/em\u003e. Princeton, NJ: Princeton University Press, 1994.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"workUuid\":null},{\"uuid\":\"bde04e5d-a7fd-4098-a0b4-e1d9a6c7e67e\",\"html\":\"\u003cp\u003eEdgerton, Franklin (1937). “Buddhist Sanskrit saṃdha, saṃdhi(-nirmocana).” \u003cem\u003eJournal of the American Oriental Society\u003c/em\u003e 5, vol. 2 (1937): 185–88.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"workUuid\":null},{\"uuid\":\"6f7a3fa3-a011-4454-9cc1-94edfe8f53e3\",\"html\":\"\u003cp\u003eEdgerton, Franklin (1953). \u003cem\u003eBuddhist Hybrid Sanskrit Grammar and Dictionary\u003c/em\u003e. Vol. 2, \u003cem\u003eDictionary\u003c/em\u003e. New Haven: Yale University Press, 1953.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"workUuid\":null},{\"uuid\":\"c46adf1e-4ea5-4240-bfc4-bfba197c5c33\",\"html\":\"\u003cp\u003eFiordalis, David V. “The Wondrous Display of Superhuman Power in the \u003cem\u003eVimalakīrtinirdeśa\u003c/em\u003e: Miracle or Marvel?” In \u003cem\u003eYoga Powers: Extraordinary Capacities Attained Through Meditation and Concentration\u003c/em\u003e, edited by Knut Axel Jacobsen, 96–125. Leiden: Brill, 2012.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"workUuid\":null},{\"uuid\":\"3baae8ca-b504-4e5a-a06d-e77758d3be35\",\"html\":\"\u003cp\u003eFrauwallner, Erich. \u003cem\u003eDie Philosophie des Buddhismus\u003c/em\u003e. Berlin: Akademie-Verlag, 1969.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"workUuid\":null},{\"uuid\":\"802ec682-9288-40c9-b2b5-a50a175b9cd1\",\"html\":\"\u003cp\u003eGómez, Luis O. “On Buddhist wonders and wonder-working.” \u003cem\u003eJournal of the International Association of Buddhist Studies\u003c/em\u003e 33, no. 1–2 (2011): 513–54.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"workUuid\":null},{\"uuid\":\"6197a439-bb0f-4fb0-91a7-2398b70d7582\",\"html\":\"\u003cp\u003eHall, Bruce Cameron. “The Meaning of Vijñapti in Vasubandhu’s Concept of Mind.” \u003cem\u003eJournal of the International Association of Buddhist Studies\u003c/em\u003e 9, no. 1 (1986): 7–23.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"workUuid\":null},{\"uuid\":\"e621db8d-41