\u003c/p\u003e\",\"workUuid\":null},{\"uuid\":\"d156ccd3-b779-4fb4-815e-03b8f9cf35b1\",\"html\":\"\u003cp\u003eTakahashi, Kōichi. “A Premise of the trilakṣaṇa theory in the \u003cem\u003eSandhinirmocanasūtra\u003c/em\u003e.” In \u003cem\u003eJournal of Indian and Buddhist Studies (=Indobukkyogaku Kenkyu)\u003c/em\u003e 54, no. 3 (2006): 85–92.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"workUuid\":null},{\"uuid\":\"d6158168-597c-4235-9edc-1852bb14181d\",\"html\":\"\u003cp\u003eTakasaki, Jikido. \u003cem\u003eA Study on the Ratnagotravibhāga (Uttaratantra): Being a Treatise on the Tathāgatagarbha Theory of Mahāyāna Buddhism\u003c/em\u003e. Serie Orientale Roma 32. Roma: Istituto italiano per il Medio ed Estremo Oriente, 1966.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"workUuid\":null},{\"uuid\":\"140128b9-122b-42b2-b492-7fbe5adee598\",\"html\":\"\u003cp\u003eTillemans, Tom J. F. “On a recent translation of the \u003cem\u003eSaṃdhi­nirmocana­sūtra\u003c/em\u003e.” In \u003cem\u003eJournal of the International Association of Buddhist Studies\u003c/em\u003e 20, no. 1 (1997): 153–64.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"workUuid\":null},{\"uuid\":\"ed6f0e53-2abd-4bbf-b102-1d4b2026f454\",\"html\":\"\u003cp\u003eTucci, Giuseppe. \u003cem\u003eMinor Buddhist Texts Part III: Third Bhāvanākrama\u003c/em\u003e. Serie Orientale Roma 43. Roma: Istituto italiano per il Medio ed Estremo Oriente, 1971.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"workUuid\":null},{\"uuid\":\"60842fde-a680-4eb6-8971-b89d2afcd12d\",\"html\":\"\u003cp\u003eVinay, Jean-Paul, and Jean Darbelnet. \u003cem\u003eComparative Stylistics of French and English: A Methodology for Translation\u003c/em\u003e. Amsterdam: John Benjamins, 1958.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"workUuid\":null},{\"uuid\":\"424e3a2b-9119-429e-9bdc-3e8c6be3b4a2\",\"html\":\"\u003cp\u003eWaldron, William S. \u003cem\u003eThe Buddhist Unconscious: The ālaya-vijñāna in the context of Indian Buddhist Thought\u003c/em\u003e. London: RoutledgeCurzon, 2003.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"workUuid\":null},{\"uuid\":\"0e429303-5ea8-4e48-a21f-b449d6bad557\",\"html\":\"\u003cp\u003eWare, James. Review of \u003cem\u003eSaṃdhi­nirmocana­sūtra, l’explication des mystères\u003c/em\u003e, by Étienne Lamotte. \u003cem\u003eJournal of the American Oriental Society\u003c/em\u003e 57, no. 1 (1937): 122–24.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"workUuid\":null},{\"uuid\":\"c9fbdc4a-448c-40af-bb97-1aef5cc028e1\",\"html\":\"\u003cp\u003eWayman, Alex. “The Mirror as a Pan-Buddhist Metaphor-Simile.” \u003cem\u003eHistory of Religions\u003c/em\u003e 13, no. 4 (1974): 251–69.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"workUuid\":null},{\"uuid\":\"be6efabd-734a-48b6-8308-0032964b27b2\",\"html\":\"\u003cp\u003eWedemeyer, Christian K. “Review of \u003cem\u003eJñānagarbha’s Commentary on Just the Maitreya Chapter from the Saṃdhi­nirmocana­sūtra: Study, Translation and Tibetan Text\u003c/em\u003e, by John Powers.” \u003cem\u003eJournal of the American Oriental Society\u003c/em\u003e 123, no. 3 (2003): 681–84. \u003c/p\u003e\",\"workUuid\":null},{\"uuid\":\"98e99bf8-ab53-40bd-9c7e-69863a6474c7\",\"html\":\"\u003cp\u003eXing, Guang. \u003cem\u003eThe Concept of the Buddha: Its evolution from early Buddhism to the “trikāya” theory\u003c/em\u003e. RoutledgeCurzon Critical Studies in Buddhism. London: RoutledgeCurzon, 2005.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"workUuid\":null},{\"uuid\":\"8cb94704-3a02-42dd-8acf-99b1cdd907f4\",\"html\":\"\u003cp\u003eYoshimizu, Chizuko (1996). “On the Four Kinds of yukti in the Tenth Chapter of the \u003cem\u003eSaṃdhi­nirmocana­sūtra\u003c/em\u003e.” \u003cem\u003eJournal of Naritasan Institute for Buddhist Studies\u003c/em\u003e 19 (1996): 123–68.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"workUuid\":null},{\"uuid\":\"3de8213f-f821-484a-8698-04ea1ae4f8b4\",\"html\":\"\u003cp\u003eYoshimizu, Chizuko (2010). “The Logic of the \u003cem\u003eSandhi­nirmocana­sūtra\u003c/em\u003e: Establishing Right Reasoning Based on Similarity (\u003cem\u003esārūpya\u003c/em\u003e) and Dissimilarity (\u003cem\u003evairūpya\u003c/em\u003e).” In \u003cem\u003eLogic in Earliest Classical India\u003c/em\u003e, edited by Brendan S. Gillon, 139–66. Delhi: Motilal Banarsidass, 2010.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"workUuid\":null}]}],\"endnotes\":[{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"9618a9da-8d06-45bd-9a17-24bbf8c4e106\",\"sort\":12373,\"type\":\"endnotesHeader\",\"label\":\"n.\",\"alignments\":{}},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"heading\",\"attrs\":{\"level\":2,\"start\":0,\"end\":5,\"uuid\":\"cb51af10-d76e-4119-9c8d-6429ad1a4a01\",\"class\":\"section-title\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Notes\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":5}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"2cd1e46e-5bad-4396-a0c2-8b521c409b5e\",\"sort\":12375,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.1\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"From a broader perspective, it is possible to consider that the teaching imparted in this sūtra is structured in terms of the basis (āśraya), the path (mārga), and the result (phala). The first four chapters on the five characteristics of the ultimate as defined in the Prajñāpāramitā sūtras represent a teaching on the abovementioned basis, namely, true reality (tathatā) as it is; chapters 5–9, a teaching on the path in terms of practices and stages to attain awakening; and chapter 10, a teaching on the result through the doctrine of the tathāgatas’ bodies and activity to awaken beings. All major Tibetan traditions consider chapter 3, focusing on the relation between the two truths, and chapter 8, focusing on meditative practice, to be authoritative. These are among the scriptures most quoted on their respective topics by Tibetan authors regardless of lineage.\",\"label\":\"i.5\",\"sort\":206,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"0f01cd34-93e0-4109-9626-30e5fa330707\",\"workUuid\":\"da0adcd3-4abf-406a-8021-b656a348fab8\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-049-001-9\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":30,\"uuid\":\"2cd1e46e-5bad-4396-a0c2-8b521c409b5e\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"See glossary entry “\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":20}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ultimate\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":20,\"end\":28},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"1ce42c0c-900f-47c2-9d40-98ccbafcb2bf\",\"uuid\":\"afac3de2-b877-470e-ac72-bb20319f80f0\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\".”\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":28,\"end\":30}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"94511998-09ff-4246-ba5c-ac0c7d5d6562\",\"sort\":12379,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.2\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"Chapter 5 is a presentation of the “secrets of mind, thought, and cognition.” Here the Buddha introduces the concept of “appropriating cognition” (ādānavijñāna), also called “subliminal cognition” (ālayavijñāna), “mind” (citta), or “mind containing all the seeds” (sarvabījaṃ cittam). This mind, in which mental events manifest, acts is like a mirror in which reflections appear. It is the basis of previous mental imprints resulting from volitions and actions that create predispositions (i.e., latent dispositions) to experience reality in conventional terms. However, once bodhisattvas cognize in an intuitive and personal way the ultimate by means of gnosis, they no longer perceive this mind. In the closing verses of this chapter, the Buddha explains that this mind is without a self, since it is conditioned and composed by seeds. Through these definitions, the Buddha de facto delineates two realms: the domain of dualistic mind and the domain of nondual gnosis.\",\"label\":\"i.9\",\"sort\":392,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"41a1ccd2-14f5-499b-9811-312f1c8a624b\",\"workUuid\":\"da0adcd3-4abf-406a-8021-b656a348fab8\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-049-001-14\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":50,\"uuid\":\"94511998-09ff-4246-ba5c-ac0c7d5d6562\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"See Brunnhölzl 2018, p. 1590, n. 89 on this point.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":50}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"43f52e19-547e-4233-9bc2-7dbdd0be42ae\",\"sort\":12381,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.3\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"$20\",\"label\":\"i.10\",\"sort\":444,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"4d317cad-071a-4e20-9e4c-9ccda349abec\",\"workUuid\":\"da0adcd3-4abf-406a-8021-b656a348fab8\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-049-001-17\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":93,\"uuid\":\"43f52e19-547e-4233-9bc2-7dbdd0be42ae\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"The numbering of paragraphs of the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":35}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Saṃdhi­nirmocana­sūtra\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":35,\"end\":57},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"57c9f8f1-0b9f-40e4-aa07-2e66caf2344d\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" follows Lamotte’s critical edition.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":57,\"end\":93}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"778c8557-fa39-40b4-990e-b3aa451bd8f4\",\"sort\":12385,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.4\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"$21\",\"label\":\"i.22\",\"sort\":1209,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"ffab1b2b-46cd-4a70-ae1f-4d8ad301a8a4\",\"workUuid\":\"da0adcd3-4abf-406a-8021-b656a348fab8\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-049-001-30\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":178,\"uuid\":\"778c8557-fa39-40b4-990e-b3aa451bd8f4\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"See Radich 2007, p. 1257 on the relationship between \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":53}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"āśraya­parivṛtti\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":53,\"end\":69},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":53,\"end\":69,\"uuid\":\"e5e79718-b07b-4077-aac0-041170b2bfba\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" and \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":69,\"end\":74}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"dauṣṭhulyakāya\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":74,\"end\":88},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":74,\"end\":88,\"uuid\":\"35dc2d0e-08d7-41e5-828e-8e3e2c8302ac\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"072b1969-eda8-4f65-8019-8dc01bc43ed8\",\"uuid\":\"3d5fc5eb-d605-46db-820e-da238d6b848b\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". Saṃdh. is the only text in the entire Kangyur in which the term \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":88,\"end\":154}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"dauṣṭhulyakāya\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":154,\"end\":168},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":154,\"end\":168,\"uuid\":\"8fb6b96b-2760-4333-90d9-db91d0bd1ba6\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"072b1969-eda8-4f65-8019-8dc01bc43ed8\",\"uuid\":\"43782b5f-c11a-49b9-bcf2-d2629141422f\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" is found.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":168,\"end\":178}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"2ac09f3c-06c5-47c4-adca-f4bb648091ff\",\"sort\":12393,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.5\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"$22\",\"label\":\"i.26\",\"sort\":1338,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"eeb05c89-0228-4d81-ae1a-91e5e51e0152\",\"workUuid\":\"da0adcd3-4abf-406a-8021-b656a348fab8\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-049-001-35\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":72,\"uuid\":\"2ac09f3c-06c5-47c4-adca-f4bb648091ff\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"In bold are textual resources I used to translate the text into English.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":72}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"cfed8d0e-d3ac-45c8-84f8-68b57f2b0db0\",\"sort\":12395,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.6\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"$23\",\"label\":\"i.26\",\"sort\":1338,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"eeb05c89-0228-4d81-ae1a-91e5e51e0152\",\"workUuid\":\"da0adcd3-4abf-406a-8021-b656a348fab8\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-049-001-35\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":126,\"uuid\":\"cfed8d0e-d3ac-45c8-84f8-68b57f2b0db0\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"See Powers 2015. Unfortunately, I haven’t been able to consult this reference work at the time of completing this translation.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":126}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"426ce268-8f64-4bb1-a834-eac6da8fc73a\",\"sort\":12397,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.7\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"$24\",\"label\":\"i.26\",\"sort\":1338,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"eeb05c89-0228-4d81-ae1a-91e5e51e0152\",\"workUuid\":\"da0adcd3-4abf-406a-8021-b656a348fab8\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-049-001-35\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":80},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Here is a list of the sigla I used to identify the various witnesses of Saṃdh.: \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":80}}]},{\"type\":\"bulletList\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":80,\"end\":1448,\"uuid\":\"67a31fed-d6b9-4723-9025-a40d3b041a56\",\"spacing\":\"vertical\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"listItem\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"(1) Witnesses of the sūtra found in the available Kangyurs and canonical collections (MsK = manuscript Kangyur, PK = xylograph): K\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":80,\"end\":210}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ʙ\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":210,\"end\":211},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"smallCaps\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":210,\"end\":211,\"uuid\":\"8fca0832-e7d9-4537-a571-12526c706ec7\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"small-caps\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\": Berlin MsK, C: Choné PK, Cz: Chizhi, D: Degé PK, Dd: Dodedrak, Dk: Dongkarla, F: Phukdrag MsK, H: Lhasa PK, Gt: Gangteng, He: Hemis I, J: ’jang sa tham/Lithang PK, L: London (Shelkar) MsK, Lg: Lang mdo, N: Narthang PK, Ng: Namgyal, Np: Neyphug, O: Tawang, Pj: Phajoding I, Pz: Phajoding II, K\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":211,\"end\":505}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ǫ\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":505,\"end\":506},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"smallCaps\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":505,\"end\":506,\"uuid\":\"c759c95d-ecec-404a-bbee-e372f073bf05\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"small-caps\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\": Peking 1737 PK, R: Ragya, S: Stok MsK, T: Tokyo MsK, U: Urga PK, V: Ulaanbaatar MsK, W: Wangli supplement, X: Basgo MsK, Z: Shey Palace MsK. Other canonical collections: Ba: Basgo fragments (Ladakh), Bd: Bardan (Zanskar), Go: Gondhla (Lahaul), Do: Dolpo. Source: http://www.rkts.org (last accessed on July 20, 2020). I am following the typology of Kangyur groups suggested by rKTs (Vienna University). I would like to warmly thank Professor Helmut Tauscher and Bruno Lainé for making available to me the editions I used for this translation project. For a general discussion of some Tibetan sources, see Skilling 1994, p. 775. \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":506,\"end\":1135}}],\"attrs\":{\"start\":80,\"end\":1135,\"uuid\":\"5594d7ba-5232-4d34-b17a-8b04fecc8879\"}}],\"attrs\":{\"start\":80,\"end\":1135,\"uuid\":\"5594d7ba-5232-4d34-b17a-8b04fecc8879\"}},{\"type\":\"listItem\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"(2) Xylographs of the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1135,\"end\":1157}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Viniścaya­saṃ­grahaṇī\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1157,\"end\":1178},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"a6c3a07b-6256-45b8-8770-19cb6134fee5\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" of the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1178,\"end\":1186}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Yogācāra­bhūmi\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1186,\"end\":1200},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"25c61e4a-efed-4f09-941d-f393b715b8c5\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" from the Tengyur: VD Degé, VG Golden, VP Peking. My thanks go to Kojirō Katō for having shared with me the bibliographical detail of these witnesses. The \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1200,\"end\":1355}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Viniścaya­saṃ­grahaṇī\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1355,\"end\":1376},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"5082e0c0-7cff-402b-bb79-9371e8c51732\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" is also available in Chinese under the following title: 瑜伽師地論卷第七十六攝決擇分.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1376,\"end\":1448}}],\"attrs\":{\"start\":1135,\"end\":1448,\"uuid\":\"442a952c-46a7-44dc-beda-b041679049b6\"}}],\"attrs\":{\"start\":1135,\"end\":1448,\"uuid\":\"442a952c-46a7-44dc-beda-b041679049b6\"}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"26dd1610-db27-4baf-9a4b-c96bada166ba\",\"sort\":12414,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.8\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"$25\",\"label\":\"i.26\",\"sort\":1338,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"eeb05c89-0228-4d81-ae1a-91e5e51e0152\",\"workUuid\":\"da0adcd3-4abf-406a-8021-b656a348fab8\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-049-001-35\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":106,\"uuid\":\"26dd1610-db27-4baf-9a4b-c96bada166ba\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"For the reference of possible additional folios, see Chayet 2005, p. 67 (n°615‍—1 folio, n°590‍—6 folios).\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":106}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"efdfff56-ad51-4dd9-8b40-ac164ab00a99\",\"sort\":12416,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.9\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"In addition, five commentaries have been composed on the Saṃdhi­nirmocana­sūtra:• Asaṅga’s Āryasaṃdhi­nirmocanabhāṣya (dgongs pa nges par ’grel pa’i rnam par bshad pa) D3981 mdo ’grel (mdo), ngi 1b–11b • Wonch’uk’s *Āryagambhīrasaṃdhi­nirmocana­sūtraṭīkā (dgongs pa zab mo nges par ’grel pa’i mdo rgya cher ’grel pa) D4016 mdo ’grel (mdo), ti 1b–di 175a • Jñāṇagarbha’s Āryasaṃdhi­nirmocanasūtre ārya­maitreya­kevala­parivarta­bhāṣya (dgongs pa nges par ’grel pa’i mdo las ’phags pa byams pa’i le’u nyi tshe bshad pa) D4033 mdo ’grel (sems tsam), bi 318b–345a • Changchup Dzutrül (byang chub rdzu ’phrul)’s *Āryasaṃdhi­nirmocana­sūtravyākhyāna (bstan bcos sna tshogs), D4358 mdo ’grel, co 1b–jo 183b • Trisong Detsen (khri srong lde brtsan)’s *Samyagvāk­pramāṇoddhṛta­sūtra (bka’ yang dag pa’i tshad ma las mdo btus pa) D4352 mdo ’grel (bstan bcos sna tshogs), co 173a–205b\",\"label\":\"i.27\",\"sort\":1562,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"0a177da6-28a3-4974-a130-ac06bdf5cda6\",\"workUuid\":\"da0adcd3-4abf-406a-8021-b656a348fab8\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-049-001-92\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":141,\"uuid\":\"efdfff56-ad51-4dd9-8b40-ac164ab00a99\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"解深密經疏 (ZZ369) is a text originally composed in Chinese that has been translated into Tibetan. On Wonch’uk’s life and works, see Powers 1992a.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":141}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"53459703-d98d-4a0e-b4fe-572848edca3d\",\"sort\":12419,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.10\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"$26\",\"label\":\"i.29\",\"sort\":1607,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"011356ac-2d68-40f8-8b24-0a3717f5c44c\",\"workUuid\":\"da0adcd3-4abf-406a-8021-b656a348fab8\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-049-001-100\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":101,\"uuid\":\"53459703-d98d-4a0e-b4fe-572848edca3d\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"I would like to warmly thank Zhuoran Xie (Vienna University) for her assistance in reading this text.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":101}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"5f0ec2e8-9633-4de1-adca-ca46946d317a\",\"sort\":12421,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.11\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"$27\",\"label\":\"i.29\",\"sort\":1607,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"011356ac-2d68-40f8-8b24-0a3717f5c44c\",\"workUuid\":\"da0adcd3-4abf-406a-8021-b656a348fab8\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-049-001-100\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":42,\"uuid\":\"5f0ec2e8-9633-4de1-adca-ca46946d317a\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"See also Katō 2011 for textual variations.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":42}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"d787562e-67c7-4869-9aa8-5165aa266db6\",\"sort\":12423,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.12\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"$28\",\"label\":\"i.29\",\"sort\":1607,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"011356ac-2d68-40f8-8b24-0a3717f5c44c\",\"workUuid\":\"da0adcd3-4abf-406a-8021-b656a348fab8\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-049-001-100\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":32,\"uuid\":\"d787562e-67c7-4869-9aa8-5165aa266db6\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"See Schmithausen 2014, p. 425ff.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":32}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"4c2ecce6-13bd-4a93-8c06-b3742cd3b7a3\",\"sort\":12425,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.13\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"$29\",\"label\":\"i.30\",\"sort\":1634,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"ddd03bb4-68be-427b-a2ea-d25d5d74a5c9\",\"workUuid\":\"da0adcd3-4abf-406a-8021-b656a348fab8\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-049-001-104\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":166,\"uuid\":\"4c2ecce6-13bd-4a93-8c06-b3742cd3b7a3\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"See Schmithausen 2014, pp. 419–20, n. 1852. On necessary adjustments to Lamotte’s rendition of the original Sanskrit terms, see Hakayama 1984, p. 180 and Delhey 2013.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":166}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"f28ad666-e1bd-4d3a-9104-f89ab7496941\",\"sort\":12427,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.14\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"$2a\",\"label\":\"i.30\",\"sort\":1634,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"ddd03bb4-68be-427b-a2ea-d25d5d74a5c9\",\"workUuid\":\"da0adcd3-4abf-406a-8021-b656a348fab8\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-049-001-104\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":177,\"uuid\":\"f28ad666-e1bd-4d3a-9104-f89ab7496941\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"See Tillemans 1997 for a review of Powers 1995. From a general perspective, it seems that Powers chose to ignore the work and methodological approach of Lamotte and Frauwallner.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":177}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"dddaaf62-52dd-4e7f-bc3b-e5bd3b633e6d\",\"sort\":12429,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.15\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"2. As mentioned above, Saṃdhi­nirmocana is also found in extenso in the Viniścaya­saṃ­grahaṇī of the Yogācāra­bhūmi and is therefore part of a tradition of texts sharing common ideas. This point should be kept in mind while translating, particularly when one has to evaluate the potential impact of terminological choices from the perspective of a more philosophical approach to the text, which, in the case of Saṃdhi­nirmocana, should be a major concern. For example, one should pay attention to the fact that interpreting “representation-only” (vijñaptimātra) as a strong form of idealism essentializing mind could be misleading from the perspective of a cultural translation of the worldview propounded in Saṃdhi­nirmocana since mind, just as much as the external object, is explicitly declared to be empty of any own-being, essence, or intrinsic nature (see chapter 8 on the three kinds of niḥsva­bhāvatā) in this text.\",\"label\":\"i.34\",\"sort\":1673,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"9e623e83-79d9-4269-bd12-c350f4c96a5a\",\"workUuid\":\"da0adcd3-4abf-406a-8021-b656a348fab8\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-049-001-110\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":201,\"uuid\":\"dddaaf62-52dd-4e7f-bc3b-e5bd3b633e6d\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"See Schmithausen 1987 and 2014, Delhey 2013, and Skilling 2013 on the simile of the illusionist (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":97}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"māyākāra\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":97,\"end\":105},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":97,\"end\":105,\"uuid\":\"f16d7fbe-738b-4220-8f74-fc2e960f5246\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"), which is also included \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":105,\"end\":131}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"inter alia\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":131,\"end\":141},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":131,\"end\":141,\"uuid\":\"c73c1b27-4e05-4983-96e3-652d02286d93\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"distinct\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" in the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":141,\"end\":149}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Māyājāla\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":149,\"end\":157},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"4e5f9d6d-3e9d-4a67-876d-17e54399b0d9\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", a \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":157,\"end\":161}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"sūtra\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":161,\"end\":166},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":161,\"end\":166,\"uuid\":\"92b958fc-0225-4314-b35e-6d85233cdb2b\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" also quoted in the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":166,\"end\":186}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Yogācāra­bhūmi\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":186,\"end\":200},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"27068f8b-54a5-4cd4-9f71-bc3aa7aa14fd\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\".\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":200,\"end\":201}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"8279c9d8-09d6-43d8-af20-a74391550fd5\",\"sort\":12441,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.16\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"2. As mentioned above, Saṃdhi­nirmocana is also found in extenso in the Viniścaya­saṃ­grahaṇī of the Yogācāra­bhūmi and is therefore part of a tradition of texts sharing common ideas. This point should be kept in mind while translating, particularly when one has to evaluate the potential impact of terminological choices from the perspective of a more philosophical approach to the text, which, in the case of Saṃdhi­nirmocana, should be a major concern. For example, one should pay attention to the fact that interpreting “representation-only” (vijñaptimātra) as a strong form of idealism essentializing mind could be misleading from the perspective of a cultural translation of the worldview propounded in Saṃdhi­nirmocana since mind, just as much as the external object, is explicitly declared to be empty of any own-being, essence, or intrinsic nature (see chapter 8 on the three kinds of niḥsva­bhāvatā) in this text.\",\"label\":\"i.34\",\"sort\":1673,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"9e623e83-79d9-4269-bd12-c350f4c96a5a\",\"workUuid\":\"da0adcd3-4abf-406a-8021-b656a348fab8\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-049-001-110\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":53,\"uuid\":\"8279c9d8-09d6-43d8-af20-a74391550fd5\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"On this issue, see Brunnhölzl 2018, pp. 414–18, n. 5.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":53}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"5cce3953-6e87-4749-80cf-cfa7a1fba899\",\"sort\":12443,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.17\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"3. Another important point is the presence of the aforementioned five commentaries on Saṃdhi­nirmocana found in the Tengyur (D). I occasionally referred to these works while finalizing the final draft of the translation. However, I first focused on the available editions of Saṃdhi­nirmocana itself as I did not want to be influenced by the interpretations of later authors. Instead, I attempted to go through all possible logically meaningful readings according to the Tibetan and Sanskrit sources without any preconceptions resulting from my reading of later commentarial traditions.\",\"label\":\"i.35\",\"sort\":1704,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"f725177d-0c33-45d0-9b63-80b626cf2c60\",\"workUuid\":\"da0adcd3-4abf-406a-8021-b656a348fab8\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-049-001-113\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":110,\"uuid\":\"5cce3953-6e87-4749-80cf-cfa7a1fba899\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"See Steinkellner 1989 and Powers 1992a, 1992b, and 1998. For a review of Powers 1998, refer to Wedemeyer 2003.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":110}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"d82aa9bc-f62f-4e92-addc-802edbed7752\",\"sort\":12445,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.18\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"4. In the same vein, one should note that Saṃdhi­nirmocana has played a major role in Tibetan hermeneutical debates. For centuries, it has been considered a central scripture referred to extensively in the writings of Tibet’s great luminaries, such as Jé Tsongkhapa (rje tsong kha pa, 1357–1419) or Jamgön Mipham Gyatso (’jam mgon mi pham rgya mtsho, 1846–1912). While it would certainly be fascinating to study the impact of Saṃdhi­nirmocana in the context of Tibetan Madhyamaka, I chose not to take into account Indian or Tibetan commentaries or exegeses of the sūtra in order to focus on the source text itself.\",\"label\":\"i.36\",\"sort\":1712,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"23f343be-f960-465b-a03f-b4c19b7c2dd0\",\"workUuid\":\"da0adcd3-4abf-406a-8021-b656a348fab8\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-049-001-115\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":46,\"uuid\":\"d82aa9bc-f62f-4e92-addc-802edbed7752\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"See for instance Hopkins 1999, 2002, and 2006.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":46}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"97d3940d-5b4a-43ef-a00b-eee1ec1f21a3\",\"sort\":12447,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.19\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"1. The translation of the title of the text became the object of several discussions among scholars regarding the meaning of the Sanskrit words saṃdhi and nirmocana as a consequence of Lamotte’s first complete translation of the text. Among the various available options, I opted for simplicity and translated the Sanskrit Saṃdhi­nirmocana­sūtra with “The Sūtra Unraveling the Intent,” which I believe renders accurately the meaning and structure of the text. Various interlocutors indeed ask the Buddha repeatedly to explain difficult points in order to clarify the purpose of his seemingly contradictory or complex doctrines on the nature of reality.\",\"label\":\"i.38\",\"sort\":1736,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"e960a63b-3657-4798-b6ff-6deaadfc1904\",\"workUuid\":\"da0adcd3-4abf-406a-8021-b656a348fab8\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-049-001-118\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":148,\"uuid\":\"97d3940d-5b4a-43ef-a00b-eee1ec1f21a3\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"See Lamotte 1935, p. 12ff., Ware 1937, Edgerton 1937, Edgerton 1953, p. 558, and later Keenan 1980, p. 126, Powers 1991a, and Powers 1993b, p. 28ff.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":148}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"0fc6b001-2f38-41c8-b9f0-f83ebb9d6554\",\"sort\":12449,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.20\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"2. Regarding the content of the sūtra itself, I proceeded to organize secondary sources by chapter and referenced this research in the notes accompanying my translation. The last chapter of Saṃdhi­nirmocana includes a very technical passage on valid cognition (pramāṇa) whose definitions predate Dignāga’s system of logic. Translating Trisong Detsen’s *Samyagvāk­pramāṇoddhṛta­sūtra, which is a commentary on the teaching on the four principles of reason (rigs pa bzhi), would help us better understand pre-Dignāgean Buddhist logic.\",\"label\":\"i.39\",\"sort\":1750,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"0cb0abe3-eec7-4b25-a13a-8d3c1d497969\",\"workUuid\":\"da0adcd3-4abf-406a-8021-b656a348fab8\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-049-001-120\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":903,\"uuid\":\"0fc6b001-2f38-41c8-b9f0-f83ebb9d6554\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Research relevant to terminological choices, syntactic reading of complex passages, and interpretation of the meaning includes Powers 1991b, 1991c, 1993b, pp. 41–77 (chapters 1 to 4); Tillemans 1997 (chapter 1); Matsuda 2013 on Sanskrit terms (chapter 2); Wayman 1974, Tillemans 1997, Mathes 2007, Matsuda 2013 (chapter 3); Katō 2002, Lusthaus 2002, Waldron 2003, Buescher 2007, 2008, Muller 2011, Schmithausen 1987 and 2014, Brunnhölzl 2018 (chapter 5); Frauwallner 1969, Takahashi 2006, Schmithausen 2014 (chapter 6); Frauwallner 1969, Tucci 1971, Tillemans 1997, Mathes 2007, Schmithausen 2014, Brunnhölzl 2018 (chapter 7); Takasaki 1966, Lamotte 1970, Lin 2010, Matsuda 2013, Schmithausen 1984, 1987, 2005, and 2014 (chapter 8); Obermiller 1933, Matsuda 1995 (chapter 9); Braarvig 1985, Kapstein 1988, Steinkellner 1989, Sakuma 1990, Yoshimizu 1996, Xing 2005, Lin 2010, Yoshimizu 2010 (chapter 10).\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":903}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"1d8a8abb-6d13-4a9a-b134-d70e1168def2\",\"sort\":12451,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.21\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"2. Regarding the content of the sūtra itself, I proceeded to organize secondary sources by chapter and referenced this research in the notes accompanying my translation. The last chapter of Saṃdhi­nirmocana includes a very technical passage on valid cognition (pramāṇa) whose definitions predate Dignāga’s system of logic. Translating Trisong Detsen’s *Samyagvāk­pramāṇoddhṛta­sūtra, which is a commentary on the teaching on the four principles of reason (rigs pa bzhi), would help us better understand pre-Dignāgean Buddhist logic.\",\"label\":\"i.39\",\"sort\":1750,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"0cb0abe3-eec7-4b25-a13a-8d3c1d497969\",\"workUuid\":\"da0adcd3-4abf-406a-8021-b656a348fab8\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-049-001-120\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":64,\"uuid\":\"1d8a8abb-6d13-4a9a-b134-d70e1168def2\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"For a detailed introduction to this text, see Steinkellner 1989.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":64}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"ef23f519-a216-44d7-81be-ae28c8875753\",\"sort\":12453,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.22\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"In this stage of the overall process, I followed Jean-François Billeter’s pragmatic approach to the translation of classical Chinese texts. This approach consists in five operations:\",\"label\":\"i.40\",\"sort\":1768,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"fa9932a4-f575-44b8-bd1a-0f1affe54ec4\",\"workUuid\":\"da0adcd3-4abf-406a-8021-b656a348fab8\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-049-001-123\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":135,\"uuid\":\"ef23f519-a216-44d7-81be-ae28c8875753\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"See Billeter 2014. I would like to thank Professor Tom Tillemans for having drawn my attention to Billeter’s principles of translation.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":135}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"f1ff6d47-61fb-475c-85ba-6ce8ebb7cac7\",\"sort\":12455,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.23\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"$2b\",\"label\":\"i.42\",\"sort\":1781,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"c8fd513b-08cb-4c6f-adc9-7d989c34979f\",\"workUuid\":\"da0adcd3-4abf-406a-8021-b656a348fab8\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-049-001-126\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":26,\"uuid\":\"f1ff6d47-61fb-475c-85ba-6ce8ebb7cac7\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"See Edgerton 1953, p. 102.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":26}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"22cbb211-7192-4c7b-bb28-109c35198347\",\"sort\":12457,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.24\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"$2c\",\"label\":\"i.42\",\"sort\":1781,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"c8fd513b-08cb-4c6f-adc9-7d989c34979f\",\"workUuid\":\"da0adcd3-4abf-406a-8021-b656a348fab8\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-049-001-126\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":39,\"uuid\":\"22cbb211-7192-4c7b-bb28-109c35198347\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"See Schmithausen 2014, p. 400, n. 1770.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":39}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"61a2d6ad-c032-4745-806d-48e793d9a0dd\",\"sort\":12459,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.25\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"$2d\",\"label\":\"i.42\",\"sort\":1781,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"c8fd513b-08cb-4c6f-adc9-7d989c34979f\",\"workUuid\":\"da0adcd3-4abf-406a-8021-b656a348fab8\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-049-001-126\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":25,\"uuid\":\"61a2d6ad-c032-4745-806d-48e793d9a0dd\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"See Lamotte 1935, p. 174.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":25}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"1fe93eec-26a1-4b55-8462-7433a631dce4\",\"sort\":12461,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.26\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"$2e\",\"label\":\"i.45\",\"sort\":1862,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"bb40c489-bc5f-4356-8831-6941b51d84dd\",\"workUuid\":\"da0adcd3-4abf-406a-8021-b656a348fab8\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-049-001-132\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":15,\"uuid\":\"1fe93eec-26a1-4b55-8462-7433a631dce4\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"See Mvyut 4414.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":15}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"c1f1c71b-a6ba-450e-8824-2188ea0d5a55\",\"sort\":12463,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.27\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"$2f\",\"label\":\"i.48\",\"sort\":1892,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"07a14bf2-0f95-4723-92bf-83e78050375b\",\"workUuid\":\"da0adcd3-4abf-406a-8021-b656a348fab8\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-049-001-136\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":29,\"uuid\":\"c1f1c71b-a6ba-450e-8824-2188ea0d5a55\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"See Vinay and Darbelnet 1958.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":29}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"ed092c38-e25b-4fba-afd2-b8b00c11b8dc\",\"sort\":12465,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.28\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"$30\",\"label\":\"i.50\",\"sort\":1919,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"132622f7-08ea-4111-8c4a-16151ff55853\",\"workUuid\":\"da0adcd3-4abf-406a-8021-b656a348fab8\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-049-001-142\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":46,\"uuid\":\"ed092c38-e25b-4fba-afd2-b8b00c11b8dc\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Or even “Yep,” “I’m with you,” “So true,” etc.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":46}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"7db3114d-503f-4db6-bad3-9e574c7cb920\",\"sort\":12467,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.29\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"In the context of Saṃdhi­nirmocana, the problem is compounded by the fact that the sūtra can be read as a collection of independent texts that would have been put together during the third or fourth century ᴄᴇ. The academic community considers the sūtra as a highly composite compilation lacking coherence from a philological perspective. Lamotte explains that the first four chapters represent a Prajñāpāramitā for the reasons mentioned above. He sees chapters 5 through 7 as forming a second group of ideas found in the Prajñāpāramitā literature that influenced the Yogācāra school. Finally, he considers chapters 8 through 10 to be later additions.\",\"label\":\"i.52\",\"sort\":1981,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"9b1bf835-a5ff-4647-8992-ea772f39b178\",\"workUuid\":\"da0adcd3-4abf-406a-8021-b656a348fab8\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-049-001-152\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":251,\"uuid\":\"7db3114d-503f-4db6-bad3-9e574c7cb920\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"“Une compilation assez maladroite”; see Lamotte 1935, p. 17. For an extensive discussion on the date and composition of Saṃdh., see Lamotte, pp. 14–25. See also Schmithausen 2014, p. 354ff. regarding the relation between the various chapters of Saṃdh.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":251}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"fec8e261-2d49-4afc-b0e9-f568c0aa2192\",\"sort\":12469,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.30\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"$31\",\"label\":\"i.54\",\"sort\":2015,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"97b7993a-5109-400d-9f75-2c0a1d159ce1\",\"workUuid\":\"da0adcd3-4abf-406a-8021-b656a348fab8\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-049-001-155\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":34,\"uuid\":\"fec8e261-2d49-4afc-b0e9-f568c0aa2192\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"See Schmithausen 2014, pp. 354–55.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":34}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"6ca1a6bb-b793-45ef-a1da-bf0db81d30d0\",\"sort\":12471,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.31\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"$32\",\"label\":\"i.55\",\"sort\":2029,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"48d849cf-0340-4703-b1b7-7b0ed20642ca\",\"workUuid\":\"da0adcd3-4abf-406a-8021-b656a348fab8\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-049-001-157\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":30,\"uuid\":\"6ca1a6bb-b793-45ef-a1da-bf0db81d30d0\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"See Schmithausen 2014, p. 365.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":30}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"4c8df7ab-612f-40f2-b78e-0bee9ea1d70e\",\"sort\":12473,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.32\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"$33\",\"label\":\"i.55\",\"sort\":2029,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"48d849cf-0340-4703-b1b7-7b0ed20642ca\",\"workUuid\":\"da0adcd3-4abf-406a-8021-b656a348fab8\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-049-001-157\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":30,\"uuid\":\"4c8df7ab-612f-40f2-b78e-0bee9ea1d70e\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"See Schmithausen 2014, p. 359.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":30}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"6c215b77-5bbe-402b-bab8-8bc482239db8\",\"sort\":12475,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.33\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"$34\",\"label\":\"i.58\",\"sort\":2159,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"uuid\":\"fb0e23b8-0657-45bd-86d1-9b8b45a2d814\",\"workUuid\":\"da0adcd3-4abf-406a-8021-b656a348fab8\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-049-001-162\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":70,\"uuid\":\"6c215b77-5bbe-402b-bab8-8bc482239db8\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"On the usage and various shades of meaning of \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":46}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"vijñapti\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":46,\"end\":54},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":46,\"end\":54,\"uuid\":\"8cc6c86e-fca1-41a8-8df0-3595f3655cd0\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", see Hall 1986.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":54,\"end\":70}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"0e767ac6-fc81-44ef-b8b7-03fee591e802\",\"sort\":12479,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.34\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"$35\",\"label\":\"p.1\",\"sort\":2232,\"type\":\"prologue\",\"uuid\":\"fba6f058-6392-4540-bb34-ce6f6077481b\",\"workUuid\":\"da0adcd3-4abf-406a-8021-b656a348fab8\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-049-001-168\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":158,\"uuid\":\"0e767ac6-fc81-44ef-b8b7-03fee591e802\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"rin po che sna bdun\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":19},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":19,\"uuid\":\"f26ca485-be04-447a-95dd-6684dafc6edb\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" does not refer to jewels only, as found in Lamotte (1935) and Keenan (2000). I follow here Powers (1995), Cornu (2005), and Cleary (1999).\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":19,\"end\":158}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"8719cfbd-072b-4d01-85c7-bdfd043a6db2\",\"sort\":12482,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.35\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"$36\",\"label\":\"p.1\",\"sort\":2232,\"type\":\"prologue\",\"uuid\":\"fba6f058-6392-4540-bb34-ce6f6077481b\",\"workUuid\":\"da0adcd3-4abf-406a-8021-b656a348fab8\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-049-001-168\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":239,\"uuid\":\"8719cfbd-072b-4d01-85c7-bdfd043a6db2\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"The logical subject of \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":23}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"’jig rten gyi khams dpag tu med pa rgyas par\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":23,\"end\":67},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":23,\"end\":67,\"uuid\":\"8882130f-6689-4307-a507-8d88251f7e5b\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"’\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":67,\"end\":68}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"gengs pa’i\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":68,\"end\":78},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":68,\"end\":78,\"uuid\":\"724c55b6-7619-4c63-9498-d4caf39bd48e\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"’\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":78,\"end\":79}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"od zer chen po shin tu mnga\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":79,\"end\":106},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":79,\"end\":106,\"uuid\":\"9a7e9720-9767-4d3c-ae28-df4f07020338\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"’\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":106,\"end\":107}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" ba\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":107,\"end\":110},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":107,\"end\":110,\"uuid\":\"cc729c68-25e8-4582-8418-2887f5b46e87\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" is the palace (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":110,\"end\":126}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"khang\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":126,\"end\":131},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":126,\"end\":131,\"uuid\":\"d7aa6daa-0881-40b7-b713-23462d63ce31\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"). Cornu (2005) and Keenan (2000) seem to read this phrase as a qualifier for the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":131,\"end\":213}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"seven precious substances\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":213,\"end\":238},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"c2db67b6-42db-4c9c-afbc-ad237b9e450d\",\"uuid\":\"214c20d3-d6a7-4047-a46b-6a347a37f126\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\".\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":238,\"end\":239}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"5cf70914-20a3-4e87-ab4a-a70c29fe4720\",\"sort\":12496,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.36\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"$37\",\"label\":\"p.1\",\"sort\":2232,\"type\":\"prologue\",\"uuid\":\"fba6f058-6392-4540-bb34-ce6f6077481b\",\"workUuid\":\"da0adcd3-4abf-406a-8021-b656a348fab8\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-049-001-168\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":1129,\"uuid\":\"5cf70914-20a3-4e87-ab4a-a70c29fe4720\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"The first paragraph of the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":27}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"nidāna\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":27,\"end\":33},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"72f80123-e9e7-421f-a43f-59ce107c9879\",\"uuid\":\"5bdc3536-83b0-419b-88a6-9a2329abb5d7\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" is a presentation of the place where the Buddha is dwelling. As already mentioned in the introduction, a succession of compounds, mainly \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":33,\"end\":171}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"bahuvrīhis\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":171,\"end\":181},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"2283dbd7-1426-4735-a42e-fa3085c70c20\",\"uuid\":\"f385241d-ee69-4803-a2ec-1bd8bd5360f3\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", enables the topicalization of the temple (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":181,\"end\":225}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"khang\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":225,\"end\":230},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":225,\"end\":230,\"uuid\":\"b10421c0-c77b-4f84-87aa-c0f71343097c\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"). Lamotte’s translation reflects this literary device, contrary to Powers who does not topicalize the palace to the same degree on account of some ambiguities regarding the logical subject of a few clauses describing this palace. To illustrate this point, it seems unclear whether the adjectives “steadfast,” “enduring,” or “free” in Powers’ translation qualify the temple or the beings attending it. Cornu mainly follows Powers here but the grammatical necessity to indicate the gender and number of qualifiers in French limits the risk of confusion, which is obviously not the case in English. Regarding the usage of tenses, Lamotte is the only translator who uses both narrative past and present in this first paragraph. He thus switches from the past tense to the present tense in order to describe the characteristics of the temple, a decision I chose not to follow in the present translation.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":230,\"end\":1129}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"fefbbc8b-7e97-40c2-bcdf-d12f0057b1c6\",\"sort\":12508,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.37\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"$38\",\"label\":\"p.1\",\"sort\":2232,\"type\":\"prologue\",\"uuid\":\"fba6f058-6392-4540-bb34-ce6f6077481b\",\"workUuid\":\"da0adcd3-4abf-406a-8021-b656a348fab8\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-049-001-168\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":602,\"uuid\":\"fefbbc8b-7e97-40c2-bcdf-d12f0057b1c6\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Lamotte, Cornu, and Powers do not translate the anaphoric pronoun \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":66}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"de\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":66,\"end\":68},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":66,\"end\":68,\"uuid\":\"596d7cd3-73fe-4eba-9541-8d163d6694fb\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" in ’\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":68,\"end\":73}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"jig rten las\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":73,\"end\":85},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":73,\"end\":85,\"uuid\":\"cf814516-e97e-4a3f-b4f5-49ea8d1ff902\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"’\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":85,\"end\":86}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"das pa de\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":86,\"end\":95},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":86,\"end\":95,\"uuid\":\"5cd99e15-cba5-42bc-88c5-27cb476cbc32\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"’\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":95,\"end\":96}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"i bla ma\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":96,\"end\":104},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":96,\"end\":104,\"uuid\":\"40fc33cf-a7d3-4e60-a94c-9d87ef1d7d10\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"’\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":104,\"end\":105}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"i dge ba\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":105,\"end\":113},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":105,\"end\":113,\"uuid\":\"9a61c5bc-740f-4f40-811c-2eede401a5f7\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"’\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":113,\"end\":114}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"i rtsa ba las byung ba\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":114,\"end\":136},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":114,\"end\":136,\"uuid\":\"04bb644d-4629-41ab-8dd3-08a717c727c1\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". Powers explains in a footnote (see Power 1995, p. 313, n. 3) that this pronoun refers to gnosis according to Wonch’uk, although his translation does not reflect this interpretation. Since wisdom has not been mentioned earlier in the text and since the pronoun \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":136,\"end\":398}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"de\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":398,\"end\":400},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":398,\"end\":400,\"uuid\":\"36eb1120-3285-4ec7-a650-ef137c9c654f\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" is anaphoric, I read \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":400,\"end\":422}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"de\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":422,\"end\":424},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":422,\"end\":424,\"uuid\":\"c02a5047-bb70-4c50-9ebe-acd0bcb321a3\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" as referring to the Buddha. Moreover, the concept of “root of virtue” is usually associated with persons and we have a reference to \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":424,\"end\":557}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"dbang sgyur ba\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":557,\"end\":571},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":557,\"end\":571,\"uuid\":\"ee81c8eb-5427-4b74-bf59-0d74c3d52c3e\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" in the next qualifying phrase.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":571,\"end\":602}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"95d0cc0f-7171-414f-b1b1-c9abc62c1a5f\",\"sort\":12532,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.38\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"$39\",\"label\":\"p.1\",\"sort\":2232,\"type\":\"prologue\",\"uuid\":\"fba6f058-6392-4540-bb34-ce6f6077481b\",\"workUuid\":\"da0adcd3-4abf-406a-8021-b656a348fab8\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-049-001-168\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":929,\"uuid\":\"95d0cc0f-7171-414f-b1b1-c9abc62c1a5f\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"The clause \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":11}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"dbang sgyur ba’i rnam par rig pa shin tu rnam par rig pa’i mtshan nyid\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":11,\"end\":81},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":11,\"end\":81,\"uuid\":\"dafc0cf7-fd30-422b-a1ec-8d7b556a0b44\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" is problematic. Lamotte translates it in the following way: “très pur, il se caractérise par une pensée maîtresse de soi.” Cornu and Powers follow the reading found in D, folio  2.a; S, folio 4.a; K\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":81,\"end\":280}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ǫ\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":280,\"end\":281},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"smallCaps\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":280,\"end\":281,\"uuid\":\"4a0e4ffa-c2e3-4bf1-9cae-07fd774397d0\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"small-caps\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", folio 1.a; L, folio 3.a; and H, folio 3.a ( \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":281,\"end\":327}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"dbang sgyur ba’i rnam par rig pa shin tu rnam par rig pa’i mtshan nyid\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":327,\"end\":397},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":327,\"end\":397,\"uuid\":\"13c01d17-4604-4998-98d0-5b513060d3e0\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\") and render the two occurrences of \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":397,\"end\":433}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"rnam par rig pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":433,\"end\":448},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":433,\"end\":448,\"uuid\":\"8857906f-c38a-460e-b225-105e395172ad\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" by an apposition: “It was characterized by perfect knowledge, the knowledge of one who has mastery.” (Powers 1995, p. 5). However, in F, folio 4.b we find a variant reading which, I believe, makes more sense: \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":448,\"end\":658}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"dbang byed pa’i rnam par rig pa shin tu rnam par dag pa’i mtshan nyid\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":658,\"end\":727},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":658,\"end\":727,\"uuid\":\"b80ea8ca-7c86-469e-9bf6-7d40c60ddf12\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". The Tibetan verbal prefix \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":727,\"end\":755}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"shin tu rnam par\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":755,\"end\":771},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":755,\"end\":771,\"uuid\":\"5d7b6a4b-87a6-4681-872d-a729a03341bf\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" is used to render the upasarga \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":771,\"end\":803}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"su\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":803,\"end\":805},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":803,\"end\":805,\"uuid\":\"b7455f15-bccf-4fcb-9ac5-ebeddeaafa29\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"- in Sanskrit, like in \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":805,\"end\":828}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"suviśuddha\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":828,\"end\":838},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":828,\"end\":838,\"uuid\":\"a942611a-0772-4917-9f2f-0cb39a04ed27\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". In Mvyut 351, \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":838,\"end\":854}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"blo shin tu rnam par dag pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":854,\"end\":881},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":854,\"end\":881,\"uuid\":\"85788cd1-9b5e-40d4-af37-b25b117358c7\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" thus translates the Sanskrit \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":881,\"end\":911}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"suviśuddhabuddhiḥ\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":911,\"end\":928},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":911,\"end\":928,\"uuid\":\"3b8d7250-e2f0-4927-8851-a699dc982715\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\".\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":928,\"end\":929}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"b0a38b5e-4332-4d52-b57f-e8f98455f1b3\",\"sort\":12556,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.39\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"$3a\",\"label\":\"p.1\",\"sort\":2232,\"type\":\"prologue\",\"uuid\":\"fba6f058-6392-4540-bb34-ce6f6077481b\",\"workUuid\":\"da0adcd3-4abf-406a-8021-b656a348fab8\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-049-001-168\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":539,\"uuid\":\"b0a38b5e-4332-4d52-b57f-e8f98455f1b3\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"nges par ’byung ba\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":18},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":18,\"uuid\":\"4f3a7b22-6262-446b-b93c-65399093cc3e\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". In Skt. \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":18,\"end\":28}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"niḥsaraṇa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":28,\"end\":37},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":28,\"end\":37,\"uuid\":\"c1d60990-0496-4d15-b11b-9c60915c0a90\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" or \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":37,\"end\":41}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"niryāṇa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":41,\"end\":48},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":41,\"end\":48,\"uuid\":\"0434588a-0537-46c3-bd1c-71cb99bd2fca\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", which have the meaning of setting forth, issue, exit, departure, escape, a road out of town. The analogy here is not about emancipation or renunciation as Powers and Cornu translated it but rather with the metaphor of the journey. In that sense, what is meant here is the departure to reach the palace. Lamotte (1935), Keenan (2000), and Cleary (1999) follow Xuanzang’s translation: 大念慧行以為游路 (Cbeta, Taishō 676). Interestingly enough, F does not have \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":48,\"end\":501}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"nges par ’byung ba\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":501,\"end\":519},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":501,\"end\":519,\"uuid\":\"6ba6bd43-b769-4500-8ed0-d27d64386df8\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" but just \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":519,\"end\":529}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"’byung ba\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":529,\"end\":538},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":529,\"end\":538,\"uuid\":\"0b280de2-ce74-4edd-8e78-33880a68c307\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\".\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":538,\"end\":539}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"7dfc0185-81f1-4009-bb13-508944659f1d\",\"sort\":12571,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.40\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"$3b\",\"label\":\"p.1\",\"sort\":2232,\"type\":\"prologue\",\"uuid\":\"fba6f058-6392-4540-bb34-ce6f6077481b\",\"workUuid\":\"da0adcd3-4abf-406a-8021-b656a348fab8\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-049-001-168\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":1220,\"uuid\":\"7dfc0185-81f1-4009-bb13-508944659f1d\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"rin po che’i pad ma’i rgyal po chen po yon tan gyi tshogs mtha’ yas pas brgyan pa’i bkod pa la rten pa na bzhugs te.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":116},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":116,\"uuid\":\"7e81679b-eb2d-4cbe-aa6e-48da68828968\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" This clause has been translated in various ways depending on how one understands the compound \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":116,\"end\":211}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"rin po che’i pad ma’i rgyal po chen po yon tan gyi tshogs mtha’ yas pas\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":211,\"end\":282},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":211,\"end\":282,\"uuid\":\"d735b740-a7ed-4dd8-8a68-046d4f69562e\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". Lamotte (1935), Powers (1995), and Cornu (2005) read it as a \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":282,\"end\":345}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"dvandva\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":345,\"end\":352},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"af32ecfa-1b74-4d47-a27a-d2ab3965f2ac\",\"uuid\":\"90356f98-69ad-41a6-858d-2411e42e2072\",\"toh\":null,\"start\":345,\"end\":0}},{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":345,\"end\":352,\"uuid\":\"c5642c56-289a-457d-8a6d-5d1e22332a60\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\": “II est orné de qualités infinies, de joyaux, de lotus et de grands rois” (Lamotte 1935, p. 167); “this pattern was adorned with boundless masses of excellent qualities, and with great kingly jeweled lotuses” (Powers 1995, pp. 5–6); “paré d’infinies qualités et de grands lotus royaux incrustés de pierreries” (Cornu 2005, p. 26). However, it seems to me that it would be better to read this compound as a \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":352,\"end\":760}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"karmadhāraya\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":760,\"end\":772},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"b0ac2880-07b9-42f3-b9af-99161d3032ab\",\"uuid\":\"0cd2a364-1c9d-4df6-9e88-caa26a566def\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". Folio 5.a offers a variant reading that could support this interpretation: \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":772,\"end\":849}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"yon ten gyi tshogs mtha’ yas pas/ brgyan pa’i rin po che chen po pad mo’i rgyal po’i bkod pa’i gnas na nyan thos kyi dge ’dun tshad med pa dang / thabs gcig tu bzhugs te\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":849,\"end\":1018},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":849,\"end\":1018,\"uuid\":\"3772d687-a3b0-46f6-a48e-28cb47a26024\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". In addition to this problem, one should note that Lamotte’s translation of the compound \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1018,\"end\":1108}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"rin po che’i pad ma\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1108,\"end\":1127},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1108,\"end\":1127,\"uuid\":\"3c0740b0-264f-4052-aa29-4742a30b1051\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"’\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1127,\"end\":1128}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"i rgyal po chen po\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1128,\"end\":1146},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1128,\"end\":1146,\"uuid\":\"42785994-b05d-4181-9ee7-e1f84f6d202c\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" as a \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1146,\"end\":1152}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"dvandva\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1152,\"end\":1159},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1152,\"end\":1159,\"uuid\":\"73db5332-fbf6-4e11-be78-f0f343001cb8\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"af32ecfa-1b74-4d47-a27a-d2ab3965f2ac\",\"uuid\":\"f9764ec6-0d6d-4b30-ae91-e1785991b78f\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" is inaccurate here. Powers’ reading of this term is correct.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1159,\"end\":1220}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"c2ef921a-f310-4187-b9af-5c51d5496220\",\"sort\":12588,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.41\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"$3c\",\"label\":\"p.2\",\"sort\":2304,\"type\":\"prologue\",\"uuid\":\"496ce909-bbb1-4e17-bae6-abc7b5da1256\",\"workUuid\":\"da0adcd3-4abf-406a-8021-b656a348fab8\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-049-001-179\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":97,\"uuid\":\"c2ef921a-f310-4187-b9af-5c51d5496220\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"chos\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":4},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":4,\"uuid\":\"247231c0-7bb2-4252-a7cd-87d57e13b3ee\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" in the sense of qualities as understood by Lamotte (1935), Powers (1995), and Cleary (1999).\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":4,\"end\":97}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"e4aa6f12-8e97-4da9-b7e7-2ec0ea839a76\",\"sort\":12591,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.42\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"$3d\",\"label\":\"p.2\",\"sort\":2304,\"type\":\"prologue\",\"uuid\":\"496ce909-bbb1-4e17-bae6-abc7b5da1256\",\"workUuid\":\"da0adcd3-4abf-406a-8021-b656a348fab8\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-049-001-179\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":364,\"uuid\":\"e4aa6f12-8e97-4da9-b7e7-2ec0ea839a76\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"spyod yul\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":9},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":9,\"uuid\":\"b2281c4a-0d0d-43bf-8137-a660f82731a7\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"; \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":9,\"end\":11}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"gocara\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":11,\"end\":17},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":11,\"end\":17,\"uuid\":\"ee7a48f4-ab8f-4d9a-bbc5-a137a5f92277\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". This term refers here to an object perceived by the six senses, so its semantic field pertains to perception as opposed to meditative practice, in which case it would be close in meaning to \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":17,\"end\":209}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ālambana\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":209,\"end\":217},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":209,\"end\":217,\"uuid\":\"fcf831e0-1f52-436c-b450-f83ac7b3050f\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"32d38a05-df64-4e0b-89c0-d67fbf88da5e\",\"uuid\":\"393f32df-2552-4be8-8360-12af6d4f470c\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" (“\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":217,\"end\":220}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"referential object\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":220,\"end\":238},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"32d38a05-df64-4e0b-89c0-d67fbf88da5e\",\"uuid\":\"417f4efa-4356-4334-ae58-8b1d6b2e7213\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"”). Translating all these terms with “object” would conflate these various semantic fields in the context of the present text.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":238,\"end\":364}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"c4c8bd87-d1f8-4016-8828-6cf42f544c31\",\"sort\":12604,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.43\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"$3e\",\"label\":\"p.2\",\"sort\":2304,\"type\":\"prologue\",\"uuid\":\"496ce909-bbb1-4e17-bae6-abc7b5da1256\",\"workUuid\":\"da0adcd3-4abf-406a-8021-b656a348fab8\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-049-001-179\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":330,\"uuid\":\"c4c8bd87-d1f8-4016-8828-6cf42f544c31\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"bsam gyis mi khyab pa rnam par ’jog pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":38},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":38,\"uuid\":\"495017d5-201a-4d0c-9214-4289de96b7c9\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" (cf. \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":38,\"end\":44}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"rnam par gzhag pa bsam gyis mi khyab pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":44,\"end\":83},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":44,\"end\":83,\"uuid\":\"7a34ec4e-4380-4ae9-97be-9d45bf98e565\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"; \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":83,\"end\":85}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"acintyavyavasthānaḥ\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":85,\"end\":104},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":85,\"end\":104,\"uuid\":\"32433117-288c-41f0-8dc6-6e8fde368dd7\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", see Mvyut 359). Compare with Lamotte: “ses attributs sont inconcevables” (Lamotte 1935, p. 168); Powers: “positing [doctrines] inconceivably” (Powers 1995, p. 7); Cornu: “il était entré dans l’indicible” (Cornu 2005, p. 26).\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":104,\"end\":330}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"05c54ddf-5975-4e9d-8589-d8585ecd39c6\",\"sort\":12611,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.44\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"$3f\",\"label\":\"p.2\",\"sort\":2304,\"type\":\"prologue\",\"uuid\":\"496ce909-bbb1-4e17-bae6-abc7b5da1256\",\"workUuid\":\"da0adcd3-4abf-406a-8021-b656a348fab8\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-049-001-179\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":169,\"uuid\":\"05c54ddf-5975-4e9d-8589-d8585ecd39c6\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"dus gsum mnyam pa nyid tshar phyin pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":37},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":37,\"uuid\":\"1c088588-f502-4449-8894-795658afa157\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"; \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":37,\"end\":39}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"tryadhvasamatāniryātaḥ\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":39,\"end\":61},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":39,\"end\":61,\"uuid\":\"5d2205aa-9914-4691-a098-a0bd517c3944\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" (Mvyut 360). The term \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":61,\"end\":84}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"niryāta\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":84,\"end\":91},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":84,\"end\":91,\"uuid\":\"b522a1c8-6484-499d-a444-1a184315e415\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" means here “adept, perfected, perfectly skilled” (see Edgerton 1953, p. 303).\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":91,\"end\":169}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"a3a0603c-8189-4410-b5f2-681b71797f2c\",\"sort\":12618,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.45\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"$40\",\"label\":\"p.2\",\"sort\":2304,\"type\":\"prologue\",\"uuid\":\"496ce909-bbb1-4e17-bae6-abc7b5da1256\",\"workUuid\":\"da0adcd3-4abf-406a-8021-b656a348fab8\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-049-001-179\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":279,\"uuid\":\"a3a0603c-8189-4410-b5f2-681b71797f2c\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"byang chub sems dpa’ thams cad kyis ye shes yang dag par blangs pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":66},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":66,\"uuid\":\"7e64758e-733d-41d5-9e5f-d9a25d080fe8\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". See Mvyut 366: \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":66,\"end\":83}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ye shes byang chub sems dpa’ thams cad kyis yang dag par mnos pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":83,\"end\":147},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":83,\"end\":147,\"uuid\":\"bd57c722-cab3-4f12-bf27-418d164562be\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"; \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":147,\"end\":149}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"sarvabodhisattvasampratīcchitajñānaḥ\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":149,\"end\":185},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":149,\"end\":185,\"uuid\":\"b961e128-7749-4949-a4a3-4e6eeba7c8ee\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". One should follow here the translations of Lamotte (1935), Keenan (2000), and Cleary (1999).\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":185,\"end\":279}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"f306ff9e-8dac-43dd-b524-88c083652764\",\"sort\":12625,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.46\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"$41\",\"label\":\"p.2\",\"sort\":2304,\"type\":\"prologue\",\"uuid\":\"496ce909-bbb1-4e17-bae6-abc7b5da1256\",\"workUuid\":\"da0adcd3-4abf-406a-8021-b656a348fab8\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-049-001-179\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":1047,\"uuid\":\"f306ff9e-8dac-43dd-b524-88c083652764\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"de bzhin gshegs pa ma ’dres pa’i rnam par thar par mdzad pa’i ye shes kyi mthar phyin pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":88},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":88,\"uuid\":\"cd9bb53d-cb78-43f2-92a6-9bc086896be8\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". See Mvyut 368: \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":88,\"end\":105}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"de bzhin gshegs pa ma ’dres pa’i rnam par thar pa’i mdzad pa’i ye shes kyi mthar phin pa/ de bzhin gshegs pa ma ’dres pa’i rnam par thar par mdzad pa’i ye shes kyi mthar phin pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":105,\"end\":282},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":105,\"end\":282,\"uuid\":\"cdac5969-01d0-40b1-8613-751ac423dcfa\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"; \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":282,\"end\":284}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"asaṃbhinnatathāgata-vimokṣajñānaniṣṭhāgataḥ\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":284,\"end\":327},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":284,\"end\":327,\"uuid\":\"0a4f26b7-18b7-41dc-bd9f-467e5fb9c48f\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". See also Mvyut 5192: \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":327,\"end\":350}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"dbyer med pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":350,\"end\":362},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":350,\"end\":362,\"uuid\":\"ef6ed65f-a712-4227-a0da-94819618109b\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"; \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":362,\"end\":364}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ma ’dres pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":364,\"end\":375},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":364,\"end\":375,\"uuid\":\"ef48c60c-271a-40ca-a9ed-2b7055f41b43\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"; \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":375,\"end\":377}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ma ’dres pa’m dbyer med pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":377,\"end\":403},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":377,\"end\":403,\"uuid\":\"e35abe0c-43ee-4bab-9ace-29dbc75b1b4a\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"; \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":403,\"end\":405}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"asaṃbhedaḥ\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":405,\"end\":415},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":405,\"end\":415,\"uuid\":\"67aa8902-208a-454a-9037-ddfb28b04c4b\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". If we understand \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":415,\"end\":434}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ma ’dres pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":434,\"end\":445},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":434,\"end\":445,\"uuid\":\"0bcc8300-ce0b-4c7b-afb6-6a2b1092fdc1\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" in the sense of \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":445,\"end\":462}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"dbyer med pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":462,\"end\":474},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":462,\"end\":474,\"uuid\":\"2293ddac-99e4-4d19-a62d-f68d366812e7\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", or even \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":474,\"end\":484}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"zung ’jug\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":484,\"end\":493},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":484,\"end\":493,\"uuid\":\"a136cfae-6e1b-49c8-b290-f1e5aa7af81c\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":493,\"end\":495}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"yuganaddha\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":495,\"end\":505},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":495,\"end\":505,\"uuid\":\"ee049168-8c42-44f4-ad91-e2bab089937b\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"), the meaning of the term is “indivisible/in unity,” conveying the notion of nonduality of the sameness mentioned several times in this introduction. Lamotte translates \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":505,\"end\":675}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ma ’dres pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":675,\"end\":686},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":675,\"end\":686,\"uuid\":\"84c8f58e-3b82-4f73-9d8e-d7de1faca118\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" with “non diversifié,” Cornu with “distinctement,” Powers with “uniquely,” Keenan with “unified.” I don’t think one should understand \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":686,\"end\":821}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ma ’dres pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":821,\"end\":832},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":821,\"end\":832,\"uuid\":\"3da37c45-783b-4b53-a4a7-bbdb3df5f322\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" with the meaning of \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":832,\"end\":853}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"kevala\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":853,\"end\":859},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":853,\"end\":859,\"uuid\":\"d3550417-94bb-4fd0-9884-3806565fb1ae\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" in the present case since it is associated with \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":859,\"end\":908}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ye shes\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":908,\"end\":915},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":908,\"end\":915,\"uuid\":\"1be61271-90ba-42f4-97d5-c42a7b1a6754\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" in other contexts where the idea of being exclusive to a particular person (e.g., buddhas) is negated (see Keenan 1980, p. 782ff.).\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":915,\"end\":1047}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"82d64bb2-cae2-4535-8799-be81cd600ab3\",\"sort\":12662,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.47\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"$42\",\"label\":\"p.2\",\"sort\":2304,\"type\":\"prologue\",\"uuid\":\"496ce909-bbb1-4e17-bae6-abc7b5da1256\",\"workUuid\":\"da0adcd3-4abf-406a-8021-b656a348fab8\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-049-001-179\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":238,\"uuid\":\"82d64bb2-cae2-4535-8799-be81cd600ab3\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"mtha’ dang dpung med pa’i sangs rgyas kyis mnyam pa nyid thugs su chud pa.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":74},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":74,\"uuid\":\"e35deb1c-90a4-4463-aa2c-0580eee65d7a\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" One should read here instead: \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":74,\"end\":105}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"mtha’ dang dbus med pa’i sangs rgyas kyi sa mnyam pa nyid bu thugs su chud pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":105,\"end\":182},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":105,\"end\":182,\"uuid\":\"c584001a-8758-40f3-bb3d-574cb853a907\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"; \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":182,\"end\":184}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"anantamadhyabuddhabhūmisamatādhigataḥ\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":184,\"end\":221},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":184,\"end\":221,\"uuid\":\"07ba9e00-e5b6-46a9-b185-6a1fa0a7925d\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" (see Mvyut 369).\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":221,\"end\":238}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"dd37e139-4f43-4d3d-bf9b-d4738116b252\",\"sort\":12669,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.48\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"$43\",\"label\":\"p.2\",\"sort\":2304,\"type\":\"prologue\",\"uuid\":\"496ce909-bbb1-4e17-bae6-abc7b5da1256\",\"workUuid\":\"da0adcd3-4abf-406a-8021-b656a348fab8\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-049-001-179\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":538,\"uuid\":\"dd37e139-4f43-4d3d-bf9b-d4738116b252\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"D, folio 2.b: \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":14}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"nam mkha’i khams kyi mthas gtugs pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":14,\"end\":49},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":14,\"end\":49,\"uuid\":\"f1951da9-461c-46dd-873a-9ae016b5ba57\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", which stands in apposition to \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":49,\"end\":81}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"chos kyi dbyings kyis klas pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":81,\"end\":110},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":81,\"end\":110,\"uuid\":\"91c6aa06-1cea-43ae-b298-bd2209daf29d\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" (“the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":110,\"end\":117}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ultimate within the domain of truth\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":117,\"end\":152},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"00431ab2-3f39-4944-b485-94bfdb8418ef\",\"uuid\":\"87f11e81-7d4d-4489-81a4-524b05d647cc\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"”). See Mvyut 6430: \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":152,\"end\":172}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"nam mkha’i dbyings kyi mtha’ gtugs pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":172,\"end\":209},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":172,\"end\":209,\"uuid\":\"60291c35-17e0-4289-85c1-3eee1bf011c0\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":209,\"end\":211}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"nam mkha’i khams kyi mthar gtugs\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":211,\"end\":243},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":211,\"end\":243,\"uuid\":\"3d2f61e1-bb94-482a-a583-eca7998bae9b\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" for the Sanskrit \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":243,\"end\":261}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ākāśadhātuparyavasānaḥ\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":261,\"end\":283},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":261,\"end\":283,\"uuid\":\"5b807e71-0652-45ac-8979-9168cb1f58fe\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". Compare with Mvyut 371: \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":283,\"end\":309}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"nam mkha’i khams kyi mtha’ klas pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":309,\"end\":343},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":309,\"end\":343,\"uuid\":\"c5ecf5e5-a23f-4fad-910c-e62ca94955af\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":343,\"end\":345}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"nam mkha’i khams kyi mthas klas pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":345,\"end\":379},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":345,\"end\":379,\"uuid\":\"0a230a56-54c5-4983-992b-1095f5d29a06\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" as Tibetan equivalents of \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":379,\"end\":406}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ākāśadhātuparyavasānaḥ\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":406,\"end\":428},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":406,\"end\":428,\"uuid\":\"9c870259-d693-4694-911a-2f6052d102f6\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". In Mvyut 431, \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":428,\"end\":444}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"don gyi mthar gtugs pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":444,\"end\":466},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":444,\"end\":466,\"uuid\":\"bbfb6d21-c5a0-4db9-ba13-455f47c46859\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" and \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":466,\"end\":471}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"don gyi mthar thug pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":471,\"end\":492},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":471,\"end\":492,\"uuid\":\"d8bc888d-41fe-4786-bcd5-bd8d08b67ca8\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" are Tibetan translations of \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":492,\"end\":521}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"paryavasitārthaḥ\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":521,\"end\":537},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":521,\"end\":537,\"uuid\":\"ca8fa1b3-9340-410d-8b28-c016df622969\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\".\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":537,\"end\":538}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"5400f3f4-91e8-4f2e-8cf9-6eb33faeb89f\",\"sort\":12695,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.49\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"The Blessed One was accompanied by the entire immeasurable assembly of hearers. Children of noble family, they were the heirs of the Buddha. Their minds were liberated, their wisdom was emancipated, and their discipline was completely pure. They happily gathered with those who longed for the Dharma. They had heard much, kept in mind what they had heard, and accumulated [merit from] what they had heard. They excelled in thought, speech, and deeds. Their wisdom was swift, quick, sharp, emancipating, discerning, vast, extensive, profound, and unequaled. They possessed the jewel of wisdom and the three forms of knowledge. They had attained the supreme state of happiness in this life. The purity of their merit, the excellence of their peaceful conduct, their patience, and their gentleness were vast. They were fully engaged in the teaching of the Tathāgata.\",\"label\":\"p.3\",\"sort\":2347,\"type\":\"prologue\",\"uuid\":\"06cc5e23-228e-48b5-9f27-eff6955db577\",\"workUuid\":\"da0adcd3-4abf-406a-8021-b656a348fab8\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-049-001-188\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":97,\"uuid\":\"5400f3f4-91e8-4f2e-8cf9-6eb33faeb89f\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"nges par ’byung ba\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":18},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":18,\"uuid\":\"05ca6273-9656-4f02-b922-985e9d5d1dfe\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"; \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":18,\"end\":20}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"niryāṇika\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":20,\"end\":29},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":20,\"end\":29,\"uuid\":\"4b39e15c-8044-42a7-a60b-41bd89e85f79\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" (?). Powers (1995) and Cornu (2005) translate it as “renunciation.”\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":29,\"end\":97}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"1681dd20-91a7-4f51-8269-63d86d980afc\",\"sort\":12700,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.50\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"The Blessed One was accompanied by the entire immeasurable assembly of hearers. Children of noble family, they were the heirs of the Buddha. Their minds were liberated, their wisdom was emancipated, and their discipline was completely pure. They happily gathered with those who longed for the Dharma. They had heard much, kept in mind what they had heard, and accumulated [merit from] what they had heard. They excelled in thought, speech, and deeds. Their wisdom was swift, quick, sharp, emancipating, discerning, vast, extensive, profound, and unequaled. They possessed the jewel of wisdom and the three forms of knowledge. They had attained the supreme state of happiness in this life. The purity of their merit, the excellence of their peaceful conduct, their patience, and their gentleness were vast. They were fully engaged in the teaching of the Tathāgata.\",\"label\":\"p.3\",\"sort\":2347,\"type\":\"prologue\",\"uuid\":\"06cc5e23-228e-48b5-9f27-eff6955db577\",\"workUuid\":\"da0adcd3-4abf-406a-8021-b656a348fab8\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-049-001-188\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":231,\"uuid\":\"1681dd20-91a7-4f51-8269-63d86d980afc\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"See Mvyut 7450: \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":16}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"nges par rtog pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":16,\"end\":32},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":16,\"end\":32,\"uuid\":\"067f36e1-f83e-4a5e-9bd9-8edc32d498f4\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"/\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":32,\"end\":33}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"nges par rtogs pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":33,\"end\":50},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":33,\"end\":50,\"uuid\":\"590694a7-eb61-4a87-b208-345e6ab378e1\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"; \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":50,\"end\":52}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"nirūpaṇā\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":52,\"end\":60},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":52,\"end\":60,\"uuid\":\"1fe39155-f699-42a6-a633-1661f7222b38\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". Translated by Lamotte with “pénétrante” and by Keenan with “penetrating,” while Powers and Cornu opted respectively for “certain realization” and “réalisation certaine.”\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":60,\"end\":231}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"f0998559-33b7-42d9-a749-4db5fb2688ea\",\"sort\":12708,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.51\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"The Blessed One was accompanied by the entire immeasurable assembly of hearers. Children of noble family, they were the heirs of the Buddha. Their minds were liberated, their wisdom was emancipated, and their discipline was completely pure. They happily gathered with those who longed for the Dharma. They had heard much, kept in mind what they had heard, and accumulated [merit from] what they had heard. They excelled in thought, speech, and deeds. Their wisdom was swift, quick, sharp, emancipating, discerning, vast, extensive, profound, and unequaled. They possessed the jewel of wisdom and the three forms of knowledge. They had attained the supreme state of happiness in this life. The purity of their merit, the excellence of their peaceful conduct, their patience, and their gentleness were vast. They were fully engaged in the teaching of the Tathāgata.\",\"label\":\"p.3\",\"sort\":2347,\"type\":\"prologue\",\"uuid\":\"06cc5e23-228e-48b5-9f27-eff6955db577\",\"workUuid\":\"da0adcd3-4abf-406a-8021-b656a348fab8\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-049-001-188\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":205,\"uuid\":\"f0998559-33b7-42d9-a749-4db5fb2688ea\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"See Mvyut 1113: \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":16}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"yon yongs su sbyong ba chen po\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":16,\"end\":46},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":16,\"end\":46,\"uuid\":\"ab5468da-4100-446b-ba96-bb6332135fec\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"; \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":46,\"end\":48}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"mahādakṣiṇāpariṣodhakaḥ\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":48,\"end\":71},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":48,\"end\":71,\"uuid\":\"00829047-49e3-442d-bdad-1985d366f4f1\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". D, 4,5; K\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":71,\"end\":82}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ǫ\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":82,\"end\":83},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"smallCaps\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":82,\"end\":83,\"uuid\":\"4f2ef783-05fa-4d96-90e6-ca096bac9f03\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"small-caps\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", folio 2.b; and H, 7,2 omit \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":83,\"end\":112}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"yon. \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":112,\"end\":117},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":112,\"end\":117,\"uuid\":\"5f84d7f5-df0c-482b-a4d7-127798c7e199\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" However, it is present in S, 7,2 and L, folio 5.a: \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":117,\"end\":169}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"yon tan\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":169,\"end\":176},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":169,\"end\":176,\"uuid\":\"61ac5ce6-8e89-4524-aefd-8e195b3a6e39\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", while F.5.b reads \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":176,\"end\":196}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"sbyin pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":196,\"end\":204},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":196,\"end\":204,\"uuid\":\"18cae0d8-555d-4da7-86ae-7a469bf9e906\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\".\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":204,\"end\":205}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"308ed6f0-37bf-4f91-b4b7-19f1cae05e08\",\"sort\":12722,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.52\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"The Blessed One was accompanied by the entire immeasurable assembly of hearers. Children of noble family, they were the heirs of the Buddha. Their minds were liberated, their wisdom was emancipated, and their discipline was completely pure. They happily gathered with those who longed for the Dharma. They had heard much, kept in mind what they had heard, and accumulated [merit from] what they had heard. They excelled in thought, speech, and deeds. Their wisdom was swift, quick, sharp, emancipating, discerning, vast, extensive, profound, and unequaled. They possessed the jewel of wisdom and the three forms of knowledge. They had attained the supreme state of happiness in this life. The purity of their merit, the excellence of their peaceful conduct, their patience, and their gentleness were vast. They were fully engaged in the teaching of the Tathāgata.\",\"label\":\"p.3\",\"sort\":2347,\"type\":\"prologue\",\"uuid\":\"06cc5e23-228e-48b5-9f27-eff6955db577\",\"workUuid\":\"da0adcd3-4abf-406a-8021-b656a348fab8\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-049-001-188\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":268,\"uuid\":\"308ed6f0-37bf-4f91-b4b7-19f1cae05e08\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Powers (1995) and Cornu (2005) read \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":36}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"nges pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":36,\"end\":43},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":36,\"end\":43,\"uuid\":\"b49e34d4-8586-4bad-8777-141524a4c966\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", but one should read here instead the graphically very similar \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":43,\"end\":107}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"des pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":107,\"end\":113},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":107,\"end\":113,\"uuid\":\"f49d092e-bfbc-49c8-b2ba-eff2a0626f09\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" (“gentleness”) as in Mvyut 1115 where this expression is also found extensively: \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":113,\"end\":195}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"bzod pa dang des pa chen po dang ldan pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":195,\"end\":235},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":195,\"end\":235,\"uuid\":\"986372e3-796b-4446-a1d5-ba566a30b3d7\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"; \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":235,\"end\":237}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"mahākṣāntisauratyasamanvāgataḥ\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":237,\"end\":267},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":237,\"end\":267,\"uuid\":\"2984ce2c-ec60-4f91-a2e1-0d104efccde5\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\".\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":267,\"end\":268}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"d7a42e54-6c1a-4354-be34-157a364e9aa1\",\"sort\":12732,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.53\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"At that time, the bodhisattva Vidhi­vatpari­pṛcchaka questioned the bodhisattva Gam­bhīrārtha­saṃdhi­nirmo­cana on the ultimate whose defining characteristic is inexpressible and nondual: “O son of the Victorious One, when it is said that all phenomena are nondual, what are these phenomena? In what way are they nondual?” Gam­bhīrārtha­saṃdhi­nirmo­cana replied, “Noble son, all phenomena, what we refer to as all phenomena, are of just two kinds: conditioned and unconditioned. With respect to these, the conditioned is neither conditioned nor unconditioned. The unconditioned is neither unconditioned nor conditioned.”\",\"label\":\"1.1\",\"sort\":2447,\"type\":\"translation\",\"uuid\":\"9737af74-7337-4ab2-a155-bac9d2739e7e\",\"workUuid\":\"da0adcd3-4abf-406a-8021-b656a348fab8\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-049-001-197\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":537,\"uuid\":\"d7a42e54-6c1a-4354-be34-157a364e9aa1\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"brjod du med pa dang / gnyis su med pa’i mtshan nyid\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":52},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":52,\"uuid\":\"0dfb3140-ee6d-4dbf-bf4c-375ec2900b10\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". I read this compound as a \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":52,\"end\":80}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"bahuvrīhi\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":80,\"end\":89},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"2283dbd7-1426-4735-a42e-fa3085c70c20\",\"uuid\":\"46fd962a-0f18-405b-a373-de290d674f28\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". The full clause [\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":89,\"end\":108}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"brjod du med pa dang / gnyis su med pa’i mtshan nyid\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":108,\"end\":160},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":108,\"end\":160,\"uuid\":\"7e6155dd-c35c-4ec1-8443-576ad1fa32b8\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"] + [\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":160,\"end\":165}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"don dam pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":165,\"end\":175},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":165,\"end\":175,\"uuid\":\"2477515d-1b95-4912-a11f-a0a55da39350\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"] is a \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":175,\"end\":182}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"karmadhāraya\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":182,\"end\":194},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"b0ac2880-07b9-42f3-b9af-99161d3032ab\",\"uuid\":\"20a60b5d-bb06-495a-9876-91b12d20aab5\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" meaning literally “the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":194,\"end\":218}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ultimate\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":218,\"end\":226},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"1ce42c0c-900f-47c2-9d40-98ccbafcb2bf\",\"uuid\":\"87f009d0-2d8f-4da7-8292-7ab75d1f9a3a\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" that is that whose defining characteristic is inexpressible and absolute.” Powers’ suggestion is also possible here (“the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":226,\"end\":349}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ultimate\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":349,\"end\":357},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"1ce42c0c-900f-47c2-9d40-98ccbafcb2bf\",\"uuid\":\"03ac2ca1-50af-4d5b-8cc6-f065814f6985\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" whose defining characteristic is inexpressible and non-dual”). Lamotte leaves out \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":357,\"end\":440}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"mtshan nyid\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":440,\"end\":451},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":440,\"end\":451,\"uuid\":\"dc370124-c423-4d42-9f64-16f255a52942\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". Cornu somewhat mixes qualifiers and qualified terms in his rendering of this clause.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":451,\"end\":537}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"e7d98285-c62a-4557-a2e5-8aa5a959d89c\",\"sort\":12757,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.54\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"$44\",\"label\":\"1.2\",\"sort\":2487,\"type\":\"translation\",\"uuid\":\"368491e9-5031-4cd8-bb10-086577164072\",\"workUuid\":\"da0adcd3-4abf-406a-8021-b656a348fab8\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-049-001-200\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":256,\"uuid\":\"e7d98285-c62a-4557-a2e5-8aa5a959d89c\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"yongs su ma grub pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":19},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":19,\"uuid\":\"997b15e5-2d78-4d12-a40d-cb59e431e44e\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"; \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":19,\"end\":21}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"apariniṣpanna\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":21,\"end\":34},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"e6e4b2ce-848f-42f6-adcd-559066db3843\",\"uuid\":\"bd7cfb9b-ec85-4c02-951c-b865d57c70bc\",\"toh\":null,\"start\":21,\"end\":0}},{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":21,\"end\":34,\"uuid\":\"960d5741-1349-453a-96a8-6145558f3b3a\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" (?). This paragraph establishes the opposition between the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":34,\"end\":94}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"imaginary\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":94,\"end\":103},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"edcb7462-a8a5-4667-9736-fa1dba77154b\",\"uuid\":\"8a4e4c55-bf3d-4ffa-987d-d9999d232620\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":103,\"end\":105}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"parikalpita\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":105,\"end\":116},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"edcb7462-a8a5-4667-9736-fa1dba77154b\",\"uuid\":\"e9f1deff-f4af-4f81-9e99-4493076f3485\",\"toh\":null,\"start\":105,\"end\":0}},{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":105,\"end\":116,\"uuid\":\"4575253a-4ea2-43f7-bfb9-b1b5b8754253\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\") and the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":116,\"end\":126}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"actual\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":126,\"end\":132},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"bf3c7cca-3030-4d6b-a560-9a324c4f01ee\",\"uuid\":\"2312f27e-8f68-41ac-91e3-2ad2ce5d7b00\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":132,\"end\":134}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"pariniṣpanna\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":134,\"end\":146},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"bf3c7cca-3030-4d6b-a560-9a324c4f01ee\",\"uuid\":\"a95bc035-45b7-4564-a8c3-805e81a97e8c\",\"toh\":null,\"start\":134,\"end\":0}},{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":134,\"end\":146,\"uuid\":\"e5054fcb-b050-4bb2-80dc-5f82685e17a6\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"). These two aspects are found in the teaching on the three kinds of \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":146,\"end\":215}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"essencelessness\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":215,\"end\":230},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"511f85e3-f5bd-4380-81c7-87048ba56676\",\"uuid\":\"45ee6a69-413e-49de-a4fe-ef06e612fd36\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\": see Saṃdh. chapters 6–8.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":230,\"end\":256}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"68e92180-ae26-451e-812a-de99cdce7ba8\",\"sort\":12772,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.55\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"$45\",\"label\":\"1.2\",\"sort\":2487,\"type\":\"translation\",\"uuid\":\"368491e9-5031-4cd8-bb10-086577164072\",\"workUuid\":\"da0adcd3-4abf-406a-8021-b656a348fab8\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-049-001-200\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":217,\"uuid\":\"68e92180-ae26-451e-812a-de99cdce7ba8\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"shes pa dang mthong ba\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":22},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":22,\"uuid\":\"d35aa944-ec27-41df-a975-f7ec70e54a52\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"; \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":22,\"end\":24}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"jñānadarśana\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":24,\"end\":36},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"c159df12-8fe9-498c-a07b-02104cd05a1f\",\"uuid\":\"c4c27ddb-b37e-4135-92a0-e0b2d3412495\",\"toh\":null,\"start\":24,\"end\":0}},{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":24,\"end\":36,\"uuid\":\"2bd820ae-4fe3-4efb-b413-eadcd75a7200\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". D, folio 3.b: \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":36,\"end\":52}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"shes pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":52,\"end\":59},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":52,\"end\":59,\"uuid\":\"bc7bdd51-adb3-4ae3-9d36-b68f5108d8b8\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" but F, folio 6.b; S, folio 5.a; VD, folio 44.b: \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":59,\"end\":108}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ye shes\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":108,\"end\":115},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":108,\"end\":115,\"uuid\":\"7d505029-bed6-48d5-a27a-d739254accb7\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". I emended the text in this way throughout the sūtra since this expression is repeated several times.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":115,\"end\":217}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"0ac80ec0-3400-480a-b1fd-ea0f5140adb6\",\"sort\":12781,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.56\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"$46\",\"label\":\"1.2\",\"sort\":2487,\"type\":\"translation\",\"uuid\":\"368491e9-5031-4cd8-bb10-086577164072\",\"workUuid\":\"da0adcd3-4abf-406a-8021-b656a348fab8\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-049-001-200\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":67,\"uuid\":\"0ac80ec0-3400-480a-b1fd-ea0f5140adb6\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Xuanzang’s translation reads 謂諸聖者以聖智聖見離名言故現等正覺 (Cbeta, Taishō 676).\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":67}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"509bb136-e74f-4e17-8303-82ca0dc8803c\",\"sort\":12785,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.57\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"$47\",\"label\":\"1.2\",\"sort\":2487,\"type\":\"translation\",\"uuid\":\"368491e9-5031-4cd8-bb10-086577164072\",\"workUuid\":\"da0adcd3-4abf-406a-8021-b656a348fab8\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-049-001-200\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":232,\"uuid\":\"509bb136-e74f-4e17-8303-82ca0dc8803c\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"As noted by Tillemans (1997), Powers reads \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":43}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"phyir\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":43,\"end\":48},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":43,\"end\":48,\"uuid\":\"1031692e-213a-492e-bc99-89603892f7da\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" in the sense of “because” here. Keenan and Cleary’s readings of Xuanzang’s translation (為慾令他現等覺故, Cbeta, Taishō 676) agree with Lamotte’s and Tillemans’ understanding of this passage.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":48,\"end\":232}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"c72cbdb3-701b-464d-b66f-106a8fedab9f\",\"sort\":12791,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.58\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"“Noble son, the term unconditioned is also a word, a label used by the Teacher. Words that are labels used by the Teacher are conventional expressions arising from imagination. These conventional expressions arising from imagination are always conventional expressions deprived of any actuality that arise from imagination in its diversity. Therefore, the term unconditioned is not the unconditioned. Noble son, the term conditioned is also included within conventions, just as expressions other than conditioned and unconditioned are and will [always] be. One might object that there is, however, no expression in the absence of the object [to which it refers]. What is then this object? It is the complete and perfect awakening to inexpressible [reality] through the sublime gnosis and vision of the noble ones. But in order to lead [others] to the perfect realization of this very inexpressible nature of phenomena, the Teacher labels this object with the term unconditioned.”\",\"label\":\"1.3\",\"sort\":2560,\"type\":\"translation\",\"uuid\":\"9b2a1fdb-bcd4-44c0-ab40-584a79dc2721\",\"workUuid\":\"da0adcd3-4abf-406a-8021-b656a348fab8\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-049-001-207\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":53,\"uuid\":\"c72cbdb3-701b-464d-b66f-106a8fedab9f\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ston pas btags pa’i tshig yin te\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":32},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":32,\"uuid\":\"9130cfb2-0f38-4266-82c9-562524cc03a3\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". VD, folio 44.b: om.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":32,\"end\":53}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"1c21868a-94f6-42f6-a394-432f741ed033\",\"sort\":12794,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.59\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"$48\",\"label\":\"1.4\",\"sort\":2610,\"type\":\"translation\",\"uuid\":\"0c9dbafb-4b01-4f77-a2a8-eda69c281356\",\"workUuid\":\"da0adcd3-4abf-406a-8021-b656a348fab8\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-049-001-209\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":136,\"uuid\":\"1c21868a-94f6-42f6-a394-432f741ed033\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"rnam grangs\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":11},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":11,\"uuid\":\"b12e6eeb-0443-47cf-aed0-b8df060856e8\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"; \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":11,\"end\":13}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"paryāya\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":13,\"end\":20},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":13,\"end\":20,\"uuid\":\"28e54f27-e4b6-4448-bd2e-2345cfbe396d\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". The Dunhuang manuscript of the sūtra instead has \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":20,\"end\":71}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"gzhung du ’du shes\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":71,\"end\":89},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":71,\"end\":89,\"uuid\":\"05bb49a9-ed30-4ffa-bab7-143a52bb0ce7\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" (n°194 folio 62.a; see Hakayama 1984, p. 187).\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":89,\"end\":136}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"62f2ac47-f1b9-4c98-b3b1-de7c4f050a95\",\"sort\":12801,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.60\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"$49\",\"label\":\"1.4\",\"sort\":2610,\"type\":\"translation\",\"uuid\":\"0c9dbafb-4b01-4f77-a2a8-eda69c281356\",\"workUuid\":\"da0adcd3-4abf-406a-8021-b656a348fab8\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-049-001-209\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":8,\"uuid\":\"62f2ac47-f1b9-4c98-b3b1-de7c4f050a95\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"See \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":4}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"1.5\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":4,\"end\":7},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"internalLink\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"d608dd24-15a5-400e-bafa-7039f000ab1f\",\"href\":\"/entity/passage/62bb7744-4d25-4c83-b8ce-7298ad70e34c\",\"entity\":\"62bb7744-4d25-4c83-b8ce-7298ad70e34c\",\"type\":\"passage\",\"toh\":null,\"isSameWork\":true,\"subtype\":\"translation\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\".\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":7,\"end\":8}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"0a08e35f-327f-4c8d-9f95-01da026834cb\",\"sort\":12805,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.61\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"$4a\",\"label\":\"1.4\",\"sort\":2610,\"type\":\"translation\",\"uuid\":\"0c9dbafb-4b01-4f77-a2a8-eda69c281356\",\"workUuid\":\"da0adcd3-4abf-406a-8021-b656a348fab8\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-049-001-209\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":100,\"uuid\":\"0a08e35f-327f-4c8d-9f95-01da026834cb\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"VD, folio 45.b reads the demonstrative pronoun as a plural (i.e., \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":66}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"de dag\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":66,\"end\":72},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":66,\"end\":72,\"uuid\":\"c8c33835-7419-4932-9b3e-60e0cbcebda5\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\") throughout this paragraph.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":72,\"end\":100}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"438c702e-8904-46bc-bfd3-190a2131ba3b\",\"sort\":12809,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.62\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"$4b\",\"label\":\"1.4\",\"sort\":2610,\"type\":\"translation\",\"uuid\":\"0c9dbafb-4b01-4f77-a2a8-eda69c281356\",\"workUuid\":\"da0adcd3-4abf-406a-8021-b656a348fab8\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-049-001-209\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":39,\"uuid\":\"438c702e-8904-46bc-bfd3-190a2131ba3b\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"’di ltar don\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":12},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":12,\"uuid\":\"56f6200b-5494-45c7-93ed-7cfb64fb95b1\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" in the sense of \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":12,\"end\":29}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"yathārtha\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":29,\"end\":38},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":29,\"end\":38,\"uuid\":\"3c5a2008-3f39-4f22-b52c-e9afba617a5f\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\".\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":38,\"end\":39}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"f2954b44-8f2a-45c1-a78a-b4480c52ae58\",\"sort\":12814,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.63\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"$4c\",\"label\":\"1.4\",\"sort\":2610,\"type\":\"translation\",\"uuid\":\"0c9dbafb-4b01-4f77-a2a8-eda69c281356\",\"workUuid\":\"da0adcd3-4abf-406a-8021-b656a348fab8\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-049-001-209\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":500,\"uuid\":\"f2954b44-8f2a-45c1-a78a-b4480c52ae58\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Powers’ and Cornu’s translations are inaccurate here: “Subsequently they do not make the conventional \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":102}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"designations\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":102,\"end\":114},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"40b7317d-88e6-4622-81f7-124865177c3a\",\"uuid\":\"e1d37a9b-32cc-4cd1-b1f3-a238d6613be0\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\": ‘This is true, the other is false.’ They make conventional \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":114,\"end\":175}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"designations\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":175,\"end\":187},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"40b7317d-88e6-4622-81f7-124865177c3a\",\"uuid\":\"214345a3-a93c-49f9-a021-a5186b4d7117\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" because they completely understand the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":187,\"end\":227}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"object\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":227,\"end\":233},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"cf9988ae-d23d-4a8e-a24a-2f5503ee7f00\",\"uuid\":\"5389f68b-394f-49ee-bdb5-4d2a88e9bef0\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" in this way.” (Powers 1995, p. 17). “Comme ils connaissent parfaitement le sens réel de ces phénomènes…” (Cornu 2005, p. 32). Lamotte seems to have translated 1.4 on the basis of the Chinese. In addition, \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":233,\"end\":439}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"rjes su\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":439,\"end\":446},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":439,\"end\":446,\"uuid\":\"0fa80b40-34d6-4f49-9283-3befa52ba7ca\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" should be read as \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":446,\"end\":465}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"rjes su tha snyad\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":465,\"end\":482},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":465,\"end\":482,\"uuid\":\"41818d4b-81df-44e2-ba5a-975477084e8c\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" for \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":482,\"end\":487}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"anuvyavahāra\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":487,\"end\":499},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":487,\"end\":499,\"uuid\":\"4aa35dbc-59e6-4e91-8b9c-2cbead36f827\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\".\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":499,\"end\":500}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"1b5eccf8-6311-4816-8458-2583d2d27a30\",\"sort\":12828,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.64\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"$4d\",\"label\":\"1.5\",\"sort\":2683,\"type\":\"translation\",\"uuid\":\"62bb7744-4d25-4c83-b8ce-7298ad70e34c\",\"workUuid\":\"da0adcd3-4abf-406a-8021-b656a348fab8\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-049-001-217\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":899,\"uuid\":\"1b5eccf8-6311-4816-8458-2583d2d27a30\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Lamotte’s rather free translation of 1.5 fails to render the opposition between what does not exist and what does according to the sūtra: \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":138}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"’di snyam du sems te/ ’dus byas dang / ’dus ma byas snang ba gang yin pa ’di ni med kyi/ gang la ’dus byas dang ’dus ma byas kyi ’du shes dang / ’dus byas dang / ’dus ma byas kyi rnam grangs kyi [F.5.a] ’du shes ’byung ba/ rnam par rtog pa las byung ba/ ’du byed kyi mtshan ma sgyu ma lta bu ’di ni yod/ blo rnam par rmongs par byed pa ’di ni yod do\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":138,\"end\":487},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":138,\"end\":487,\"uuid\":\"f4c0b5b3-e7e6-4b75-a363-06164eb56059\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". The first chapter gives an introduction to central concepts, such as \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":487,\"end\":558}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"conditioned\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":558,\"end\":569},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"c41c6d0c-b684-45c0-9367-3c0df3d7d01b\",\"uuid\":\"ed99bf43-a1ec-42be-a1b5-bc9b0752ae43\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"/\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":569,\"end\":570}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"unconditioned\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":570,\"end\":583},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"d680987b-fab1-4356-95cb-fce547654eec\",\"uuid\":\"89d62718-4a07-4c76-8301-f748988db9ed\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", existent/nonexistent, \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":583,\"end\":607}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"imaginary\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":607,\"end\":616},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"edcb7462-a8a5-4667-9736-fa1dba77154b\",\"uuid\":\"e45d8356-5203-4e6a-8b78-d6a9b5637fda\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"/\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":616,\"end\":617}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"actual\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":617,\"end\":623},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"bf3c7cca-3030-4d6b-a560-9a324c4f01ee\",\"uuid\":\"d7df628a-da92-438e-a367-fe248ed6afb9\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". It prefigures the treatment of the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":623,\"end\":660}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"two truths\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":660,\"end\":670},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"a0dea610-3170-45d1-8066-2121a1ad810f\",\"uuid\":\"1d01794f-6053-4cc8-9eb9-1e91b73c6cc0\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":670,\"end\":672}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"bden pa gnyis\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":672,\"end\":685},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":672,\"end\":685,\"uuid\":\"e6b159d5-90f5-41ed-b918-d5300ba6576d\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"; \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":685,\"end\":687}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"satyadvaya\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":687,\"end\":697},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":687,\"end\":697,\"uuid\":\"2a9a542c-9dd1-4400-8dbe-632b03f6469f\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\") in Saṃdh. chapter 3 as well as that of the three natures/\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":697,\"end\":756}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"essences\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":756,\"end\":764},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"47c8923c-56be-43d8-b398-ff4290cece41\",\"uuid\":\"5feb328e-03a9-4a59-af70-18f6cc1d7051\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" and three kinds of nonexistence of nature/\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":764,\"end\":807}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"essence\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":807,\"end\":814},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"47c8923c-56be-43d8-b398-ff4290cece41\",\"uuid\":\"cb172a7e-2710-40b6-a169-e057501d6ee4\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":814,\"end\":816}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ngo bo nyid (med pa) nyid\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":816,\"end\":841},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":816,\"end\":841,\"uuid\":\"b7bb7484-5f91-4234-a5f7-5bfbbb282173\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"; \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":841,\"end\":843}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"(niḥ)svabhāvatā\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":843,\"end\":858},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":843,\"end\":858,\"uuid\":\"3e348c6b-d751-4184-aefa-d9d4aeaad9b0\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\") expounded in Saṃdh. (cf. chapters 6–8).\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":858,\"end\":899}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"1086fd1f-40b0-4095-8e8f-d43919df9527\",\"sort\":12854,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.65\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"$4e\",\"label\":\"2.1\",\"sort\":2819,\"type\":\"translation\",\"uuid\":\"5ee1053b-7911-4600-b68b-664f3eb45a71\",\"workUuid\":\"da0adcd3-4abf-406a-8021-b656a348fab8\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-049-001-225\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":132,\"uuid\":\"1086fd1f-40b0-4095-8e8f-d43919df9527\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"brtsams pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":10},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":10,\"uuid\":\"2e5dd853-abf3-4eb0-ab7b-8d077c64016d\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"; \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":10,\"end\":12}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ārabhya\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":12,\"end\":19},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":12,\"end\":19,\"uuid\":\"6a8c6cb5-5df5-4dd4-9c60-6be2c6600541\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" with the meaning of “referring to/having to do with,” a frequent occurrence in Saṃdh. See Edgerton 1953, p. 102.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":19,\"end\":132}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"d01c2112-9d68-4051-8666-c790e163e9af\",\"sort\":12859,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.66\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"$4f\",\"label\":\"2.1\",\"sort\":2819,\"type\":\"translation\",\"uuid\":\"5ee1053b-7911-4600-b68b-664f3eb45a71\",\"workUuid\":\"da0adcd3-4abf-406a-8021-b656a348fab8\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-049-001-225\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":406,\"uuid\":\"d01c2112-9d68-4051-8666-c790e163e9af\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"rtog ge thams cad las yang dag par ’das pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":42},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":42,\"uuid\":\"e0759f74-9d09-4300-8cf9-1d147dd688d5\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"; \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":42,\"end\":44}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"sarva­tarka­samati­krānta\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":44,\"end\":69},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":44,\"end\":69,\"uuid\":\"8c3f880d-cae5-4244-be94-008a1e07b057\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". Regarding the translation of the term \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":69,\"end\":109}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"rtog ge\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":109,\"end\":116},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":109,\"end\":116,\"uuid\":\"00ab53fa-beac-47c5-959f-0095ebf1c426\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":116,\"end\":118}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"tarka\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":118,\"end\":123},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":118,\"end\":123,\"uuid\":\"041a4d01-9209-4d40-8276-b3fe69a3234c\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"), Powers 1995, p. 25 suggests “argumentation,” but the emphasis in the present context is not on logical reasoning. The term \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":123,\"end\":249}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"tarka\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":249,\"end\":254},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":249,\"end\":254,\"uuid\":\"d470e580-29ea-44cd-9237-3a7ebc4ed0a2\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" denotes here any kind of \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":254,\"end\":280}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"assumption\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":280,\"end\":290},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"c5540d92-f1c5-48ff-9dd7-a4c9a3d8128c\",\"uuid\":\"e3b9e97b-18a5-4989-bde7-beb16c028785\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", presupposition, representation, or conjecture regarding the absolute that is the product of the intellect (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":290,\"end\":399}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"manas\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":399,\"end\":404},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":399,\"end\":404,\"uuid\":\"2c5445f3-d463-489b-ab00-36f795b5da17\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\").\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":404,\"end\":406}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"1b736611-c21a-497d-928c-eb29d320a9b2\",\"sort\":12874,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.67\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"$50\",\"label\":\"2.2\",\"sort\":2864,\"type\":\"translation\",\"uuid\":\"3faa44e6-9bb4-4672-a02d-cca23dbdb2a4\",\"workUuid\":\"da0adcd3-4abf-406a-8021-b656a348fab8\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-049-001-228\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":664,\"uuid\":\"1b736611-c21a-497d-928c-eb29d320a9b2\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"The English translation of this passage should convey the paradox of the situation. Although the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":97}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ultimate\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":97,\"end\":105},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"1ce42c0c-900f-47c2-9d40-98ccbafcb2bf\",\"uuid\":\"d365b9c1-7b89-43fb-8de7-734bd4438781\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" is \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":105,\"end\":109}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"inexpressible\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":109,\"end\":122},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"8836e1d5-a1cb-48d5-aa27-78153a0bb6bf\",\"uuid\":\"489236b4-7974-4ba9-87ce-b18d21816faa\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", the Buddha gave countless teachings. Syntactic connective particles between clauses about the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":122,\"end\":218}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"inexpressible\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":218,\"end\":231},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"8836e1d5-a1cb-48d5-aa27-78153a0bb6bf\",\"uuid\":\"a3abb82b-b2c2-4687-b41f-8a04d8034d60\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":231,\"end\":232}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ultimate\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":232,\"end\":240},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"1ce42c0c-900f-47c2-9d40-98ccbafcb2bf\",\"uuid\":\"81099bb8-7a39-4213-83d0-1cb122842477\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" and the domain of expression and reasoning have therefore an adversative meaning in the present paragraph: \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":240,\"end\":348}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ngas ni don dam pa rtog ge thams cad las yang dag par ’das pa’i mtshan nyid mngon par rdzogs par sangs rgyas te/ mngon par rdzogs par sangs rgyas nas kyang bsnyad cing gsal bar byas/ rnam par phye/ gdags par byas/ rab tu bstan to/ de ci’i phyir zhe na\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":348,\"end\":599},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":348,\"end\":599,\"uuid\":\"8646d700-6f26-4673-aebb-058fb8e27235\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". Lamotte’s and Powers’ translation do not make this point clear.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":599,\"end\":664}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"ce13c614-6392-4ac2-afbc-0cf42c1c2ba5\",\"sort\":12886,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.68\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"$51\",\"label\":\"2.2\",\"sort\":2864,\"type\":\"translation\",\"uuid\":\"3faa44e6-9bb4-4672-a02d-cca23dbdb2a4\",\"workUuid\":\"da0adcd3-4abf-406a-8021-b656a348fab8\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-049-001-228\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":527,\"uuid\":\"ce13c614-6392-4ac2-afbc-0cf42c1c2ba5\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"so so(r) rang rig pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":20},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":20,\"uuid\":\"176e8c53-09c1-491b-9c9c-cad980f10219\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"; \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":20,\"end\":22}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"pratyātmavedya\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":22,\"end\":36},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":22,\"end\":36,\"uuid\":\"9d4c8525-2617-4cdb-ac68-b03f89bd4c44\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"/\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":36,\"end\":37}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"pratyātmavedanīya\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":37,\"end\":54},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":37,\"end\":54,\"uuid\":\"dad8b891-6b54-4613-b2b7-1e176c68743b\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"/\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":54,\"end\":55}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"pratyātmajñāna\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":55,\"end\":69},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":55,\"end\":69,\"uuid\":\"4b997c1a-9126-4404-8e62-02ee17e94165\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"/\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":69,\"end\":70}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"prātyatmam\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":70,\"end\":80},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":70,\"end\":80,\"uuid\":\"ea875715-0937-407b-94d6-076af5c567ea\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" (see Schmithausen 2014, p. 346), in the sense of realizing or understanding for oneself in an intuitive way, as personal experience. Powers’ translation does not reflect the meaning of this term: “I have explained that the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":80,\"end\":304}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ultimate\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":304,\"end\":312},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"1ce42c0c-900f-47c2-9d40-98ccbafcb2bf\",\"uuid\":\"c82c7335-c330-425a-886b-d75e4eeb2a32\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" is realized individually by the Aryas, while \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":312,\"end\":358}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"objects\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":358,\"end\":365},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"cf9988ae-d23d-4a8e-a24a-2f5503ee7f00\",\"uuid\":\"12871921-1f20-42f4-b1bf-fe8d572ec173\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" collectively known by \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":365,\"end\":388}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ordinary beings\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":388,\"end\":403},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"50e629b7-b87f-4638-a601-6473a169ebed\",\"uuid\":\"38da536c-8951-4b15-aabb-268a7bd96e89\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" [belong to] the realm of argumentation.” In the sūtra, \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":403,\"end\":459}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"so so(r) rang rig pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":459,\"end\":479},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":459,\"end\":479,\"uuid\":\"5999f31d-ad6d-4281-bc34-621057e680e1\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" is a synonym or a qualifier of \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":479,\"end\":511}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ye shes\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":511,\"end\":518},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":511,\"end\":518,\"uuid\":\"e2286771-9404-4aae-902e-8dcf953e3fe5\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":518,\"end\":520}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"jñāna\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":520,\"end\":525},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":520,\"end\":525,\"uuid\":\"de5eb6aa-eee9-4031-b0c9-d495a6fae710\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\").\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":525,\"end\":527}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"c47efb69-12d9-4633-9f38-a52da241ba48\",\"sort\":12909,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.69\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"$52\",\"label\":\"2.2\",\"sort\":2864,\"type\":\"translation\",\"uuid\":\"3faa44e6-9bb4-4672-a02d-cca23dbdb2a4\",\"workUuid\":\"da0adcd3-4abf-406a-8021-b656a348fab8\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-049-001-228\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":442,\"uuid\":\"c47efb69-12d9-4633-9f38-a52da241ba48\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Lamotte translates \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":19}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"rtog ge’i spyod yul\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":19,\"end\":38},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":19,\"end\":38,\"uuid\":\"23f08917-a670-4a7f-95b5-4cc475828e20\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" by “affaire de tradition”; see Lamotte 1935, p. 173. Beyond the fact that this is wrong, it is worth noting that the opposition here is between the intuitive and personal knowledge of the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":38,\"end\":227}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"noble beings\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":227,\"end\":239},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"bfa6b55c-3da0-4cca-9355-a5dae8884e1d\",\"uuid\":\"2aad42c8-687c-4e7f-ba5f-a423f205db63\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" and the intellectual and transactional knowledge of \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":239,\"end\":292}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ordinary beings\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":292,\"end\":307},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"50e629b7-b87f-4638-a601-6473a169ebed\",\"uuid\":\"140c82ee-3820-49b9-a274-684b8bc1eb67\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", namely, between \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":307,\"end\":325}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"gnosis\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":325,\"end\":331},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"b36258b5-bd30-4205-aeeb-75bac743076f\",\"uuid\":\"5f33d9d4-b406-4a95-a0f1-08412b2a821f\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" and \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":331,\"end\":336}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"mind\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":336,\"end\":340},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"b667709c-9e2a-4877-96d5-8b056867ac96\",\"uuid\":\"466b15fd-b0c5-4fad-9340-88b66260eb4b\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". Powers 1995, p. 27 reflects the personal aspect of \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":340,\"end\":393}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"so sor rang gi rig\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":393,\"end\":411},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":393,\"end\":411,\"uuid\":\"f859a915-7b2c-45ba-a739-5f18fcac9d17\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" but not its intuitive \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":411,\"end\":434}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"quality\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":434,\"end\":441},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"db978d42-1d2b-4528-96ec-5d3723ce043c\",\"uuid\":\"8f5d8b7b-9d8b-43ae-9932-913dce467fe2\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\".\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":441,\"end\":442}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"4b0d6cc3-1df9-410d-b3cb-c007d40e3b10\",\"sort\":12925,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.70\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"$53\",\"label\":\"2.2\",\"sort\":2864,\"type\":\"translation\",\"uuid\":\"3faa44e6-9bb4-4672-a02d-cca23dbdb2a4\",\"workUuid\":\"da0adcd3-4abf-406a-8021-b656a348fab8\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-049-001-228\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":328,\"uuid\":\"4b0d6cc3-1df9-410d-b3cb-c007d40e3b10\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"mtshan ma\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":9},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":9,\"uuid\":\"d99a19ec-343c-4ba4-a378-c0e9a505f67d\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"; \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":9,\"end\":11}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"nimitta\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":11,\"end\":18},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":11,\"end\":18,\"uuid\":\"8ef0f52f-3547-461a-b9ff-51679356f46d\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"47d7ce80-c6de-4173-bf62-5997019ee7de\",\"uuid\":\"60f22286-d3fe-4d7b-8d4f-8fb5e728fbd0\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". Although “notion” would fit well here, one should keep in \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":18,\"end\":78}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"mind\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":78,\"end\":82},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"b667709c-9e2a-4877-96d5-8b056867ac96\",\"uuid\":\"a78f91ad-bd10-446c-9335-98a7979f0c0f\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" that \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":82,\"end\":88}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"nimitta\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":88,\"end\":95},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":88,\"end\":95,\"uuid\":\"b0743599-caf9-4205-b16d-7e68ba7a737e\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}},{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"47d7ce80-c6de-4173-bf62-5997019ee7de\",\"uuid\":\"bba8b457-530e-46ee-bbfa-e1d3ea07d1a3\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" as a polysemic term denotes \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":95,\"end\":124}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"phenomenal appearance\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":124,\"end\":145},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"47d7ce80-c6de-4173-bf62-5997019ee7de\",\"uuid\":\"bf9c4c20-e20e-4efd-9788-d906bec3656d\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" throughout the sūtra. However, it is clear that “\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":145,\"end\":195}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"phenomenal appearance\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":195,\"end\":216},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"47d7ce80-c6de-4173-bf62-5997019ee7de\",\"uuid\":\"08674961-930b-4fd6-bc8c-c906439b4e0a\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"” and “notion” are two terms that are joined at the hip from the perspective of the doctrine expounded in Saṃdh.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":216,\"end\":328}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"c0060139-61eb-49f6-8140-80c493f6ee4d\",\"sort\":12938,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.71\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"$54\",\"label\":\"2.2\",\"sort\":2864,\"type\":\"translation\",\"uuid\":\"3faa44e6-9bb4-4672-a02d-cca23dbdb2a4\",\"workUuid\":\"da0adcd3-4abf-406a-8021-b656a348fab8\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-049-001-228\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":440,\"uuid\":\"c0060139-61eb-49f6-8140-80c493f6ee4d\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"In 2.2, the Buddha mentions a paradox. He gives explanations about the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":71}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ultimate\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":71,\"end\":79},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"1ce42c0c-900f-47c2-9d40-98ccbafcb2bf\",\"uuid\":\"b3e1d481-f856-49ce-93fe-cbf163b6ea17\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" in speculative terms, although the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":79,\"end\":115}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ultimate\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":115,\"end\":123},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"1ce42c0c-900f-47c2-9d40-98ccbafcb2bf\",\"uuid\":\"8bb39128-b00b-4fb3-b829-4f0f63d47373\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" is \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":123,\"end\":127}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"inexpressible\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":127,\"end\":140},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"8836e1d5-a1cb-48d5-aa27-78153a0bb6bf\",\"uuid\":\"c2c61c20-f12f-45b1-abd6-afa38f8f71df\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". This paradox is best rendered in English or French by reading the particle \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":140,\"end\":217}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"la\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":217,\"end\":219},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":217,\"end\":219,\"uuid\":\"c3f69f6a-e767-4b2a-abcb-219ca2578481\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" in the statements in question as having an adversative meaning. For example: \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":219,\"end\":297}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"chos ’phags gzhan yang don dam pa ni tha snyad thams cad yang dag par chad pa yin par ngas bshad la/ rtog ge ni tha snyad kyi spyod yul yin te\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":297,\"end\":439},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":297,\"end\":439,\"uuid\":\"bdaf7a7a-0dd5-4e1e-9a01-230be0263ad6\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\".\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":439,\"end\":440}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"9a676aa1-dc5b-40ba-b7b8-43e3645d5569\",\"sort\":12950,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.72\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"Then, at that moment, the Blessed One spoke these verses: “It is the domain whose characteristic must be intuitively cognized, Beyond all expressions, apart from all conventions, And free from argumentative disputations‍— Such is the ultimate whose characteristic transcends all speculation.” This was the chapter of the bodhisattva Dharmodgata‍—the second chapter.\",\"label\":\"2.4\",\"sort\":2996,\"type\":\"translation\",\"uuid\":\"c06acec9-e0b9-4942-a775-4b8586fc2db7\",\"workUuid\":\"da0adcd3-4abf-406a-8021-b656a348fab8\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-049-001-236\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":369,\"uuid\":\"9a676aa1-dc5b-40ba-b7b8-43e3645d5569\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"The Turfan Sanskrit fragment found by Matsuda reads \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":52}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"paramārtha\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":52,\"end\":62},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":52,\"end\":62,\"uuid\":\"2a7ce9ac-f1cd-4abf-8ea6-a4fabf5dde84\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" [\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":62,\"end\":64}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"dhar\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":64,\"end\":68},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":64,\"end\":68,\"uuid\":\"59684833-1153-499f-805b-cca8b1cd661c\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"]\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":68,\"end\":69}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"mā vigatābhilāpaḥ\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":69,\"end\":86},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":69,\"end\":86,\"uuid\":\"3fc257ff-1080-440e-b4e8-8b71a0c7f8f2\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" at the end of chapter 2’s closing \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":86,\"end\":121}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"gāthā\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":121,\"end\":126},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"71bbdd49-c6e1-487c-9d30-86e7fa56a899\",\"uuid\":\"2871494f-f038-435f-9c6d-2b955d1fdeff\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" (cf. Sanskrit text in Matsuda 2013: p. 940 \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":126,\"end\":170}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ad\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":170,\"end\":172},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":170,\"end\":172,\"uuid\":\"5109625a-ae2d-4281-a0c6-f772c9577669\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"distinct\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" Lamotte VIII.41). In D, folio 6.b and F, folio 10.b, we have instead the Tibetan term \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":172,\"end\":259}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"rtsod dang bral ba\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":259,\"end\":277},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":259,\"end\":277,\"uuid\":\"ff6872da-c1da-49d3-a6e9-ae279c34ca1b\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". It is possible that \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":277,\"end\":299}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"brjod med\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":299,\"end\":308},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":299,\"end\":308,\"uuid\":\"918e82e4-0af9-4fef-b006-fc025579bfd9\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" in line 2 and \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":308,\"end\":323}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"rtsod dang bral ba\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":323,\"end\":341},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":323,\"end\":341,\"uuid\":\"d046d111-ee38-453e-97a3-ce81c7acbf8f\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" were inverted \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":341,\"end\":356}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"metri causae\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":356,\"end\":368},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":356,\"end\":368,\"uuid\":\"aa8fe71a-4ceb-463a-9a58-c5e688acfcf2\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Zh-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\".\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":368,\"end\":369}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"82107dd5-67db-4fca-b1f2-226ed52a93f8\",\"sort\":12970,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.73\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"Then, at that moment, the Blessed One spoke these verses: “It is the domain whose characteristic must be intuitively cognized, Beyond all expressions, apart from all conventions, And free from argumentative disputations‍— Such is the ultimate whose characteristic transcends all speculation.” This was the chapter of the bodhisattva Dharmodgata‍—the second chapter.\",\"label\":\"2.4\",\"sort\":2996,\"type\":\"translation\",\"uuid\":\"c06acec9-e0b9-4942-a775-4b8586fc2db7\",\"workUuid\":\"da0adcd3-4abf-406a-8021-b656a348fab8\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-049-001-236\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":306,\"uuid\":\"82107dd5-67db-4fca-b1f2-226ed52a93f8\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Powers reads \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":13}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"don dam pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":13,\"end\":23},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":13,\"end\":23,\"uuid\":\"0768ab2b-a9ba-43b7-8167-a2778ac9f864\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" and \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":23,\"end\":28}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"mtshan nyid\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":28,\"end\":39},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":28,\"end\":39,\"uuid\":\"c521ed9a-9014-4a10-8c8a-3104809a915e\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" as being in apposition in the sentence \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":39,\"end\":79}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"de\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":79,\"end\":81},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":79,\"end\":81,\"uuid\":\"98beae3b-05df-4003-9c7c-1c98f4429974\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" [i.e., \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":81,\"end\":89}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"don dam pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":89,\"end\":99},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":89,\"end\":99,\"uuid\":\"11bd59b3-35b2-4bb9-94d4-fae4a4da1140\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"] \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":99,\"end\":101}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ni rtog ge kun las ’das mtshan nyid\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":101,\"end\":136},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":101,\"end\":136,\"uuid\":\"d6222700-65c8-41c4-8280-e6d1962477ba\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". Lamotte reads \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":136,\"end\":152}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"rtog ge kun las ’das mtshan nyid\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":152,\"end\":184},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":152,\"end\":184,\"uuid\":\"3e12a7b9-f428-433e-926d-fa51abe6538d\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":184,\"end\":186}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"sarva­tarka­samati­krāntalakṣaṇa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":186,\"end\":218},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":186,\"end\":218,\"uuid\":\"bc78eb1d-d7f1-4630-abe5-0742f434adb5\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\") as a \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":218,\"end\":225}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"bahuvrīhi\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":225,\"end\":234},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"2283dbd7-1426-4735-a42e-fa3085c70c20\",\"uuid\":\"680b2869-070d-4d50-b0d3-0b7e70a38343\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", which is much better. See Powers 1995, p. 31 and Lamotte 1935, p. 174.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":234,\"end\":306}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"74c105d3-cba4-4477-8dea-6f6c15315c11\",\"sort\":12988,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.74\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"$55\",\"label\":\"3.1\",\"sort\":3022,\"type\":\"translation\",\"uuid\":\"70bfee1b-c1f8-4d09-adf9-a3a6ef7ad4ed\",\"workUuid\":\"da0adcd3-4abf-406a-8021-b656a348fab8\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-049-001-241\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":456,\"uuid\":\"74c105d3-cba4-4477-8dea-6f6c15315c11\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"I am using the adjective “indistinct” here in the sense of the first definition given in the Oxford English Dictionary: “1. Not distinct or distinguished from each other, or from something else; not kept separate or apart in the mind or perception; not clearly defined or marked off.” \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":285}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Oxford English Dictionary Online\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":285,\"end\":317},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"e1977566-cfb0-47e7-9f7d-2613b2593ec8\",\"lang\":\"en\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", s.v. “indistinct,” accessed July 20, 2020, https://www-oed-com.ezproxy.leidenuniv.nl:2443/view/Entry/94602?redirectedFrom=indistinct#eid.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":317,\"end\":456}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"8da6624b-f29e-45b8-8bb6-bc302a67353c\",\"sort\":12996,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.75\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"$56\",\"label\":\"3.1\",\"sort\":3022,\"type\":\"translation\",\"uuid\":\"70bfee1b-c1f8-4d09-adf9-a3a6ef7ad4ed\",\"workUuid\":\"da0adcd3-4abf-406a-8021-b656a348fab8\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-049-001-241\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":104,\"uuid\":\"8da6624b-f29e-45b8-8bb6-bc302a67353c\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"mos pa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":6},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":6,\"uuid\":\"b8ea6a5b-a64e-490e-bf89-859096ec0091\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"; \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":6,\"end\":8}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"praṇidhāna\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":8,\"end\":18},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":8,\"end\":18,\"uuid\":\"b824f79f-d25b-4ed1-ac23-95a6ac6a5d84\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". See \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":18,\"end\":24}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"mos pa spyod pa’i sa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":24,\"end\":44},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":24,\"end\":44,\"uuid\":\"6bd6eca8-6ad5-4d5f-8325-2cee6c717967\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". See Mvyut 897: \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":44,\"end\":61}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"mos pa spyod pa’i sa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":61,\"end\":81},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":61,\"end\":81,\"uuid\":\"b24a10aa-75f8-4e5d-b63d-a1fedddd06ac\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"; \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":81,\"end\":83}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"adhimukticaryābhūmiḥ\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":83,\"end\":103},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":83,\"end\":103,\"uuid\":\"f7f26c0b-70f9-415a-99c2-7fcdcefafaed\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\".\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":103,\"end\":104}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"cdd35459-2747-440c-aac4-1f941cd63d83\",\"sort\":13007,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.76\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"$57\",\"label\":\"3.1\",\"sort\":3022,\"type\":\"translation\",\"uuid\":\"70bfee1b-c1f8-4d09-adf9-a3a6ef7ad4ed\",\"workUuid\":\"da0adcd3-4abf-406a-8021-b656a348fab8\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-049-001-241\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":706,\"uuid\":\"cdd35459-2747-440c-aac4-1f941cd63d83\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Schmithausen reads \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":19}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"don dam pa’i mtshan nyid\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":19,\"end\":43},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":19,\"end\":43,\"uuid\":\"f79134c5-e6ad-47ca-966c-37b76497acfc\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":43,\"end\":45}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"paramārthalakṣaṇa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":45,\"end\":62},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":45,\"end\":62,\"uuid\":\"7f9248bf-8d1e-4b8d-a9b1-3e288303c5de\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\") as “the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":62,\"end\":72}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"defining characteristic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":72,\"end\":95},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"f4503be0-02d4-474f-8f1c-a69993648574\",\"uuid\":\"7091ba1d-054c-468d-9f60-948482366b3c\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" that is the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":95,\"end\":108}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ultimate\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":108,\"end\":116},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"1ce42c0c-900f-47c2-9d40-98ccbafcb2bf\",\"uuid\":\"7505b207-2bdf-4d72-af26-e3f7f4435153\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"” in \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":116,\"end\":121}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"3.5\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":121,\"end\":124},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"internalLink\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"e1fe0e9d-a0bd-42e2-8f2a-54b3267e321a\",\"href\":\"/entity/passage/9cde80ae-98ea-41b5-adfd-3895a431a73a\",\"entity\":\"9cde80ae-98ea-41b5-adfd-3895a431a73a\",\"type\":\"passage\",\"toh\":null,\"isSameWork\":true,\"subtype\":\"translation\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" (see Schmithausen 2014, p. 558, §512.3). However, Saṃdh. chapter 3 is about \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":124,\"end\":201}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"conditioned phenomena\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":201,\"end\":222},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"cf78a4e2-f7a7-4e09-992d-8e8c0671369b\",\"uuid\":\"2e9dc924-5482-4602-94a8-6ff3fa430669\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" in relation to the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":222,\"end\":242}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ultimate\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":242,\"end\":250},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"1ce42c0c-900f-47c2-9d40-98ccbafcb2bf\",\"uuid\":\"030d5595-253b-4988-90fd-4ee89046e207\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" when their respective \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":250,\"end\":273}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"defining characteristics\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":273,\"end\":297},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"f4503be0-02d4-474f-8f1c-a69993648574\",\"uuid\":\"d6f5732b-5153-477e-a66b-199dcfc829f3\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" are examined. The question here is not to determine whether the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":297,\"end\":362}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ultimate\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":362,\"end\":370},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"1ce42c0c-900f-47c2-9d40-98ccbafcb2bf\",\"uuid\":\"7e514936-0067-4f62-8a14-14402cc88091\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" is the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":370,\"end\":378}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"defining characteristic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":378,\"end\":401},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"f4503be0-02d4-474f-8f1c-a69993648574\",\"uuid\":\"4cde2d6b-ebfb-499b-a0de-d5175e1d57f4\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" of \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":401,\"end\":405}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"conditioned phenomena\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":405,\"end\":426},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"cf78a4e2-f7a7-4e09-992d-8e8c0671369b\",\"uuid\":\"e55b82a9-7dc4-4190-ba7f-289105822ab8\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". Rather, it is to determine whether the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":426,\"end\":467}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"conditioned\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":467,\"end\":478},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"c41c6d0c-b684-45c0-9367-3c0df3d7d01b\",\"uuid\":\"820e7a70-3b37-4b98-9ef3-eca7a4f87225\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" and the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":478,\"end\":487}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ultimate\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":487,\"end\":495},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"1ce42c0c-900f-47c2-9d40-98ccbafcb2bf\",\"uuid\":\"122670f7-e15d-4456-917c-c30ef557a258\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" are different by examining their \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":495,\"end\":529}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"defining characteristics\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":529,\"end\":553},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"f4503be0-02d4-474f-8f1c-a69993648574\",\"uuid\":\"eeca90d3-45a6-40e5-98a5-56ee68c56f2a\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". Therefore, I read \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":553,\"end\":573}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"don dam pa’i mtshan nyid\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":573,\"end\":597},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":573,\"end\":597,\"uuid\":\"672e5cb8-396e-474e-bc77-e88798859f87\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" as “the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":597,\"end\":606}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"defining characteristic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":606,\"end\":629},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"f4503be0-02d4-474f-8f1c-a69993648574\",\"uuid\":\"1961e852-87a1-4fe7-bfb0-d061bb64c82c\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" of the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":629,\"end\":637}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ultimate\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":637,\"end\":645},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"1ce42c0c-900f-47c2-9d40-98ccbafcb2bf\",\"uuid\":\"90dbff85-2073-4255-9858-eda71c17565f\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\",” namely, as a genitive \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":645,\"end\":670}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"tatpuruṣa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":670,\"end\":679},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"9bd9c153-adda-44e8-a777-c891f1060bba\",\"uuid\":\"9e7bd84c-db64-467f-a207-d1b923d83c73\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" and not as a \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":679,\"end\":693}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"karmadhāraya\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":693,\"end\":705},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"b0ac2880-07b9-42f3-b9af-99161d3032ab\",\"uuid\":\"895a049f-b52b-40c2-81a1-751b0b2a04c1\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\".\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":705,\"end\":706}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"5e311a46-3613-4efb-8a92-9f36f50b2f2d\",\"sort\":13051,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.77\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"$58\",\"label\":\"3.1\",\"sort\":3022,\"type\":\"translation\",\"uuid\":\"70bfee1b-c1f8-4d09-adf9-a3a6ef7ad4ed\",\"workUuid\":\"da0adcd3-4abf-406a-8021-b656a348fab8\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-049-001-241\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":19,\"uuid\":\"5e311a46-3613-4efb-8a92-9f36f50b2f2d\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"To render \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":10}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"sha stag\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":10,\"end\":18},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":10,\"end\":18,\"uuid\":\"8ea8806b-adfa-4845-8e84-5a32c204a57d\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\".\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":18,\"end\":19}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"1c219cab-d5ef-4c10-bc7e-e0f08a9352be\",\"sort\":13055,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.78\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"$59\",\"label\":\"3.3\",\"sort\":3128,\"type\":\"translation\",\"uuid\":\"993cd0a3-5bf0-4e0a-8784-579445180f29\",\"workUuid\":\"da0adcd3-4abf-406a-8021-b656a348fab8\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-049-001-249\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":378,\"uuid\":\"1c219cab-d5ef-4c10-bc7e-e0f08a9352be\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"I did not translate the phrase \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":31}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"so so’i skye bo kho nar gyur bzhin du\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":31,\"end\":68},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":31,\"end\":68,\"uuid\":\"ec8f473a-3172-4f4a-8d84-5f718d2a3f8a\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" in an adversative mode (e.g., “though merely ordinary”) because the same phrase is found in the next paragraph in a parallel construction where the syntax in relation to the meaning cannot be interpreted to express contrast. Here \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":68,\"end\":299}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"bzhin du\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":299,\"end\":307},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":299,\"end\":307,\"uuid\":\"7c6b7538-44c9-4ed5-89d8-c274ea9fe8a0\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" stands for \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":307,\"end\":319}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"yathā\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":319,\"end\":324},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":319,\"end\":324,\"uuid\":\"12271e6b-23c6-44f7-99b6-9a07958cbacd\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" in the sense of “as” (i.e., “en tant que” in French).\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":324,\"end\":378}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"b5776147-e336-4830-a85e-3affa525a75e\",\"sort\":13063,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.79\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"$5a\",\"label\":\"3.3\",\"sort\":3128,\"type\":\"translation\",\"uuid\":\"993cd0a3-5bf0-4e0a-8784-579445180f29\",\"workUuid\":\"da0adcd3-4abf-406a-8021-b656a348fab8\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-049-001-249\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":274,\"uuid\":\"b5776147-e336-4830-a85e-3affa525a75e\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"grub pa dang bde ba\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":19},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":19,\"uuid\":\"47ff9af5-2287-4efe-8ee1-58e6751b99b5\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"; \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":19,\"end\":21}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"yogakṣema\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":21,\"end\":30},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":21,\"end\":30,\"uuid\":\"f7711a1c-7837-4547-a751-285c7bb34872\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" (see Edgerton 1953, p. 448a,b). Refer to Tillemans 1997, p. 157ff. for a discussion of Powers’ rendering of the term in his translation of Saṃdh. (Powers 1995). Lamotte translates this term with “de sécurité suprême.” See Lamotte 1935, p. 175.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":30,\"end\":274}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"72adbc69-8793-462c-863e-5528098e8e7f\",\"sort\":13068,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.80\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"$5b\",\"label\":\"3.3\",\"sort\":3128,\"type\":\"translation\",\"uuid\":\"993cd0a3-5bf0-4e0a-8784-579445180f29\",\"workUuid\":\"da0adcd3-4abf-406a-8021-b656a348fab8\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-049-001-249\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":1384,\"uuid\":\"72adbc69-8793-462c-863e-5528098e8e7f\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"I linked the two clauses with “and” because these two clauses are part of the logical argument on being “not different.” We have here a relative-correlative syntactic structure: \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":178}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"gang gi phyir\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":178,\"end\":191},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":178,\"end\":191,\"uuid\":\"35c4ca17-36d9-4da2-b7c3-4fcd5b1091fc\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" … \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":191,\"end\":194}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"de’i phyir\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":194,\"end\":204},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":194,\"end\":204,\"uuid\":\"3b7239cc-59c6-49bb-98c6-633fee09ffdf\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"  (i.e., \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":204,\"end\":213}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"yasmāt\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":213,\"end\":219},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":213,\"end\":219,\"uuid\":\"404c41a2-223e-4f2c-8a78-ab80136cd9b0\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" … \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":219,\"end\":222}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"tasmāt\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":222,\"end\":228},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":222,\"end\":228,\"uuid\":\"2ecd827b-5af1-4aaa-8d29-0341d00b9d5d\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"). The first two clauses linked by “and” represent the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":228,\"end\":283}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"hetu\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":283,\"end\":287},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":283,\"end\":287,\"uuid\":\"c2fbf688-a888-4e75-8408-638057842178\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" (“premise” or “reason”) \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":287,\"end\":312}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"posited\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":312,\"end\":319},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"e8587840-8619-45ba-a6ca-c2945fd37cca\",\"uuid\":\"0ccae95b-92e0-4edb-9c3c-77618be227a1\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" by \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":319,\"end\":323}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"yasmāt\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":323,\"end\":329},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":323,\"end\":329,\"uuid\":\"75b1bcbd-c8f6-4a22-94e1-f66db3a3c627\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". The logical structure of the paragraph is “since (a), (b), and (c), therefore (d)” (the conclusion that is stated in the very next sentence “For this reason…”): “\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":329,\"end\":493}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Su­viśuddha­mati\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":493,\"end\":509},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"ad3fb61a-79d5-4bba-ad3c-77a816d89022\",\"uuid\":\"2a70f233-5d28-4591-95c4-5df3e4662e10\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":509,\"end\":511}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ordinary beings\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":511,\"end\":526},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"50e629b7-b87f-4638-a601-6473a169ebed\",\"uuid\":\"c65abb58-e93c-4c86-8d6f-038f742a6326\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" (a) do not realize the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":526,\"end\":550}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"truth\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":550,\"end\":555},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"abe60eab-c2c6-4378-8741-74dc4f33f705\",\"uuid\":\"a1875b63-eb39-4c53-8bf9-ce941903cc04\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" and, as mere \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":555,\"end\":569}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ordinary beings\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":569,\"end\":584},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"50e629b7-b87f-4638-a601-6473a169ebed\",\"uuid\":\"c5b20b61-dda9-4790-bfc0-181ba0a57d01\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", (b) neither do they attain \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":584,\"end\":613}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"nirvāṇa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":613,\"end\":620},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"957da5d5-795e-4533-909b-58063c94b409\",\"uuid\":\"0a67e0de-c768-4030-9228-b0d35f9e7ff0\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":620,\"end\":626}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"unsurpassable good\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":626,\"end\":644},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"e9dc42a6-cab2-4d8a-8f96-6dc6862b5751\",\"uuid\":\"20fd17f9-d554-4e3b-ac0e-e5e977eb0a22\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", (c) nor do they fully and completely awaken to the unsurpassable complete and perfect \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":644,\"end\":732}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"awakening\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":732,\"end\":741},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"d0fda944-71f7-4a27-a806-7debbf320eea\",\"uuid\":\"091b10bf-1efe-4f16-bd32-d02e5ae2a706\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". For these reasons (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":741,\"end\":762}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"de’i phyir\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":762,\"end\":772},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":762,\"end\":772,\"uuid\":\"65004af6-3f7a-4a5b-a404-065c64d02741\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", referring to (a), (b), and (c)), it is not correct to say that the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":772,\"end\":841}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"defining characteristic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":841,\"end\":864},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"f4503be0-02d4-474f-8f1c-a69993648574\",\"uuid\":\"d0792b62-4ce6-4096-b03f-ddd8f4c3ead8\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" of \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":864,\"end\":868}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"conditioned phenomena\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":868,\"end\":889},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"cf78a4e2-f7a7-4e09-992d-8e8c0671369b\",\"uuid\":\"97cc96e1-836f-4d36-beaf-3b3b4ad0e595\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" and the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":889,\"end\":898}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"defining characteristic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":898,\"end\":921},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"f4503be0-02d4-474f-8f1c-a69993648574\",\"uuid\":\"20bc3471-ef65-41d6-ae49-099d33f5b4be\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" of the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":921,\"end\":929}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ultimate\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":929,\"end\":937},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"1ce42c0c-900f-47c2-9d40-98ccbafcb2bf\",\"uuid\":\"c59b2c85-05b5-46c9-8b60-ae755ef5c76c\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" are indistinct.” D, folio 7.b: \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":937,\"end\":969}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"blo gros shin tu rnam dag gang gi phyir so so’i skye bo bden pa mthong ba ma yin/ so so’i skye bo kho nar gyur bzhin du grub pa dang / bde ba bla na med pa’i mya ngan las ’das pa ’thob par yang mi ’gyur/ bla na med pa yang dag par rdzogs pa’i byang chub mngon par rdzogs par ’tshang rgya bar mi ’gyur ba de’i phyir ’du byed kyi mtshan nyid dang / don dam pa’i mtshan nyid tha dad pa ma yin zhes bya bar mi rung ste\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":969,\"end\":1383},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":969,\"end\":1383,\"uuid\":\"628f647b-2c93-4d63-8988-b1f0aea0d5e2\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\".\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1383,\"end\":1384}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"416322a3-23d6-4c13-b574-cec299d0fc95\",\"sort\":13110,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.81\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"$5c\",\"label\":\"3.3\",\"sort\":3128,\"type\":\"translation\",\"uuid\":\"993cd0a3-5bf0-4e0a-8784-579445180f29\",\"workUuid\":\"da0adcd3-4abf-406a-8021-b656a348fab8\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-049-001-249\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":1539,\"uuid\":\"416322a3-23d6-4c13-b574-cec299d0fc95\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"This entire paragraph is problematic in D: \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":43}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"blo gros shin tu rnam dag gang gi phyir bden pa mthong ba rnams ’du byed kyi mtshan ma dang bral ba ma yin gyi/ bral ba kho na yin pa dang / bden pa mthong ba mtshan ma’i ’ching ba las rnam par grol ba ma yin gyi/ rnam par grol ba yin pa dang / bden pa mthong ba gnas ngan len gyi ’ching ba las rnam par grol ba ma yin gyi/ rnam par grol ba dang / ’ching ba de gnyi ga las rnam par grol na grub pa dang / bde pa bla na [F.8.a] med pa’i phyir mya ngan las ’das pa ’thob par ’gyur ba dang / bla na med pa yang dag par rdzogs pa’i byang chub mngon par rdzogs par ’tshang rgya bar yang ’gyur ba\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":43,\"end\":633},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":43,\"end\":633,\"uuid\":\"37a49b3d-209f-4d2f-aee2-0741f2488388\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". However, Lamotte, Keenan, and Cleary translate the phrases in bold with a double \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":633,\"end\":716}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"negation\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":716,\"end\":724},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"637a0d08-6c42-4c32-a448-a854aca7bbc4\",\"uuid\":\"6fbff687-d172-47cf-b0c4-7154e61da786\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". If we look at the same paragraph in F, folio 10.a, we find an interesting textual variant in which the expected double \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":724,\"end\":845}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"negation\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":845,\"end\":853},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"637a0d08-6c42-4c32-a448-a854aca7bbc4\",\"uuid\":\"4c2ebb40-9c50-449e-ad25-25dd45411edd\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" is found: \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":853,\"end\":864}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ma bral ba’ang ma yin te\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":864,\"end\":888},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":864,\"end\":888,\"uuid\":\"5f51e0f1-7f42-4694-a766-9b71dc32a41b\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" and \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":888,\"end\":893}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ma grol ba’ang ma yin te\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":893,\"end\":917},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":893,\"end\":917,\"uuid\":\"576b8197-21ce-4637-af07-c7e171a864c6\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", just like in Xuanzang’s translation (由此道理當知一切非如理行 不如正理善清淨慧。由於今時非見諦者。於諸行相不能除遣。然能除遣非見諦者。 Cbeta, Taishō 676). Powers chose to translate this passage without proceeding to any emendation, which makes little sense from the perspective of the argument expounded in this section of the text: “\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":917,\"end\":1205}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Su­viśuddha­mati\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1205,\"end\":1221},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"ad3fb61a-79d5-4bba-ad3c-77a816d89022\",\"uuid\":\"b7760a66-ec2a-4672-9eab-fb7dbde78f6e\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", it is not the case that seers of \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1221,\"end\":1256}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"truth\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1256,\"end\":1261},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"abe60eab-c2c6-4378-8741-74dc4f33f705\",\"uuid\":\"88cadc7b-48d5-49da-bc98-b7d3516c37b2\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" are free from the signs of the compounded; they are simply free. Moreover, seers of \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1261,\"end\":1346}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"truth\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1346,\"end\":1351},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"abe60eab-c2c6-4378-8741-74dc4f33f705\",\"uuid\":\"c099f8ae-048b-4d36-973b-d1a2021213d5\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" are not liberated from the bondage of signs, but they are liberated. Seers of \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1351,\"end\":1430}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"truth\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1430,\"end\":1435},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"abe60eab-c2c6-4378-8741-74dc4f33f705\",\"uuid\":\"9136619d-cb38-4ce3-aeba-67fdae1028dd\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" are not liberated from the bondage of errant tendencies, but they are liberated.” (Powers 1995, p. 41).\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1435,\"end\":1539}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"a5164c27-2f61-425a-af6f-36c383ec692f\",\"sort\":13132,\"type\":\"endnotes\",\"label\":\"n.82\",\"alignments\":{},\"references\":[{\"content\":\"$5d\",\"label\":\"3.3\",\"sort\":3128,\"type\":\"translation\",\"uuid\":\"993cd0a3-5bf0-4e0a-8784-579445180f29\",\"workUuid\":\"da0adcd3-4abf-406a-8021-b656a348fab8\",\"xmlId\":\"UT22084-049-001-249\",\"toh\":null,\"alignments\":[],\"annotations\":[]}]},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":1966,\"uuid\":\"a5164c27-2f61-425a-af6f-36c383ec692f\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"We have here again a complex relative-correlative syntactic structure: \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":71}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"gang gi phyir\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":71,\"end\":84},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":71,\"end\":84,\"uuid\":\"b21599b2-f704-4d6d-89c1-88a61e9c52b2\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" … \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":84,\"end\":87}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"de’i phyir\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":87,\"end\":97},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":87,\"end\":97,\"uuid\":\"054d9cf6-e8f3-4478-93dd-59d92ffa1a70\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" (i.e., \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":97,\"end\":105}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"yasmāt\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":105,\"end\":111},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":105,\"end\":111,\"uuid\":\"fdb39f9e-cac5-4525-90a3-a5d897a424c2\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" … \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":111,\"end\":114}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"tasmāt\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":114,\"end\":120},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":114,\"end\":120,\"uuid\":\"d7403cb4-0f94-4f53-bcdb-1ed219121aa4\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"). All the clauses between \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":120,\"end\":147}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"gang gi phyir\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":147,\"end\":160},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":147,\"end\":160,\"uuid\":\"6b8cb54e-3780-4e70-a822-a157d3c7562e\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" and \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":160,\"end\":165}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"de’i phyir\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":165,\"end\":175},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":165,\"end\":175,\"uuid\":\"9e25a7dd-8285-457e-9bac-9bbad4cb4d6a\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" represent the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":175,\"end\":190}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"hetu\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":190,\"end\":194},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":190,\"end\":194,\"uuid\":\"122308d9-7821-42e7-af7d-ced391f66a9d\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" (“premise” or “reason”) \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":194,\"end\":219}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"posited\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":219,\"end\":226},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"e8587840-8619-45ba-a6ca-c2945fd37cca\",\"uuid\":\"c7197966-cfcc-48f4-a9b8-2e43ff8c4447\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" by \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":226,\"end\":230}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"yasmāt\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":230,\"end\":236},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":230,\"end\":236,\"uuid\":\"4e2803f2-ec6a-4d51-b5d9-0abefbccdb71\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". The logical structure of the paragraph is “since (a), (b), (c), (d), therefore (e)” (the conclusion that is stated in the very next sentence, “For all these reasons,…”): “\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":236,\"end\":409}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Su­viśuddha­mati\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":409,\"end\":425},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"ad3fb61a-79d5-4bba-ad3c-77a816d89022\",\"uuid\":\"70b56fa4-7145-4d4a-88f3-cf2e5353d2e6\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", it is not the case that (a) those who realize the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":425,\"end\":477}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"truth\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":477,\"end\":482},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"abe60eab-c2c6-4378-8741-74dc4f33f705\",\"uuid\":\"5552a683-eaf6-4b15-9208-10f65f69c9e4\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" are not detached from the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":482,\"end\":509}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"phenomenal appearance of conditioned phenomena\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":509,\"end\":555},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"73574cde-38df-4f75-ac34-711b2bb284ed\",\"uuid\":\"6a7d6f9c-4b78-4c7e-b599-09d1c07075fc\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", for they are indeed detached from it. (b) Neither are they not liberated from the bondage of \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":555,\"end\":650}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"phenomenal appearance\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":650,\"end\":671},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"47d7ce80-c6de-4173-bf62-5997019ee7de\",\"uuid\":\"93d4d71f-8499-49c2-92ec-cea3d9054c6d\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", for they are indeed liberated from it. (c) Nor are they not liberated from the bondage of \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":671,\"end\":763}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"corruption\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":763,\"end\":773},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"beb8bd2f-4c8d-4044-b122-b481bb12239f\",\"uuid\":\"57a2887b-0236-4fb9-86a7-241edc959ca6\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", for they are indeed liberated from it. (d) Since they are liberated from these two kinds of bondage, [F.8.a] not only do they attain \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":773,\"end\":908}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"nirvāṇa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":908,\"end\":915},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"957da5d5-795e-4533-909b-58063c94b409\",\"uuid\":\"77a603e3-1c00-43e7-8c5f-24e08ea5a25f\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":915,\"end\":921}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"unsurpassable good\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":921,\"end\":939},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"e9dc42a6-cab2-4d8a-8f96-6dc6862b5751\",\"uuid\":\"6547cf9a-89fa-496a-8a4e-8555684a0581\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", but they will also fully and completely awaken to the unsurpassable complete and perfect \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":939,\"end\":1030}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"awakening\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1030,\"end\":1039},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"d0fda944-71f7-4a27-a806-7debbf320eea\",\"uuid\":\"1a264c92-d8eb-4fd9-a207-82c0d04c0061\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". (e) For all these reasons (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1039,\"end\":1068}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"de’i phyir\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1068,\"end\":1078},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1068,\"end\":1078,\"uuid\":\"91af855a-50fd-4614-aa0e-e59281e3241d\",\"type\":\"span\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"textStyle\":\"foreign\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" referring to (a), (b), (c), and (d)), it is not correct to say that the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1078,\"end\":1151}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"defining characteristic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1151,\"end\":1174},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"f4503be0-02d4-474f-8f1c-a69993648574\",\"uuid\":\"d3f734e3-19f0-4247-8e55-2e57c2061493\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" of \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1174,\"end\":1178}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"conditioned phenomena\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1178,\"end\":1199},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"cf78a4e2-f7a7-4e09-992d-8e8c0671369b\",\"uuid\":\"063fff69-d488-4318-a3b2-ff74644ccecb\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" and the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1199,\"end\":1208}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"defining characteristic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1208,\"end\":1231},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"f4503be0-02d4-474f-8f1c-a69993648574\",\"uuid\":\"acd28715-fcf2-4971-8333-dcf49149933f\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" of the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1231,\"end\":1239}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ultimate\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1239,\"end\":1247},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"gl