an\":\"བྱང་ཆུབ་སེམས་དཔའི་སྡེ་སྣོད།\",\"sanskrit\":\"bodhisattvapiṭaka\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"byang chub sems dpa’i sde snod\"}},{\"uuid\":\"29817c3c-4480-49e7-898c-dc83946daf00\",\"authority\":\"1a59d44f-7dd0-483e-97ab-b5013b832660\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"communication\",\"tibetan\":\"མིང་དུ་བྱ་བ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"saṃjñāpya\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"ming du bya ba\"}},{\"uuid\":\"5722d5a4-f634-4bf9-8ff7-02c6f7cb8f1f\",\"authority\":\"7727708a-8015-4958-8800-313b50726040\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"complete equanimity\",\"tibetan\":\"ལྷག་པར་བཏང་སྙོམས།\",\"sanskrit\":\"adhyupekṣya\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"lhag par btang snyoms\"}},{\"uuid\":\"642a2578-7627-4a96-9a66-fa70dd6d8fd8\",\"authority\":\"7e49cbc1-5e6c-4955-a13b-05c69328922f\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eMahāvyutpatti 6405.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"completely\",\"tibetan\":\"ཐམས་ཅད་ཀྱི་ཐམས་ཅད།\",\"sanskrit\":\"sarveṇa sarvam\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"thams cad kyi thams cad\"}},{\"uuid\":\"f906d3b1-54d9-404c-b6f8-61b44462c590\",\"authority\":\"ae21be7a-7f7e-47d5-b46c-62371f880f95\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"comprehension\",\"tibetan\":\"ཡོངས་སུ་ཤེས་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"parijñā\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"yongs su shes pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"fd605d5b-64e4-4b17-b210-6105958d064e\",\"authority\":\"943f8980-5ce2-4057-a3ae-0ffb9571f0ec\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eA state of deep \u003cspan\u003econcentration\u003c/span\u003e in which the mind is absorbed in its object to such a degree that conceptual thought is suspended. It is sometimes interpreted as settling (\u003cem class=\\\"foreign break text-sa\\\" lang=\\\"sa-LATN\\\"\u003eāhita\u003c/em\u003e) the mind in equanimity (\u003cem class=\\\"foreign break text-sa\\\" lang=\\\"sa-LATN\\\"\u003esama\u003c/em\u003e).\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":