innatathāgatavimokṣajñānaniṣṭhāgataḥ\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"de bzhin gshegs pa ma ’dres pa’i rnam par thar par mdzad pa’i ye shes kyi mthar phyin pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"243f52bb-9193-424f-bd42-63fcc81f27c2\",\"authority\":\"eb77d8fc-b4d7-4e7b-b0fc-9e13fbf14919\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"thesis\",\"tibetan\":\"དམ་བཅས།, སོ་སོའི་ཤེས་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"pratijñā\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"dam bcas, so so’i shes pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"d3543d54-0021-4c95-b565-8e4dc67c3858\",\"authority\":\"482f2880-dc80-43a0-a0de-7f8fed355ec8\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"thinks\",\"tibetan\":\"བྱེ་བྲག་ཕྱེད་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"mata\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"bye brag phyed pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"2abebaf5-c180-474a-a3cf-789828fd7825\",\"authority\":\"b5dcbda5-f0fe-4d17-a339-afb412ef03ca\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"those not following you\",\"tibetan\":\"སླད་རོལ་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"tīrthika\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"slad rol pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"e4defc4f-3f16-451f-95d4-409dd3e7b749\",\"authority\":\"3779c030-a446-45b1-b1c3-73f81aeb454d\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eThe three knowledges are the \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-049-001-1635\\\"\u003esuperior knowledge\u003c/span\u003e that is the realization of the recollection of former states (\u003cem class=\\\"foreign break text-sa\\\" lang=\\\"sa-LATN\\\"\u003epūrvanivāsanānusmṛtisākṣātkārābhijñā\u003c/em\u003e ), the \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-049-001-1635\\\"\u003esuperior knowledge\u003c/span\u003e that is the realization of death and rebirth (\u003cem class=\\\"foreign break text-sa\\\" lang=\\\"sa-LATN\\\"\u003ecyutyupapādasākṣātkārābhijñā\u003c/em\u003e), and the \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-049-001-1635\\\"\u003esuperior knowledge\u003c/span\u003e that is the realization of the cessation of outflows (\u003cem class=\\\"foreign break text-sa\\\" lang=\\\"sa-LATN\\\"\u003eāsravakṣayasākṣātkārābhijñā\u003c/em\u003e). See Powers 1995, p. 316, n. 17. \u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"three forms of knowledge\",\"tibetan\":\"རིགས་པ་གསུམ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"trividyā\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"rigs pa gsum\"}},{\"uuid\":\"a7fa4fdc-041a-4315-bc84-fabc84da189f\",\"authority\":\"3aba3c23-34ef-45d7-9f98-fa54fe939ce3\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eThe \u003cspan class=\\\"ignore\\\"\u003ethree worlds\u003c/span\u003e are: the desire realm (\u003cem class=\\\"foreign break text-sa\\\" lang=\\\"sa-LATN\\\"\u003ekāmadhātu\u003c/em\u003e, \u003cem class=\\\"foreign text-wy\\\" lang=\\\"bo-LATN\\\"\u003e’dod khams\u003c/em\u003e), form realm (\u003cem class=\\\"foreign break text-sa\\\" lang=\\\"sa-LATN\\\"\u003erūpadhātu\u003c/em\u003e, \u003cem class=\\\"foreign text-wy\\\" lang=\\\"bo-LATN\\\"\u003egzugs khams\u003c/em\u003e) and the formless realm (\u003cem class=\\\"foreign break text-sa\\\" lang=\\\"sa-LATN\\\"\u003eārūpyadhātu\u003c/em\u003e, \u003cem class=\\\"foreign text-wy\\\" lang=\\\"bo-LATN\\\"\u003egzugs med khams\u003c/em\u003e). These \u003cspan class=\\\"ignore\\\"\u003ethree worlds\u003c/span\u003e include all of saṃsāra.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"three worlds\",\"tibetan\":\"ཁམས་གསུམ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"traidhātuka, tridhātu\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"khams gsum\"}},{\"uuid\":\"4acb7607-6bde-4e9c-a42a-2d578d75908a\",\"authority\":\"36c5c0ad-ef51-4492-be22-a881ea641d27\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eThe timira disease includes a variety of eye disorders including myopia, cataract, etc. In the context of Buddhist texts, this term is used to refer to eye floaters (i.e., spots, specks, or strings appearing in one’s visual field). This eye disorder is called \u003cem class=\\\"foreign\\\"\u003emyodesopsia\u003c/em\u003e or \u003cem class=\\\"foreign\\\"\u003emuscae volitantes\u003c/em\u003e (Latin for “flying flies”).\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"timira\",\"tibetan\":\"རབ་རིབ་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"timira\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"rab rib pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"8989e737-34db-4935-becd-f2d33c521741\",\"authority\":\"c73d08fc-6490-4295-b9c7-76deadcd8875\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"to be comprehended\",\"tibetan\":\"ཡོངས་སུ་ཤེས་པར་བྱ་བའི་དངོས་པོ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"parijñeyavastu\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"yongs su shes par bya ba’i dngos po\"}},{\"uuid\":\"8118fffd-fbca-4a6a-8571-6a90ed13269d\",\"authority\":\"37ee8261-363c-4e10-b7f6-97e58067bd03\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp\u003eThe largest universe described in Buddhist cosmology. This term, in Abhidharma cosmology, refers to 1,000\u003csup\u003e³\u003c/sup\u003e world systems, i.e., 1,000 “dichiliocosms” or “two thousand great thousand world realms” (\u003cem class=\\\"foreign break text-sa\\\" lang=\\\"sa-LATN\\\"\u003edvi­sāhasra­mahā­sāhasra­lokadhātu\u003c/em\u003e), which are in turn made up of 1,000 first-order world systems, each with its own Mount Sumeru, continents, sun and moon, etc.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"trichiliocosm\",\"tibetan\":\"སྟོང་གསུམ་གྱི་སྟོང་ཆེན་པོའི་འཇིག་རྟེན་གྱི་ཁམས།\",\"sanskrit\":\"trisāhasra mahāssāhasralokadhātu\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"stong gsum gyi stong chen po’i ’jig rten gyi khams\"}},{\"uuid\":\"6ad93bf6-3994-4d9b-bb77-fdd3f8da0768\",\"authority\":\"9551ecf4-bc2b-4937-a6f9-18763cbe4125\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"true nature\",\"tibetan\":\"འདི་ལྟར་དོན།\",\"sanskrit\":\"yathārtha\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"’di ltar don\"}},{\"uuid\":\"76ba6263-e6ce-4069-b4c8-114361f6c5d0\",\"authority\":\"59af8757-263e-441c-90a9-dc0225d5e894\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eThe true state or \u003cspan class=\\\"ignore\\\"\u003enature of things\u003c/span\u003e. See also \u003ca href=\\\"end-notes.xhtml#UT22084-049-001-296\\\" data-pointer-type=\\\"id\\\"\u003en.97\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"true reality\",\"tibetan\":\"དེ་ཁོ་ན།, དེ་ཉིད།, དེ་བཞིན་ཉིད།\",\"sanskrit\":\"tathatā, tattva\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"de bzhin nyid, de kho na, de nyid\"}},{\"uuid\":\"abe60eab-c2c6-4378-8741-74dc4f33f705\",\"authority\":\"e3c6ab8a-4565-4c89-bf43-cff2ebae0063\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eSee the “\u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-049-001-1663\\\"\u003etwo truths\u003c/span\u003e” and “\u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-049-001-1474\\\"\u003efour noble truths\u003c/span\u003e.”\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"truth\",\"tibetan\":\"བདེན་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"satya\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"bden pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"a0dea610-3170-45d1-8066-2121a1ad810f\",\"authority\":\"0d072e74-3aaf-4424-8bff-29e126e70313\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eThe \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-049-001-1664\\\"\u003eultimate\u003c/span\u003e and relative, or conventional, \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-049-001-1661\\\"\u003etruth\u003c/span\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"two truths\",\"tibetan\":\"བདེན་པ་གཉིས།\",\"sanskrit\":\"satyadvaya\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"bden pa gnyis\"}},{\"uuid\":\"1ce42c0c-900f-47c2-9d40-98ccbafcb2bf\",\"authority\":\"77fecb3c-ea5b-4747-9cda-31f83a9598b3\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e The \u003cspan class=\\\"ignore\\\"\u003eultimate\u003c/span\u003e is said to be \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-049-001-1506\\\"\u003einexpressible\u003c/span\u003e, \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-049-001-1556\\\"\u003enondual\u003c/span\u003e, transcending speculation, transcending difference and sameness, and \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-049-001-1564\\\"\u003eof a single nature\u003c/span\u003e (i.e., \u003cem class=\\\"foreign break text-sa\\\" lang=\\\"sa-LATN\\\"\u003eanabhilāpya\u003c/em\u003e, \u003cem class=\\\"foreign break text-sa\\\" lang=\\\"sa-LATN\\\"\u003eadvaya\u003c/em\u003e, \u003cem class=\\\"foreign break text-sa\\\" lang=\\\"sa-LATN\\\"\u003esarva­tarka­samati­krānta\u003c/em\u003e, \u003cem class=\\\"foreign break text-sa\\\" lang=\\\"sa-LATN\\\"\u003ebhe­dābhe­dasa­mati­krānta\u003c/em\u003e, \u003cem class=\\\"foreign break text-sa\\\" lang=\\\"sa-LATN\\\"\u003eekarasa\u003c/em\u003e).\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"ultimate\",\"tibetan\":\"དོན་དམ་པ།, དོན་དམ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"paramārtha\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"don dam, don dam pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"396c822c-5328-4b13-9cb8-f880aaefff15\",\"authority\":\"474544b7-f5a4-4439-b00f-30a1e436a12d\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eThis term has three meanings: (1) the ultimate nature, (2) the experience of the ultimate nature, and (3) the quiescent state of a worthy one (\u003cem class=\\\"foreign break text-sa\\\" lang=\\\"sa-LATN\\\"\u003earhat\u003c/em\u003e) to be avoided by bodhisattvas.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"ultimate limit of existence\",\"tibetan\":\"ཡང་དག་པའི་མཐའ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"bhūtakoṭi\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"yang dag pa’i mtha’\"}},{\"uuid\":\"1165a20a-d114-40ab-8461-e122acff697a\",\"authority\":\"120e4a30-b213-49de-a1ac-c7d869c4ffb3\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"ultimate reality\",\"tibetan\":\"དེ་བཞིན་ཉིད་དོན་དམ་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"de bzhin nyid don dam pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"00431ab2-3f39-4944-b485-94bfdb8418ef\",\"authority\":\"f8197837-8a2e-4814-8094-17beeb95c82f\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eMahāvyutpatti 6429. \u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"ultimate within the domain of truth\",\"tibetan\":\"ཆོས་ཀྱི་དབྱིངས་ཀྱིས་ཀླས་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"dharmadhātuparamaḥ\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"chos kyi dbyings kyis klas pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"760ae48f-4c62-4d01-9846-06e850f94816\",\"authority\":\"32776ba5-d760-4337-b5b2-e8b95ce826d2\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"unborn\",\"tibetan\":\"མ་སྐྱེས་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"anutpanna\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"ma skyes pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"d680987b-fab1-4356-95cb-fce547654eec\",\"authority\":\"85072434-4b85-4c25-8277-d9c4f1a08dfc\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"unconditioned\",\"tibetan\":\"འདུ་མ་བྱས།\",\"sanskrit\":\"asaṃskṛta\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"’du ma byas\"}},{\"uuid\":\"21f1e13b-1a06-40b2-8c45-b653ba7eee42\",\"authority\":\"f7445d23-d66d-49cc-baac-d9139b7920be\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eMahāvyutpatti 363. \u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"understood all practices\",\"tibetan\":\"སྤྱོད་པ་ཐམས་ཅད་དང་ལྡན་པའི་བློ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"sarvacaryāsamanvāgatabuddhiḥ\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"spyod pa thams cad dang ldan pa’i blo\"}},{\"uuid\":\"422b9d6a-bae0-464f-bdce-bbf38a48872d\",\"authority\":\"e0497bf3-6bfd-48c3-a785-2aedf38436d0\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"unite them evenly\",\"tibetan\":\"ཟུང་དུ་འཇུག་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"yuganaddha\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"zung du ’jug pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"62eb469e-35c2-45af-af92-22b98ef6a17d\",\"authority\":\"f31a49a3-2045-4fe4-9173-d0d1496f798b\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"universe of a thousand worlds, universes of a thousand worlds\",\"tibetan\":\"སྟོང་གི་འཇིག་རྟེན་གྱི་ཁམས།\",\"sanskrit\":\"sāhasracūḍikalokadhātu\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"stong gi ’jig rten gyi khams\"}},{\"uuid\":\"c0aeaba2-c5bd-4256-83b2-0795eda22494\",\"authority\":\"44de7bfc-0f88-4c7c-9960-9ce118fee937\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eThe term has a double connotation: (1) “without effort” and (2) “unproduced (or brought about) by causes and conditions.” See Edgerton 1953, p. 21. \u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"unproduced by intentional action\",\"tibetan\":\"མངོན་པར་འདུ་བྱ་བ་མེད་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"anabhisaṃskāra, anabhisaṃskāraṇa\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"mngon par ’du bya ba med pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"e9dc42a6-cab2-4d8a-8f96-6dc6862b5751\",\"authority\":\"c1ae1086-fd11-451f-b2be-c36341c9d569\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eSee Edgerton 1953, p. 448,1–2; Tillemans 1997, p. 157ff. Lamotte translates this term with ‘…de sécurité suprême’; see Lamotte 1935, p. 175.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"unsurpassable good\",\"tibetan\":\"གྲུབ་པ་དང་བདེ་བ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"yogakṣema\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"grub pa dang bde ba\"}},{\"uuid\":\"17bee561-88f9-4d44-ab8a-ad93b1bfc968\",\"authority\":\"df70704c-b05b-4996-bb32-3199b8174e52\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eSee Edgerton 1953, p. 398.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"useful\",\"tibetan\":\"གཅེས་སྤྲས་བྱེད་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"bahukara\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"gces spras byed pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"e8437f52-dccc-4aa1-8329-40f0fe29eda8\",\"authority\":\"1990689e-9590-4aa7-8946-62d80e77cc2a\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eThe name of a bodhisattva \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-049-001-1624\\\"\u003estage\u003c/span\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Utmost Joy\",\"tibetan\":\"རབ་ཏུ་དགའ་བ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"pramuditā\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"rab tu dga’ ba\"}},{\"uuid\":\"5add74cc-e3ca-4918-9ab4-3da5bcec5089\",\"authority\":\"9277b3a3-78e9-4b21-bc39-56a87f308125\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eThe name of the northern continent of \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-049-001-1711\\\"\u003eJambudvīpa\u003c/span\u003e where people live in perfect harmony. See Bhattacharya 2000.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Uttarakuru\",\"tibetan\":\"བྱང་གི་སྒྲ་མི་སྙན་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"uttarakuru\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"byang gi sgra mi snyan pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"b58178d6-72f9-48fb-ae04-1dc1771c0947\",\"authority\":\"e54b87f1-5c7f-4d28-940f-acbe355aff01\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"valid\",\"tibetan\":\"ཡོངས་སུ་དག་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"pariśuddha\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"yongs su dag pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"e3a57f81-276c-45e4-ac8c-fbf09cd85d41\",\"authority\":\"0455e370-e73e-498e-95f1-df5d9cb468e8\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"valid cognition\",\"tibetan\":\"ཚད་མ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"pramāṇa\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"tshad ma\"}},{\"uuid\":\"082df3ce-24c2-4f9a-be57-bffa938e69cd\",\"authority\":\"a17bc2c1-73a7-4f1f-b46f-0992ab603a17\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eAlso known as Benares, one of the oldest cities of northeast India on the banks of the Ganges, in modern-day Uttar Pradesh. It was once the capital of the ancient kingdom of Kāśi, and in the Buddha’s time it had been absorbed into the kingdom of Kośala. It was an important religious center, as well as a major city, even during the time of the Buddha. The name may derive from being where the Varuna and Assi rivers flow into the Ganges. It was on the outskirts of Vārāṇasī that the Buddha first taught the Dharma, in the location known as Deer Park (\u003cem class=\\\"foreign break text-sa\\\" lang=\\\"sa-LATN\\\"\u003eMṛgadāva\u003c/em\u003e). For numerous episodes set in Vārāṇasī, including its kings, see \u003ca target=\\\"_blank\\\" href=\\\"https://read.84000.co/translation/toh340.html\\\" title=\\\"The Hundred Deeds\\\"\u003e\u003ccite class=\\\"title text-en\\\" lang=\\\"en\\\"\u003eThe Hundred Deeds\u003c/cite\u003e\u003c/a\u003e, Toh 340.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Vārāṇasī\",\"tibetan\":\"བཱ་རཱ་ཎ་སཱི།\",\"sanskrit\":\"vārāṇasī\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"bA rA Na sI\"}},{\"uuid\":\"afb1fe39-9a5a-4dfe-8723-31f7d6185185\",\"authority\":\"e2b83915-1535-43ad-b454-4e451255edf3\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eA bodhisattva mahāsattva.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Vidhi­vatpari­pṛcchaka\",\"tibetan\":\"ཚུལ་བཞིན་ཀུན་འདྲི།\",\"sanskrit\":\"vidhi­vatpari­pṛcchaka\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"tshul bzhin kun ’dri\"}},{\"uuid\":\"bf5c3642-eff6-4764-bbcc-53671b7226c2\",\"authority\":\"0b0380e8-e475-4908-80e8-72138fb7983c\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eTechnical term in Buddhist logic.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"vipakṣa\",\"tibetan\":\"\",\"sanskrit\":\"vipakṣa\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"\"}},{\"uuid\":\"7fffbce6-1a2e-4ff5-9c6b-ea9c71592c5c\",\"authority\":\"62c7f7c8-1927-4d85-bbf9-bce38eca8afc\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eThe name of a \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-049-001-1726\\\"\u003etathāgata\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Viśālakīrti\",\"tibetan\":\"\",\"sanskrit\":\"viśālakīrti\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"\"}},{\"uuid\":\"9b26647e-f72e-43fe-b4ad-83021b6b5dfc\",\"authority\":\"bfd73106-2500-412e-9727-5bb50082903e\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eA bodhisattva mahāsattva.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Viśālamati\",\"tibetan\":\"བློ་གྲོས་ཡངས་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"viśālamati\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"blo gros yangs pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"827740ac-1357-40ca-ae93-45ea3e70d73f\",\"authority\":\"6357cf17-e19e-4be5-952c-e68e958e81e4\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"vow\",\"tibetan\":\"སྡོམ་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"saṃvara\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"sdom pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"93b17f2f-c672-40de-850f-391ae60d7ce1\",\"authority\":\"908101c6-68ac-4f42-9af2-47ef4eecab86\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"wander like beggars\",\"tibetan\":\"སྤོངས་ཞིང་རྒྱུ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"caraṃti bhikṣāṃ\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"spongs zhing rgyu\"}},{\"uuid\":\"e3450112-5b5b-4385-b9eb-76b3bc8f466e\",\"authority\":\"f6103e93-078f-4946-8afc-4641b64f3e84\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"wavering\",\"tibetan\":\"རྒྱུ་བ་མེད་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"apracāra\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"rgyu ba med pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"b42b2ac8-e231-470f-9cb3-707080206a26\",\"authority\":\"d6d003c7-42ba-4062-8558-d371ff7235bb\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"whose defining characteristic is of a single nature everywhere\",\"tibetan\":\"ཐམས་ཅད་དུ་རོ་གཅིག་པའི་མཚན་ཉིད།\",\"sanskrit\":\"sarvatraikarasalakṣaṇa\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"thams cad du ro gcig pa’i mtshan nyid\"}},{\"uuid\":\"4c3420a1-ffdd-40b2-9f85-e4293f7c2bbb\",\"authority\":\"0463a3a0-7c70-451c-8dc5-e9db749dc718\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"wisdom\",\"tibetan\":\"ཤེས་རབ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"prajñā\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"shes rab\"}},{\"uuid\":\"93a3f64b-84f7-4f97-a268-b559e1128933\",\"authority\":\"31657084-0b1c-484a-9de5-90999963f022\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eOne of the three \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-049-001-1481\\\"\u003egates of liberation\u003c/span\u003e along with \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-049-001-1317\\\"\u003eappearancelessness\u003c/span\u003e and \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-049-001-1435\\\"\u003eemptiness\u003c/span\u003e. \u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"wishlessness\",\"tibetan\":\"སྨོན་པ་མེད་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"apraṇihita\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"smon pa med pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"8174be0a-0c24-4c40-88c1-d944d5ade59e\",\"authority\":\"9530182a-2e9a-4191-b2cc-458c51b439ad\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eSee Edgerton 1953, p. 102.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"with outflows\",\"tibetan\":\"ཟག་པ་དང་བཅས་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"sāsrava\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"zag pa dang bcas pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"246c0a8e-6027-4962-bccc-b731e30af102\",\"authority\":\"71ac8031-da8c-401c-92cd-2dee961d8940\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"without a person\",\"tibetan\":\"ཟག་མེད།\",\"sanskrit\":\"anāsrava\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"zag med\"}},{\"uuid\":\"92d5f010-0049-4d4c-8487-587582600dfc\",\"authority\":\"fa6ba879-1b5f-41a6-856d-3e94311e80a5\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"without support\",\"tibetan\":\"མི་གནས་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"apratiṣṭhita\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"mi gnas pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"c111f176-89d6-4bfc-9b2a-9b3756cabef1\",\"authority\":\"6bc88464-d01f-41dd-83e3-906807fba845\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp\u003eA class of nonhuman beings who inhabit forests, mountainous areas, and other natural spaces, or serve as guardians of villages and towns, and may be propitiated for health, wealth, protection, and other boons, or controlled through magic. According to tradition, their homeland is in the north, where they live under the rule of the Great King Vaiśravaṇa.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e Several members of this class have been deified as gods of wealth (these include the just-mentioned Vaiśravaṇa) or as bodhisattva generals of yakṣa armies, and have entered the Buddhist pantheon in a variety of forms, including, in tantric Buddhism, those of wrathful deities.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"yakṣa\",\"tibetan\":\"\",\"sanskrit\":\"yakṣa\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"\"}},{\"uuid\":\"d5ff75c7-72d7-4cf1-9a43-4a2048f72866\",\"authority\":\"ac6463e3-aa9e-4f27-83cf-ac5bd20feff0\",\"definition\":\"\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"yoga\",\"tibetan\":\"སྦྱོར་བ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"yoga\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"sbyor ba\"}}]}]\n"])</script><div hidden id="S:5"><div dir="ltr" data-orientation="horizontal" data-slot="tabs" class="flex flex-col w-full gap-0 @container/sidebar"><div class="sticky top-0 pt-1 pb-2 z-10 w-full rounded-t bg-background overflow-x-auto text-center"><div role="tablist" aria-orientation="horizontal" data-slot="tabs-list" class="bg-background gap-1 sm:gap-3 h-10 items-center justify-center sm:p-1 w-fit px-6 inline-flex mx-auto rounded-none" tabindex="-1" data-orientation="horizontal" style="outline:none"><button type="button" role="tab" aria-selected="true" aria-controls="radix-_R_2npftt6btb_-content-endnotes" data-state="active" id="radix-_R_2npftt6btb_-trigger-endnotes" data-slot="tabs-trigger" class="inline-flex items-center justify-center whitespace-nowrap px-1 py-0.75 text-sm data-[state=active]:font-semibold ring-offset-background transition-all focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-ring focus-visible:ring-offset-2 disabled:pointer-events-none disabled:opacity-50 bg-background text-foreground border-b-2 border-transparent data-[state=active]:border-primary-300 decoration-primary-25 hover:text-primary hover:border-primary/20 hover:cursor-pointer" tabindex="-1" data-orientation="horizontal" data-radix-collection-item="">Notes</button><button type="button" role="tab" aria-selected="false" aria-controls="radix-_R_2npftt6btb_-content-glossary" data-state="inactive" id="radix-_R_2npftt6btb_-trigger-glossary" data-slot="tabs-trigger" class="inline-flex items-center justify-center whitespace-nowrap px-1 py-0.75 text-sm data-[state=active]:font-semibold ring-offset-background transition-all focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-ring focus-visible:ring-offset-2 disabled:pointer-events-none disabled:opacity-50 bg-background text-foreground border-b-2 border-transparent data-[state=active]:border-primary-300 decoration-primary-25 hover:text-primary hover:border-primary/20 hover:cursor-pointer" tabindex="-1" data-orientation="horizontal" data-radix-collection-item="">Glossary</button><button type="button" role="tab" aria-selected="false" aria-controls="radix-_R_2npftt6btb_-content-bibliography" data-state="inactive" id="radix-_R_2npftt6btb_-trigger-bibliography" data-slot="tabs-trigger" class="inline-flex items-center justify-center whitespace-nowrap px-1 py-0.75 text-sm data-[state=active]:font-semibold ring-offset-background transition-all focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-ring focus-visible:ring-offset-2 disabled:pointer-events-none disabled:opacity-50 bg-background text-foreground border-b-2 border-transparent data-[state=active]:border-primary-300 decoration-primary-25 hover:text-primary hover:border-primary/20 hover:cursor-pointer" tabindex="-1" data-orientation="horizontal" data-radix-collection-item="">Biblio</button><button type="button" role="tab" aria-selected="false" aria-controls="radix-_R_2npftt6btb_-content-abbreviations" data-state="inactive" id="radix-_R_2npftt6btb_-trigger-abbreviations" data-slot="tabs-trigger" class="inline-flex items-center justify-center whitespace-nowrap px-1 py-0.75 text-sm data-[state=active]:font-semibold ring-offset-background transition-all focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-ring focus-visible:ring-offset-2 disabled:pointer-events-none disabled:opacity-50 bg-background text-foreground border-b-2 border-transparent data-[state=active]:border-primary-300 decoration-primary-25 hover:text-primary hover:border-primary/20 hover:cursor-pointer" tabindex="-1" data-orientation="horizontal" data-radix-collection-item="">Abbr</button></div></div><div class="px-2"><div class="overflow-auto md:h-[calc(100vh-8.5rem)] h-[calc(100vh-4rem)] rounded bg-surface"><div class="rounded ps-10 pe-4 max-w-readable mx-auto"><div data-state="active" data-orientation="horizontal" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="radix-_R_2npftt6btb_-trigger-endnotes" id="radix-_R_2npftt6btb_-content-endnotes" tabindex="0" data-slot="tabs-content" class="mt-2 ring-offset-background focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-ring focus-visible:ring-offset-2 data-[state=inactive]:hidden" style="animation-duration:0s"><div class="h-0"></div><div></div><div class="h-0"></div><div class="flex flex-col gap-4 pb-8"><div class="flex gap-5"><div class="animate-pulse rounded-md bg-foreground/10 h-6 w-6"></div><div class="animate-pulse rounded-md bg-foreground/10 h-32 grow"></div></div><div class="flex gap-5"><div class="animate-pulse rounded-md bg-foreground/10 h-6 w-6"></div><div class="animate-pulse rounded-md bg-foreground/10 h-32 grow"></div></div><div class="flex gap-5"><div class="animate-pulse rounded-md bg-foreground/10 h-6 w-6"></div><div class="animate-pulse rounded-md bg-foreground/10 h-32 grow"></div></div></div></div><div data-state="inactive" data-orientation="horizontal" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="radix-_R_2npftt6btb_-trigger-glossary" id="radix-_R_2npftt6btb_-content-glossary" tabindex="0" data-slot="tabs-content" class="mt-2 ring-offset-background focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-ring focus-visible:ring-offset-2 pb-8 data-[state=inactive]:hidden"><div class="flex flex-col w-full"><div id="glossary" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_2lanpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4 @c/sidebar:mt-5 mt-6">g.</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><h2 class="font-serif font-light text-primary scroll-m-20 text-xl @c/sidebar:mt-4 mt-6 @c/sidebar:pb-2 pb-3 @c/sidebar:text-left text-center section-title">Glossary</h2></div></div><div class="mt-3 flex flex-col gap-6"><div id="3337283c-de00-4fc7-a620-01a3880e630c" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_40d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">[five] faculties, five faculties</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dbang po lnga</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དབང་པོ་ལྔ།</span></li><li class="italic">pañcendriyāṇi</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">The five faculties are those of (1) <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-049-001-1458">faith</span>, (2) <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-049-001-1682">vigor</span>, (3) <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-049-001-1544">mindfulness</span>, (4) <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-049-001-1361">concentration</span> (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">samādhi</em>), and (5) <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-049-001-1689">wisdom</span> (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">prajñā</em>). These are similar to the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-049-001-1463">five forces</span> but in a lesser <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-049-001-1624">stage</span> of development. </p></div></div></div></div><div id="0424c860-5400-4461-987d-8901b6b7101a" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_40l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.2</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">[four kinds] of sustenance, four kinds of sustenance</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">zas bzhi</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཟས་བཞི།</span></li><li class="italic">catvārāhārāḥ</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">The <span>four kinds of sustenance</span> are the sustenance of material ingestion, the sustenance of contact, the sustenance of will, and the sustenance of consciousness.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="e418bdfb-b2bc-43d1-83f3-c08cbfd4316c" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_40t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.3</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">[noble] truth, noble truth</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’phags pa’i bden pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འཕགས་པའི་བདེན་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">ārya­satya</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">See “<span data-glossary-id="UT22084-049-001-1474">four noble truths</span>.”</p></div></div></div></div><div id="50842e77-6495-4f22-bb13-2d5616baf1ee" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_4155anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.4</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">abiding in phenomena, constancy of phenomena</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">chos gnas pa nyid, chos gnas pa nyid</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཆོས་གནས་པ་ཉིད།, ཆོས་གནས་པ་ཉིད།</span></li><li class="italic">dharmasthititā, dharmasthititā</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="e6a0be6e-94b5-468e-b115-1dfe67998b9c" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_41d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.5</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">abiding in phenomena, constancy of phenomena</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">chos gnas pa nyid, chos gnas pa nyid</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཆོས་གནས་པ་ཉིད།, ཆོས་གནས་པ་ཉིད།</span></li><li class="italic">dharmasthititā, dharmasthititā</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">Mahāvyutpatti 1719. </p></div></div></div></div><div id="93577576-cd69-4df1-bfd8-583a7b087cf8" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_41l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.6</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">absorption</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">snyoms par ’jug pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྙོམས་པར་འཇུག་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">samāpatti</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">The Sanskrit literally means “attainment,” and is used to refer specifically to meditative attainment and to particular meditative states. The Tibetan translators interpreted it as <em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">sama-āpatti</em>, which suggests the idea of “equal” or “level”; however, they also parsed it as <em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">sam-āpatti</em>, in which case it would have the sense of “concentration” or “absorption,” much like <em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">samādhi</em>, but with the added sense of “attainment.”</p></div></div></div></div><div id="71f76501-f55e-44e7-97e4-42ad298ec793" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_41t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.7</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">absorption in the state of cessation</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’gog pa la snyoms par zhugs pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འགོག་པ་ལ་སྙོམས་པར་ཞུགས་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">nirodhasamāpatti</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">See Mvyut 1500 and 1988.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="b7a96b61-49dc-47df-b835-9b316e7d9e37" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_4255anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.8</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">accept, accepted</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">len</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ལེན།</span></li><li class="italic">ādadante</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">cf. Sanskrit text in Matsuda 2013, p. 940 <em class="distinct">ad</em> Lamotte VIII.40.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="a64d208d-5bfa-47f5-977a-f3965a021305" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_42d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.9</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">acceptance that phenomena are non-arisen</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mi skye ba’i chos la bzod pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མི་སྐྱེ་བའི་ཆོས་ལ་བཟོད་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">anutpattidharmakṣānti</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">The bodhisattvas’ realization that all phenomena are unproduced and empty. It sustains them on the difficult path of benefiting all beings so that they do not succumb to the goal of personal liberation. Different sources link this realization to the first or eighth bodhisattva level (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">bhūmi</em>).</p></div></div></div></div><div id="cea59c3e-f95c-4c07-b5fd-9d2a8585bc9f" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_42l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.10</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">accomplishment of the goal</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dgos pa yongs su grub pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དགོས་པ་ཡོངས་སུ་གྲུབ་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">kṛtyānuṣṭhāna</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="0337bf7a-bb0a-4e26-bde7-6d34219dc604" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_42t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.11</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">accumulated</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">kun tu bsags pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཀུན་ཏུ་བསགས་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">ācita</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="e0126492-66c1-4460-a854-51aba7ad431b" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_4355anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.12</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">accused</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">shag kyis ’chags</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཤག་ཀྱིས་འཆགས།</span></li><li class="italic">codanā</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="f423f038-1637-4e21-908e-a2e2fb698bf2" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_43d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.13</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">activity of conditioning mental factors</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’du byed kyi ’jug pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འདུ་བྱེད་ཀྱི་འཇུག་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">saṃskārapravṛtti</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="9824d9e7-fe91-4bd2-b6a2-b0f39df50f51" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_43l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.14</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">actual defining characteristic</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">yongs su grub pa’i mtshan nyid</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཡོངས་སུ་གྲུབ་པའི་མཚན་ཉིད།</span></li><li class="italic">pari­niṣpanna­lakṣaṇa</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="15e5b656-11a1-4b39-95dd-97194159b293" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_43t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.15</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">actual essence</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">yongs su grub pa’i ngo bo nyid, yongs su grub pa’i rang bzhin</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཡོངས་སུ་གྲུབ་པའི་ངོ་བོ་ཉིད།, ཡོངས་སུ་གྲུབ་པའི་རང་བཞིན།</span></li><li class="italic">pariniṣpannasvabhāva</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="bf3c7cca-3030-4d6b-a560-9a324c4f01ee" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_4455anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.16</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">actual, pariniṣpanna</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">yongs su grub pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཡོངས་སུ་གྲུབ་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">pariniṣpanna</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">See <a href="end-notes.xhtml#UT22084-049-001-347" data-pointer-type="id">n.125</a>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="fc0adedd-0475-41e8-8e95-9e11ceafcf51" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_44d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.17</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">actualization</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mngon du bya ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མངོན་དུ་བྱ་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">sākṣātkāra</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="cf6a6985-eefe-49a3-855c-e43e7222aa79" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_44l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.18</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">actually refer to</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mngon par rjod pas rjod pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མངོན་པར་རྗོད་པས་རྗོད་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">abhivadamānā, abhivadanti</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">Mahāvyutpatti 1290. </p></div></div></div></div><div id="096578ea-4bc4-49a3-b39c-bb89d277b3ef" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_44t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.19</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">affliction</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">kun nas nyon mongs pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཀུན་ནས་ཉོན་མོངས་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">saṃkleśa</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A term meaning defilement, impurity, and pollution, broadly referring to cognitive and emotional factors that disturb and obscure the mind. As the self-perpetuating process of affliction in the minds of beings, it is a synonym for <em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">saṃsāra</em>. It is often paired with its opposite, <em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">vyavadāna</em>, meaning “purification.”</p></div></div></div></div><div id="8374849e-bf9a-4380-bfff-576677d94ca0" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_4555anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.20</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">aggregate</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">phung pho</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཕུང་ཕོ།</span></li><li class="italic">skandha</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">The five skandhas (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">pañcaskandha</em>) are: forms (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">rūpa</em>), sensation (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">vedanā</em>), <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-049-001-1362">conception</span> (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN"><span data-glossary-id="UT22084-049-001-1362">saṃjñā</span></em>), formations (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">saṃskāra</em>), consciousness (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN"><span data-glossary-id="UT22084-049-001-1353">vijñāna</span></em>).</p></div></div></div></div><div id="0074f3b5-760e-4bb9-8abf-a0e643afa24f" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_45d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.21</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">analysis, examine, examined, examining</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">brtag, brtag pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བརྟག, བརྟག་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">parīkṣā</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="6a3e4d93-90b0-491e-b354-c6a7d952e5b4" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_45l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.22</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">analysis, examine, examined, examining</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">brtag, brtag pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བརྟག, བརྟག་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">parīkṣā</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="52a43376-0e37-4735-92e6-257998d83884" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_45t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.23</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">analytical knowledge</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">so sor yang dag par rig pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སོ་སོར་ཡང་དག་པར་རིག་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">pratisaṃvid</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">See Har Dayal 2004, p. 260ff.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="15dd2d8f-6f51-491a-965d-508b0ff395f0" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_4655anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.24</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">analytical knowledge of designations</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">chos so sor yang dag par rig pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཆོས་སོ་སོར་ཡང་དག་པར་རིག་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">dharma­prati­saṃvid</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="e29ef49f-aee5-4a46-a202-dc8f256325ba" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_46d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.25</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">analytical knowledge of the objects of designation</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">don so sor yang dag par rig pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དོན་སོ་སོར་ཡང་དག་པར་རིག་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">ārthapratisaṃvid</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="a0849c8e-a301-4513-9fb5-6d97229d1a4c" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_46l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.26</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">analyze, analyzing, pratyavekṣaṇa</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">so sor rtog pa, so sor rtog par byed</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སོ་སོར་རྟོག་པ།, སོ་སོར་རྟོག་པར་བྱེད།</span></li><li class="italic">pratyavekṣa, pratyavekṣaṇa</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">The term <em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">so sor rtog pa</em> has two meanings in our text: (1) <span class="ignore">analysis</span> (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">pratyavekṣa</em>) and (2) <span class="ignore">comprehension</span>, realization, <span class="ignore">awakening</span> (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">pratibodha</em>).</p></div></div></div></div><div id="838f52c4-9050-4c3a-9448-d2551bd51a3d" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_46t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.27</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">anumāṇa</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">anumāṇa</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">Technical term in Buddhist logic.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="e6e4b2ce-848f-42f6-adcd-559066db3843" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_4755anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.28</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">apariniṣpanna, unreal</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">yongs su ma grub pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཡོངས་སུ་མ་གྲུབ་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">apariniṣpanna</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">lack of [any] actuality, no actuality, deprived of any actuality, devoid of any actuality</p></div></div></div></div><div id="c55da13f-bceb-4490-9ec0-b80198240718" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_47d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.29</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">appearance</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">snang ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྣང་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">pratibhāsa</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="00274071-9887-4dfc-8f82-15ee3940b0ec" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_47l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.30</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">appearancelessness</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mtshan ma med pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མཚན་མ་མེད་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">animitta</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of the three <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-049-001-1481">gates of liberation</span> along with <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-049-001-1435">emptiness</span> and <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-049-001-1690">wishlessness</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="7bf0f602-2608-4888-b126-e4ebc8621f83" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_47t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.31</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">applications of mindfulness</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dran pa nye bar gzhag pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དྲན་པ་ཉེ་བར་གཞག་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">smṛtyupasthāna</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">The four foundations of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-049-001-1544">mindfulness</span> refers to the application of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-049-001-1544">mindfulness</span> to: the body, sensations, the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-049-001-1542">mind</span>, phenomena.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="0b062c2c-29c2-48dc-932b-48db574cedee" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_4855anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.32</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">appropriating cognition, ādānavijñāna</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">len pa’i rnam par shes pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ལེན་པའི་རྣམ་པར་ཤེས་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">ādānavijñāna</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="6091439d-40c9-41d8-bed0-be7851248498" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_48d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.33</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">argumentative disputation</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rtsod pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྩོད་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">vivāda</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="6fe5e02d-827a-47a7-b414-89aaf5d45cc8" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_48l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.34</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">aspiration</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">smon lam</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྨོན་ལམ།</span></li><li class="italic">praṇidhāna</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="976b88ab-44b3-4582-96fa-ac60354c632a" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_48t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.35</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">aspiration</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mos pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མོས་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">praṇidhāna</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="c5540d92-f1c5-48ff-9dd7-a4c9a3d8128c" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_4955anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.36</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">assumption, erroneous conception, wrongly conceive</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mngon par zhen, mngon par zhen pa, mngon par zhen pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མངོན་པར་ཞེན་པ།, མངོན་པར་ཞེན་པ།, མངོན་པར་ཞེན།</span></li><li class="italic">abhiniveśa, abhiniviśanti, abhiniviśanti</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="260d711e-0ced-438d-a03b-7923b4dc4a01" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_49d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.37</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">assumption, erroneous conception, wrongly conceive</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mngon par zhen, mngon par zhen pa, mngon par zhen pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མངོན་པར་ཞེན་པ།, མངོན་པར་ཞེན་པ།, མངོན་པར་ཞེན།</span></li><li class="italic">abhiniveśa, abhiniviśanti, abhiniviśanti</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="a3e3ca3d-5d92-43b5-bf7a-d02257107104" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_49l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.38</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">assumption, erroneous conception, wrongly conceive</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mngon par zhen, mngon par zhen pa, mngon par zhen pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མངོན་པར་ཞེན་པ།, མངོན་པར་ཞེན་པ།, མངོན་པར་ཞེན།</span></li><li class="italic">abhiniveśa, abhiniviśanti, abhiniviśanti</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">See Edgerton 1953, p. 53. The term has various shades of meaning such as “to be attached to,” “to adhere to,” “to <span class="ignore">wrongly conceive</span>,” “to hold fast to,” and “to believe in” with a negative connotation.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="65c99d4b-8378-4dbe-b737-8c27c1149218" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_49t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.39</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">attaining the powers</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">stobs bskyed pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྟོབས་བསྐྱེད་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">balādhāna</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="960917a1-b12e-4b4e-a342-001a818bf3e9" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_4a55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.40</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">attend, attending</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rjes su dpyod pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྗེས་སུ་དཔྱོད་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">anucaranti</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="f40cf7aa-6754-416b-9014-59d521983239" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_4ad5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.41</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">authoritative scripture</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">yid ches pa’i lung gi tshad ma</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཡིད་ཆེས་པའི་ལུང་གི་ཚད་མ།</span></li><li class="italic">āptāgamapramāṇa</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="17cba7f1-2de7-40eb-914b-e914b0d3cc50" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_4al5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.42</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Avaloki­teśvara, Āryāva­loki­teśvara</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">spyan ras gzigs, ’phags pa spyan ras gzigs dbang phyug</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འཕགས་པ་སྤྱན་རས་གཟིགས་དབང་ཕྱུག, སྤྱན་རས་གཟིགས།</span></li><li class="italic">avaloki­teśvara, āryāva­loki­teśvara</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of the “eight close sons of the Buddha,” he is also known as the bodhisattva who embodies compassion. In certain tantras, he is also the lord of the three families, where he embodies the compassion of the buddhas. In Tibet, he attained great significance as a special protector of Tibet, and in China, in female form, as Guanyin, the most important bodhisattva in all of East Asia.</p><p class="definition">Also mentioned in this text as <span class="ignore">Āryāva­loki­teśvara</span>, the noble <span class="ignore">Avaloki­teśvara</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="d0fda944-71f7-4a27-a806-7debbf320eea" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_4at5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.43</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">awakening</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">byang chub</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བྱང་ཆུབ།</span></li><li class="italic">bodhi</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="20e0d91d-2b54-4a47-84f8-bc4eac85f0f8" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_4b55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.44</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">awakening factors</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">byang chub kyi phyogs dang ’thun pa’i chos</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བྱང་ཆུབ་ཀྱི་ཕྱོགས་དང་འཐུན་པའི་ཆོས།</span></li><li class="italic">bodhi­pakṣya­dharma</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="c0849f08-9eba-42c8-9f16-e8ca8d34f002" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_4bd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.45</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">awakening mind, bodhicitta</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">byang chub kyi sems</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བྱང་ཆུབ་ཀྱི་སེམས།</span></li><li class="italic">bodhicitta</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">In the general Mahāyāna teachings the mind of awakening (bodhicitta) is the intention to attain the complete awakening of a perfect buddha for the sake of all beings. On the level of absolute truth, the mind of awakening is the realization of the awakened state itself.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="deddb27a-9b11-4d74-8db6-3e1ec86d3905" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_4bl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.46</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">awareness</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">shes bzhin</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཤེས་བཞིན།</span></li><li class="italic">samprajāna</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="2283dbd7-1426-4735-a42e-fa3085c70c20" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_4bt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.47</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">bahuvrīhi</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bahuvrīhi</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">Type of Sanskrit compound.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="821f306a-a110-4274-8a91-035ea30b9389" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_4c55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.48</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">bases of supernatural powers</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rdzu ’phrul gyi rkang pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྫུ་འཕྲུལ་གྱི་རྐང་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">ṛddhipādaḥ</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">The four <span class="ignore">bases of supernatural powers</span> (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">ṛddhipāda</em>, <em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">rdzu ’phrul gyi rkang pa bzhi</em>) are: (1) <span class="ignore">concentration</span> through will (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">chanda</em>, <em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">’dun pa</em>), (2) <span class="ignore">concentration</span> through <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-049-001-1682">vigor</span> (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">vīrya</em>, <em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">brtson ’grus</em>), (3) <span class="ignore">concentration</span> through the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-049-001-1542">mind</span> (<span class="ignore"><em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">citta</em></span>, <em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">bsam pa</em>), and (4) <span class="ignore">concentration</span> through <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-049-001-1516">investigation</span> (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">mīmāṃsā</em>, <em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">dpyod pa</em> ). See Rahula 2001, p. 163. </p></div></div></div></div><div id="ad3097fe-b272-4d95-8811-3cbb3824ee9e" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_4cd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.49</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">being, sentient being</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">sems can</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སེམས་ཅན།</span></li><li class="italic">sattva</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">Often rendered simply as “being.”</p></div></div></div></div><div id="84127eb5-0b6c-44c9-af0b-af8d0d8d5130" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_4cl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.50</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">belief in a perduring self</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’jig tshogs la lta ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འཇིག་ཚོགས་ལ་ལྟ་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">satkāyadṛṣṭi</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="88b90b1b-99ac-4b88-81b0-3ecc3c52d507" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_4ct5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.51</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">beryl</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bai dUr+ya</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བཻ་དཱུརྱ།</span></li><li class="italic">vaidūrya</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="b2dce9e4-3534-414a-b2d6-cff7c661c202" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_4d55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.52</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">bichiliocosm</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">stong gnyis pa bar ma’i ’jig rten gyi khams</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྟོང་གཉིས་པ་བར་མའི་འཇིག་རྟེན་གྱི་ཁམས།</span></li><li class="italic">dvitīyamadhyama sāhasralokadhātu</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">Equal to a thousand <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-049-001-1673">universes of a thousand worlds</span> (i.e., a universe of a million worlds). </p></div></div></div></div><div id="af66dd3c-6528-471c-b580-a844c4e22358" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_4dd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.53</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">binding</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’ching ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འཆིང་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">bandhana</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="1b51c11a-be57-45e7-82eb-2691bb785c0d" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_4dl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.54</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">blessed one</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bcom ldan ’das</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བཅོམ་ལྡན་འདས།</span></li><li class="italic">bhagavat, bhagavān</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p>In Buddhist literature, this is an epithet applied to buddhas, most often to Śākyamuni. The Sanskrit term generally means “possessing fortune,” but in specifically Buddhist contexts it implies that a buddha is in possession of six auspicious qualities (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">bhaga</em>) associated with complete awakening. The Tibetan term‍—where <em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">bcom</em> is said to refer to “subduing” the four māras, <em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">ldan</em> to “possessing” the great qualities of buddhahood, and <em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">’das</em> to “going beyond” saṃsāra and nirvāṇa‍—possibly reflects the commentarial tradition where the Sanskrit <em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">bhagavat</em> is interpreted, in addition, as “one who destroys the four māras.” This is achieved either by reading <em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">bhagavat</em> as <em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">bhagnavat</em> (“one who broke”), or by tracing the word <em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">bhaga</em> to the root <em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">√bhañj</em> (“to break”).</p></div></div></div></div><div id="072b1969-eda8-4f65-8019-8dc01bc43ed8" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_4dt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.55</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">body afflicted by corruption, dauṣṭhulyakāya</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">gnas ngan len gyi lus</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གནས་ངན་ལེན་གྱི་ལུས།</span></li><li class="italic">dauṣṭhulyakāya</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="e8fdd6ff-6a03-404c-ab6f-63e7897326fe" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_4e55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.56</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">branches of awakening</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">byang chub kyi yan lag</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བྱང་ཆུབ་ཀྱི་ཡན་ལག</span></li><li class="italic">bodhyaṅgāni</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">The <span class="ignore">seven branches of awakening</span> are: (1) correct <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-049-001-1544">mindfulness</span>, (2) correct <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-049-001-1419">discrimination of dharmas</span>, (3) correct <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-049-001-1682">vigor</span>, (4) correct <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-049-001-1517">joy</span>, (5) correct <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-049-001-1466">flexibility</span>, (6) <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-049-001-1384">correct concentration</span>, and (7) correct <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-049-001-1439">equanimity</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="6ffb5915-a151-47df-97a7-db6ca506d632" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_4ed5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.57</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">bring together</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">kun ’byung ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཀུན་འབྱུང་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">samudaya</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="9e16ea9a-c82c-4bd4-900b-0a953f38b0d4" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_4el5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.58</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">buddha field, buddha realm</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">sangs rgyas kyi zhing, sangs rgyas kyi zhing</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སངས་རྒྱས་ཀྱི་ཞིང་།, སངས་རྒྱས་ཀྱི་ཞིང་།</span></li><li class="italic">buddhakṣetra, buddhakṣetra</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">Also translated as “<span data-glossary-id="UT22084-049-001-1343">buddha realm</span>.”</p></div></div></div></div><div id="64d3d13d-c471-4fa9-9b50-a8bd526b8c9f" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_4et5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.59</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">buddha field, buddha realm</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">sangs rgyas kyi zhing, sangs rgyas kyi zhing</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སངས་རྒྱས་ཀྱི་ཞིང་།, སངས་རྒྱས་ཀྱི་ཞིང་།</span></li><li class="italic">buddhakṣetra, buddhakṣetra</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">Also translated as “<span data-glossary-id="UT22084-049-001-1342">buddha field</span>.”</p></div></div></div></div><div id="36bf805a-5c33-4284-97c1-2d996ab43fec" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_4f55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.60</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Buddha Stage</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">sangs rgyas kyi sa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སངས་རྒྱས་ཀྱི་ས།</span></li><li class="italic">buddhabhūmi</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">The name of a bodhisattva <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-049-001-1624">stage</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="30db83b9-fb86-44d2-ae83-c614ad5c97a0" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_4fd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.61</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">can [only] be known by intelligent scholars well versed in the subtle</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">zhib mo brtags pa’i mkhas pa dang ’dzangs pas rig pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཞིབ་མོ་བརྟགས་པའི་མཁས་པ་དང་འཛངས་པས་རིག་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">sūkṣmaṃ nipuṇapaṇḍitavijñavedanīyaḥ</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">Mahāvyutpatti 2918. </p></div></div></div></div><div id="a298f87f-32ae-4a99-8476-e193a9ff5643" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_4fl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.62</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">causal dependence</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rang dbang med pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རང་དབང་མེད་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">asvatantra</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="d07d28c6-052b-43db-8dbc-42f5c8db3a10" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_4ft5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.63</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">cause and effect</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rgyu dang ’bras bu</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྒྱུ་དང་འབྲས་བུ།</span></li><li class="italic">hetuphala</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="310909ba-dff8-4141-ac89-2e09e2900927" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_4g55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.64</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">changing opinions</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">blo gros tha dad pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བློ་གྲོས་ཐ་དད་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">matibheda</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="92cf6450-6650-463f-9a99-8d3388b470d5" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_4gd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.65</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">characterized as being beyond all speculation, ultimate beyond speculation, whose characteristic transcends all speculation, whose defining characteristic is beyond all speculation</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rtog ge thams cad las yang dag par ’das pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྟོག་གེ་ཐམས་ཅད་ལས་ཡང་དག་པར་འདས་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">sarva­tarka­samati­krānta</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="bec5686e-d233-4767-9078-f8c7919dc20d" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_4gl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.66</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">characterized as, characterized by, consisting in, constituted</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rab tu phye ba, rab tu phye ba, rab tu phye ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རབ་ཏུ་ཕྱེ་བ།, རབ་ཏུ་ཕྱེ་བ།, རབ་ཏུ་ཕྱེ་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">prabhāvita, prabhāvita, prabhāvita</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">See Schmithausen 2014, p. 557, §512.1. Also translated here as “<span data-glossary-id="UT22084-049-001-1376">consisting in</span>” and “<span data-glossary-id="UT22084-049-001-1380">constituted</span>.”</p></div></div></div></div><div id="afc53781-0387-4f04-916f-8cd48b06c476" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_4gt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.67</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">characterized as, characterized by, consisting in, constituted</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rab tu phye ba, rab tu phye ba, rab tu phye ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རབ་ཏུ་ཕྱེ་བ།, རབ་ཏུ་ཕྱེ་བ།, རབ་ཏུ་ཕྱེ་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">prabhāvita, prabhāvita, prabhāvita</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">Also translated here as “<span data-glossary-id="UT22084-049-001-1348">characterized by</span>” and “<span data-glossary-id="UT22084-049-001-1380">constituted</span>.” See Schmithausen 2014, p. 557, §512.1. </p></div></div></div></div><div id="fa830996-9c11-4cc4-9e78-6790a6dbb583" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_4h55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.68</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">characterized as, characterized by, consisting in, constituted</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rab tu phye ba, rab tu phye ba, rab tu phye ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རབ་ཏུ་ཕྱེ་བ།, རབ་ཏུ་ཕྱེ་བ།, རབ་ཏུ་ཕྱེ་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">prabhāvita, prabhāvita, prabhāvita</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">See Schmithausen 2014, p. 557, §512.1. Also translated here as “<span data-glossary-id="UT22084-049-001-1348">characterized by</span>” and “<span data-glossary-id="UT22084-049-001-1376">consisting in</span>.”</p></div></div></div></div><div id="b667709c-9e2a-4877-96d5-8b056867ac96" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_4hd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.69</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">citta, mind</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">sems</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སེམས།</span></li><li class="italic">citta</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="557f7fb5-0f01-4df5-a0cf-f1a986c41349" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_4hl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.70</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">clarified butter</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mar gyi snying khu</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མར་གྱི་སྙིང་ཁུ།</span></li><li class="italic">sarpirmaṇḍa</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">Mahāvyutpatti 5683. </p></div></div></div></div><div id="9031e045-bf36-49cb-a90d-7cae16379e65" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_4ht5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.71</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">clear mindfulness</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">gsal ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གསལ་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">paṭu</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="96980ca8-70b9-4221-b15e-7c9d9c0035f6" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_4i55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.72</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Cloud of Dharma</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">chos kyi sprin</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཆོས་ཀྱི་སྤྲིན།</span></li><li class="italic">dharmameghā</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">The name of a bodhisattva <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-049-001-1624">stage</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="5f669fb2-a2c6-4bc5-b5ca-d59b153c1134" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_4id5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.73</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">cognition that is personal and intuitive</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">so sor rang rig pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སོ་སོར་རང་རིག་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">pratyātmajñāna, pratyātmavedanīya, pratyātmavedya, prātyatmam</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="2f9b275a-4384-48e1-82d5-36ad42fe9878" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_4il5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.74</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">cognition, vijñāna</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rnam par shes pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྣམ་པར་ཤེས་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">vijñāna</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="e28dd000-748d-4ed1-891a-38e0434f282a" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_4it5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.75</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">collection of teachings on the bodhisattva [path]</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">byang chub sems dpa’i sde snod</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བྱང་ཆུབ་སེམས་དཔའི་སྡེ་སྣོད།</span></li><li class="italic">bodhisattvapiṭaka</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="29817c3c-4480-49e7-898c-dc83946daf00" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_4j55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.76</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">communication</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ming du bya ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མིང་དུ་བྱ་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">saṃjñāpya</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="5722d5a4-f634-4bf9-8ff7-02c6f7cb8f1f" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_4jd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.77</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">complete equanimity</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">lhag par btang snyoms</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ལྷག་པར་བཏང་སྙོམས།</span></li><li class="italic">adhyupekṣya</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="642a2578-7627-4a96-9a66-fa70dd6d8fd8" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_4jl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.78</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">completely</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">thams cad kyi thams cad</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཐམས་ཅད་ཀྱི་ཐམས་ཅད།</span></li><li class="italic">sarveṇa sarvam</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">Mahāvyutpatti 6405.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="f906d3b1-54d9-404c-b6f8-61b44462c590" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_4jt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.79</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">comprehension</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">yongs su shes pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཡོངས་སུ་ཤེས་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">parijñā</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="fd605d5b-64e4-4b17-b210-6105958d064e" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_4k55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.80</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">concentrated</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mnyam par bzhag pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མཉམ་པར་བཞག་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">samāhita</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A state of deep <span>concentration</span> in which the mind is absorbed in its object to such a degree that conceptual thought is suspended. It is sometimes interpreted as settling (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">āhita</em>) the mind in equanimity (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">sama</em>).</p></div></div></div></div><div id="fec7c7f4-838e-4999-8c42-00a65490e047" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_4kd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.81</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">concentration</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ting nge ’dzin</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཏིང་ངེ་འཛིན།</span></li><li class="italic">samādhi</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">In a general sense, <em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">samādhi</em> can describe a number of different meditative states. In the Mahāyāna literature, in particular in the Prajñāpāramitā sūtras, we find extensive lists of different samādhis, numbering over one hundred.</p><p class="definition">In a more restricted sense, and when understood as a mental state, <em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">samādhi</em> is defined as the one-pointedness of the mind (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">cittaikāgratā</em>), the ability to remain on the same object over long periods of time. The <cite class="title text-en" lang="en">Drajor Bamponyipa</cite> (<cite class="title text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">sgra sbyor bam po gnyis pa</cite>) commentary on the <cite class="title break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">Mahāvyutpatti</cite> explains the term <em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">samādhi</em> as referring to the instrument through which mind and mental states “get collected,” i.e., it is by the force of samādhi that the continuum of mind and mental states becomes collected on a single point of reference without getting distracted.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="2e4fa357-8441-4161-a3b9-d398d2f9936e" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_4kl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.82</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">conception, investigate, investigating, mental engagement, vitarka</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rtog pa, rtog pa, rtog pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྟོག་པ།, རྟོག་པ།, རྟོག་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">kalpanā, vitarka, vitarka</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="03c0c712-ce56-4808-944d-648a25c3913e" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_4kt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.83</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">conception, investigate, investigating, mental engagement, vitarka</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rtog pa, rtog pa, rtog pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྟོག་པ།, རྟོག་པ།, རྟོག་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">kalpanā, vitarka, vitarka</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">Also translated here as “<span data-glossary-id="UT22084-049-001-1536">mental engagement</span>.”</p></div></div></div></div><div id="b260d4ed-1d68-4114-a625-827ee94e4053" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_4l55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.84</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">conception, investigate, investigating, mental engagement, vitarka</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rtog pa, rtog pa, rtog pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྟོག་པ།, རྟོག་པ།, རྟོག་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">kalpanā, vitarka, vitarka</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">Also translated here as “<span data-glossary-id="UT22084-049-001-1515">investigating</span>.”</p></div></div></div></div><div id="a3757d91-e567-4ade-97ce-e3d6488dcec6" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_4ld5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.85</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">conception, saṃjñā</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’du shes</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འདུ་ཤེས།</span></li><li class="italic">saṃjñā</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="246a0eb5-4b80-4bcc-aa5d-ae60c274b356" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_4ll5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.86</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">conceptualization</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rnam par rtog pa, rnam rtog</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྣམ་པར་རྟོག་པ།, རྣམ་རྟོག</span></li><li class="italic">vikalpa</li></ul></div></div></div><div id="849eab88-55ca-4ea5-b91f-cd427d9d9e81" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_4lt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.87</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">conceptualize, decide, designation</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">btags pa, gdags pa, gdags pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གདགས་པ།, གདགས་པ།, བཏགས་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">prajñapti, prajñapti, prajñapti</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">Also translated here as “<span data-glossary-id="UT22084-049-001-1387">decide</span>.”</p></div></div></div></div><div id="51155bb1-2098-44df-809d-771de9b1ee1a" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button typ