he notion that phenomena have a \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":264,\"end\":326}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"defining characteristic\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":326,\"end\":349},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"f4503be0-02d4-474f-8f1c-a69993648574\",\"uuid\":\"2841a2ca-615e-4ab1-a882-f642ea93263f\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" to teach the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":349,\"end\":363}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"essencelessness\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":363,\"end\":378},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"511f85e3-f5bd-4380-81c7-87048ba56676\",\"uuid\":\"16779030-d9b5-4d71-97d4-5f43d17a24c5\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" of these \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":378,\"end\":388}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"defining characteristics\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":388,\"end\":412},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"f4503be0-02d4-474f-8f1c-a69993648574\",\"uuid\":\"c2f05d7e-5f9f-4fc0-bda8-0d8eee844fc9\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" in a series of teachings such as the five \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":412,\"end\":455}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"aggregates\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":455,\"end\":465},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"8374849e-bf9a-4380-bfff-576677d94ca0\",\"uuid\":\"d4b26d15-ae11-484e-a1a5-4b96f1e67cf3\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", the twelve \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":465,\"end\":478}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"sense domains\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":478,\"end\":491},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"9661ded2-d387-44b2-87c7-3ebbaff2eb52\",\"uuid\":\"f23f1d2f-1b94-4a19-aea0-79e447a232f8\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", and so on (see also \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":491,\"end\":513}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"4.1–6\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":513,\"end\":518},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"internalLink\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"688de6f0-52bc-4c60-b79b-09e8ccb4b6e5\",\"href\":\"/entity/passage/592fa1a1-8b49-4a45-b8c1-c3806aa83272\",\"entity\":\"592fa1a1-8b49-4a45-b8c1-c3806aa83272\",\"type\":\"passage\",\"toh\":null,\"isSameWork\":true,\"subtype\":\"translation\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"). In our metaphor on virtual reality, one could see these teachings as being expounded on the basis of the very \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":518,\"end\":631}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"imaginary\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":631,\"end\":640},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"edcb7462-a8a5-4667-9736-fa1dba77154b\",\"uuid\":\"0605e997-e005-4c69-b41d-452592a6244e\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" phenomena conceptualized as truly existing. When children experience a nightmare, their parents show that the monster does not exist by implicitly, i.e. provisionally, accepting its existence, saying, “Look! It is not there.” (2) The second turning of the wheel teaches the first aspect of \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":640,\"end\":931}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"essencelessness with regard to the ultimate\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":931,\"end\":974},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"664120b2-4588-4b3e-9632-3c7586b13cad\",\"uuid\":\"a483f89a-6e04-497d-a099-4bb94ad4cdf8\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", stating that phenomena are \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":974,\"end\":1003}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"unborn\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1003,\"end\":1009},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"760ae48f-4c62-4d01-9846-06e850f94816\",\"uuid\":\"a14a768c-94c7-49b0-bf28-7129c032b1f6\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". From this perspective, the primordial selflessness of phenomena is still taught in relation to dualistic phenomena. As a consequence, \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1009,\"end\":1145}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Para­mārtha­samud­gata\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1145,\"end\":1167},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"537e957c-58b2-4ce7-88cc-ad811243d1ba\",\"uuid\":\"98115ada-91de-4f23-82a7-465c0b8551a8\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" considers this cycle of teachings as provisional. (3) The third turning of the wheel aims at teaching the second aspect of \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1167,\"end\":1291}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"essencelessness with regard to the ultimate\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1291,\"end\":1334},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"664120b2-4588-4b3e-9632-3c7586b13cad\",\"uuid\":\"acc16309-3cc1-4394-82de-1620ab1d8381\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" in a way that is not limited to the domain of dualistic phenomena. To pursue our metaphor, this third cycle of teachings gives a complete overview of the three \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1334,\"end\":1495}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"defining characteristics\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1495,\"end\":1519},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"f4503be0-02d4-474f-8f1c-a69993648574\",\"uuid\":\"8a96b370-8b05-45fb-8192-79103b91ae9d\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" of phenomena: the completely \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1519,\"end\":1549}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"imaginary\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1549,\"end\":1558},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"edcb7462-a8a5-4667-9736-fa1dba77154b\",\"uuid\":\"de5d4528-cba1-4091-bd80-6a83cff5a1c8\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" experience of a virtual reality, the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1558,\"end\":1596}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"magic illusion\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1596,\"end\":1610},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"2ce48dfb-9147-4d14-9059-2860bd12bbb6\",\"uuid\":\"79297a24-fb42-4685-b3b3-c306df9ad32f\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" of the projecting \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1610,\"end\":1629}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"mind\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1629,\"end\":1633},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"b667709c-9e2a-4877-96d5-8b056867ac96\",\"uuid\":\"df1c5308-6c09-41a5-b6c7-cad5b4ae625d\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", and the primordial domain of \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1633,\"end\":1664}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"gnosis\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1664,\"end\":1670},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"b36258b5-bd30-4205-aeeb-75bac743076f\",\"uuid\":\"8f81b760-6e5d-488c-beca-fbef3f5151ad\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1670,\"end\":1672}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Para­mārtha­samud­gata\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1672,\"end\":1694},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"537e957c-58b2-4ce7-88cc-ad811243d1ba\",\"uuid\":\"f0da0914-816b-4c58-84ad-7dcb4f7fd946\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" declares the third turning to be of definitive meaning.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1694,\"end\":1750}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"2c578e2c-2150-49c3-9b0b-0ebe53a52644\",\"sort\":740,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"label\":\"i.15\",\"alignments\":{}},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":628,\"uuid\":\"2c578e2c-2150-49c3-9b0b-0ebe53a52644\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"It is worth noting that the doctrine of the three \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":50}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"defining characteristics\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":50,\"end\":74},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"f4503be0-02d4-474f-8f1c-a69993648574\",\"uuid\":\"357477e0-49a0-4504-b238-af5e1692ec5b\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" can be seen as delineating three great categories of soteriological approaches found in Indo-Tibetan Buddhist traditions: (1) the deconstruction of putative notions of an individual self through mereological and relational strateg